const a=[{id:"baby",label:"婴儿阶段",range:"0-12 个月",color:"#E8A87C"},{id:"toddler",label:"幼儿阶段",range:"13-24 个月",color:"#C38D9E"},{id:"bigToddler",label:"大幼儿阶段",range:"25-36 个月",color:"#7FB685"},{id:"preschool",label:"学前阶段",range:"37-60 个月",color:"#6C8EAD"}],o=[{id:"looker",name:"The Looker",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-looker",ageRange:"0-12 周",ageRangeEn:"0-12 weeks",ageMonths:"0-3m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#E8A87C",bgColor:"#FFF5EE",lightColor:"#FDEEE3",description:"新生儿的世界像一台没调好频道的老电视——视力只有0.01-0.02，20-30厘米以外的东西都是一团模糊色块。但他对一样东西有天然的敏锐感：高对比度。黑白分明的图案、你的发际线、光线穿过百叶窗投下的条纹——这些是他最先能「看见」的世界。",descriptionEn:"A newborn's world is like an old, untuned television—their vision is only about 0.01-0.02, and anything beyond 20-30 centimeters is a blurry mess of color. But they have a natural acuity for one thing: high contrast. Stark black and white patterns, your hairline, the stripes of light coming through the blinds—these are the first things they can truly 'see' in the world.",toys:[{name:"黑白床铃",englishName:"The Mobile",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"把它挂在宝宝的婴儿床或更换台上方，让宝宝躺着看。床铃会轻轻旋转，黑白和彩色的图案可以吸引宝宝的注意力，让他/她练习追视。",developmentGoal:"促进宝宝的视觉发育和专注力，帮助他们学习追蹤移动的物体，并随着成长识别不同的颜色和形状。",parentReview:"很多家长说宝宝完全被这个床铃迷住了，会盯着看很久。质量很好，设计也很漂亮。缺点是需要自己另外购买挂钩或支架来悬挂。",howToUseEn:"Hang it above your baby's crib or changing table for them to watch while lying down. The mobile will gently rotate, and the black, white, and colorful patterns can capture your baby's attention, helping them practice visual tracking.",developmentGoalEn:"Promotes your baby's visual development and concentration, helps them learn to track moving objects, and, as they grow, to recognize different colors and shapes.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say their babies are completely mesmerized by this mobile and will stare at it for a long time. The quality is excellent, and the design is beautiful. The downside is that you need to purchase a hook or stand separately to hang it."},{name:"感官连接环",englishName:"Sensory Links",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"可以将这些连接环串在一起，挂在游戏垫、婴儿车或汽车座椅上，让宝宝抓握、摇晃和探索。每个环都有不同的质地和声音，比如摇铃声和沙沙声，可以给宝宝带来丰富的感官刺激。",developmentGoal:"锻炼宝宝的抓握能力和手眼协调能力，并通过不同的声音和材质促进其听觉和触觉发展。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具非常实用，可以挂在任何地方，宝宝很喜欢抓握和啃咬。质量很好，即使宝宝用力拉扯也不容易损坏。有些家长提到，如果能有更多鲜艳的颜色会更好。",howToUseEn:"You can string these links together and hang them on a play mat, stroller, or car seat for your baby to grasp, shake, and explore. Each link has a different texture and sound, like rattling and crinkling, providing rich sensory stimulation for your baby.",developmentGoalEn:"Exercises your baby's grasping ability and hand-eye coordination, and promotes their auditory and tactile development through different sounds and materials.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this toy very practical as it can be hung anywhere, and babies love to grasp and chew on it. The quality is great, and it doesn't break easily even when pulled hard. Some parents mentioned that it would be better if there were more bright colors."},{name:"简单黑白卡片",englishName:"Simple Black & White Card Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"将卡片放在宝宝面前，或者配合卡片支架，在宝宝练习趴着的时候给他看。高对比度的图案可以有效吸引新生儿的注意力。",developmentGoal:"刺激新生儿正在发育的视力，帮助他们练习对焦和识别简单的形状。",parentReview:"很多家长反映宝宝非常喜欢看这些卡片，能有效安抚宝宝并延长趴着的时间。卡片本身比较薄，容易被弄弯。",howToUseEn:"Place the cards in front of your baby, or use them with the card holder, to show them while they are practicing tummy time. The high-contrast patterns can effectively capture a newborn's attention.",developmentGoalEn:"Stimulates a newborn's developing vision, helping them practice focusing and recognizing simple shapes.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report that their babies love looking at these cards, which can effectively soothe them and extend tummy time. The cards themselves are quite thin and can be easily bent."},{name:"卡片支架",englishName:"Standing Card Holder",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"用来支撑黑白卡片，方便宝宝在趴着或躺着时观看。可以轻松折叠，方便携带和存放。",developmentGoal:"辅助进行视觉刺激，并鼓励宝宝在趴着时抬头，锻炼颈部和背部肌肉。",parentReview:"家长们认为这个支架非常实用，是进行Tummy Time的好帮手。但也有评论说支架的设计可能会让卡片轻微弯曲。",howToUseEn:"Use this to hold up the black and white cards, making it easy for your baby to see them during tummy time or while lying down. It folds easily for convenient portability and storage.",developmentGoalEn:"Aids in visual stimulation and encourages your baby to lift their head during tummy time, strengthening their neck and back muscles.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this holder very useful and a great helper for Tummy Time. However, some reviews mention that the design of the holder might cause the cards to bend slightly."},{name:"复杂黑白卡片",englishName:"Complex Black & White Card Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"在宝宝熟悉了简单图案后，可以引入这些更复杂的黑白卡片，持续提供视觉刺激。同样可以配合卡片支架使用。",developmentGoal:"随着宝宝视觉能力的发展，提供更复杂的视觉信息，促进大脑认知和模式识别能力的发展。",parentReview:"家长们表示，随着宝宝长大，这些更复杂的图案确实更能吸引他们的注意力。和简单卡片一样，材质偏薄是主要的抱怨点。",howToUseEn:"After your baby becomes familiar with the simple patterns, you can introduce these more complex black and white cards to continue providing visual stimulation. They can also be used with the card holder.",developmentGoalEn:"As your baby's visual abilities develop, these cards provide more complex visual information, promoting cognitive development and pattern recognition skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents have noted that as their babies grow, these more complex patterns do indeed capture their attention more effectively. Like the simple cards, the main complaint is that the material is on the thin side."},{name:"黑白手套",englishName:"Black & White Mittens",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"给宝宝戴上这个黑白条纹的手套，让他/她自然地观察自己的小手。当宝宝挥舞手臂时，高对比度的图案会吸引他/她的注意力。",developmentGoal:"促进宝宝对自己的身体，特别是双手的认知，是身体意识发展的早期阶段。同时也能锻炼宝宝的视觉追踪能力。",parentReview:"一些家长觉得这个手套很可爱，能吸引宝宝看自己的手。但也有不少家长反映，宝宝对手套的兴趣不大，或者手套很容易掉下来。属于比较有争议的一款玩具。",howToUseEn:"Put these black and white striped mittens on your baby to let them naturally observe their own little hands. When your baby waves their arms, the high-contrast pattern will attract their attention.",developmentGoalEn:"Promotes your baby's awareness of their own body, especially their hands, which is an early stage of body awareness development. It also helps exercise your baby's visual tracking skills.",parentReviewEn:"Some parents find these mittens cute and effective at getting their baby to look at their hands. However, many others report that their baby isn't very interested in the mittens, or that they fall off easily. This is a more controversial toy."},{name:"木制书",englishName:"Wooden Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是宝宝的第一本书，由可持续采伐的木材制成。家长可以抱着宝宝，一页一页地翻给他看，并描述书上的黑白动物图案，让宝宝感受书本的质感。",developmentGoal:"向宝宝介绍书本的概念，鼓励探索，并为早期的语言启蒙和阅读习惯打下基础。坚固的材质也适合宝宝出牙期啃咬。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这本书非常独特和耐用，不怕宝宝撕咬。有些宝宝很早就对它表现出兴趣，喜欢看上面的图案。也有家长说，宝宝在几个月大时对它兴趣一般，但稍大一点后开始喜欢上它。",howToUseEn:"This is your baby's first book, made from sustainably harvested wood. You can hold your baby and flip through the pages, describing the black and white animal patterns and letting your baby feel the texture of the book.",developmentGoalEn:"Introduces the concept of a book to your baby, encourages exploration, and lays the foundation for early language development and reading habits. The sturdy material is also suitable for teething babies to chew on.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this book to be very unique and durable, and they don't have to worry about their baby tearing or chewing it. Some babies show interest in it very early on and enjoy looking at the patterns. Other parents say their baby wasn't very interested in it at a few months old, but started to like it as they got a little older."},{name:"带可拆卸球的硅胶摇铃",englishName:"Silicone Rattle With Removable Ball",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个摇铃很容易让小手抓握，可以鼓励宝宝练习双手协作。摇晃时会发出柔和的声音，里面的小球还可以拿出来单独玩，既是摇铃也是牙胶。",developmentGoal:"锻炼宝宝的抓握能力、手眼协调能力和听觉追踪能力。可拆卸的设计也为宝宝提供了解决问题的早期练习。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具设计得很好，宝宝很早就学会抓握它。声音很柔和，不会过分刺激。可拆卸的小球增加了玩法，也很受宝宝欢迎。作为牙胶也很安全。",howToUseEn:"This rattle is easy for little hands to grasp and encourages your baby to practice bilateral coordination. It makes a soft sound when shaken, and the small ball inside can be taken out to play with separately. It's both a rattle and a teether.",developmentGoalEn:"Exercises your baby's grasping ability, hand-eye coordination, and auditory tracking skills. The removable design also provides an early problem-solving exercise for your baby.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this toy is well-designed, and their babies learn to grasp it early on. The sound is soft and not overly stimulating. The removable ball adds to the play value and is also very popular with babies. It's also safe as a teether."}]},{id:"charmer",name:"The Charmer",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-charmer",ageRange:"3-4 个月",ageRangeEn:"3-4 months",ageMonths:"3-4m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#E09F7D",bgColor:"#FFF3EC",lightColor:"#FDEADF",description:"3-4个月的宝宝解锁了人生第一个社交技能——社交性微笑。不是之前那种无意识的嘴角抽动，是看到你就咧嘴笑、嘴里还发出「啊咕」声回应你说话的那种真笑。手开始有意识地朝面前的东西伸过去，趴趴时间也从「放下就哭」变成能撑个几分钟了。",descriptionEn:'At 3 to 4 months old, your baby unlocks their first social skill—the social smile. This isn’t just an unconscious twitch of the lips anymore; it’s a genuine smile that lights up their face when they see you, often accompanied by sweet little coos like "ah-gu" in response to your voice. Their hands start reaching out intentionally toward things in front of them, and tummy time improves from immediate fussiness to lasting a few minutes comfortably.',toys:[{name:"木制摇铃",englishName:"Wooden Rattle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"摇动摇铃，让宝宝追视和追声，锻炼宝宝的视觉和听觉能力。也可以让宝宝自己抓握，锻炼手部精细动作。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝练习视觉追踪和声音处理，同时锻炼手部力量和抓握能力。",parentReview:"很多家长表示，这款木制摇铃是经典玩具，宝宝很喜欢。但也有家长担心，宝宝可能会用它砸到自己的脸。",howToUseEn:"Shake the rattle to encourage your baby to track both sight and sound, helping develop their visual and auditory skills. You can also let your baby grasp it independently to strengthen fine motor skills in their hands.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps your baby practice visual tracking and sound processing while strengthening hand muscles and grip skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this wooden rattle is a classic toy that their babies really enjoy. However, some parents worry that their little ones might accidentally hit their own faces with it."},{name:"硅胶三重牙胶和有机出牙布",englishName:"Silicone Triple Teether & Organic Teething Cloth",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"让宝宝啃咬不同质地的牙胶，缓解出牙期的不适。可以将出牙布冷藏后给宝宝使用，舒缓牙龈。",developmentGoal:"促进宝宝的感官、语言和口腔运动发展。",parentReview:"家长们认为这款牙胶设计很好，有多种质地，可以满足宝宝不同时期的需求。有机出牙布也很受欢迎，可以冷藏后使用。",howToUseEn:"Let your baby chew on teething toys with different textures to help ease the discomfort during teething. You can also chill a teething cloth in the fridge before giving it to your baby to soothe their gums.",developmentGoalEn:"Supports your baby’s sensory, language, and oral motor development.",parentReviewEn:"Parents appreciate that this teether is thoughtfully designed with multiple textures to suit their baby’s different stages. The organic teething cloth is also popular, especially since it can be chilled for soothing relief."},{name:"滚动铃铛",englishName:"Rolling Bell",category:"感官/大运动",categoryEn:"Sensory/Gross Motor",howToUse:"在宝宝趴着的时候，将滚动铃铛放在宝宝面前，鼓励宝宝抬头和伸手去够。也可以在地板上滚动，吸引宝宝爬行。",developmentGoal:"鼓励宝宝在俯卧时间抬头和翻身，锻炼宝宝的粗大运动技能和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"很多家长说这款滚动铃铛是宝宝练习趴着和翻身的神器。但也有家长提到，如果宝宝还不能很好地控制头部，可能会在玩的时候磕到头。",howToUseEn:"When your baby is lying on their tummy, place the rolling bell toy in front of them to encourage them to lift their head and reach out. You can also roll it along the floor to attract your baby to crawl toward it.",developmentGoalEn:"Encourage your baby to lift their head and roll over during tummy time to help develop their gross motor skills and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this rolling bell toy is a great aid for babies practicing tummy time and rolling over. However, some also mention that if a baby hasn’t yet developed good head control, they might bump their head while playing."},{name:"软布书",englishName:"Soft Book",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"和宝宝一起翻阅软布书，可以指着书中的图片给宝宝讲故事，也可以让宝宝自己探索书中的不同材质和声音。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的阅读兴趣，促进亲子关系，同时锻炼宝宝的感官和精细动作。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为Lovevery的布书质量很好，内容也很有趣。但也有家长觉得，对于小月龄的宝宝来说，书本的互动性稍显不足。",howToUseEn:"Looking through a soft cloth book with your baby is a wonderful way to bond. You can point to the pictures and tell stories, or let your little one explore the different textures and sounds on their own.",developmentGoalEn:"Foster your baby's love for reading, strengthen your parent-child bond, and help develop their sensory and fine motor skills all at once.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally agree that Lovevery’s cloth books are of high quality and feature engaging content. However, some feel that the books offer slightly less interactive elements for very young infants."},{name:"镜子卡片",englishName:"Mirror Card",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"将镜子卡片放在宝宝面前，让宝宝观察自己的脸。也可以和宝宝一起做鬼脸，增加互动。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝建立自我认知，促进社交和情感发展。",parentReview:"家长们觉得镜子卡片是很好的互动玩具，可以吸引宝宝的注意力。",howToUseEn:"Place the mirror card in front of your baby so they can observe their own face. You can also make funny faces together to boost interaction and make it more fun.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps your baby build self-awareness and supports their social and emotional development.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find mirror cards to be excellent interactive toys that effectively capture their babies’ attention."},{name:"黑白红卡片",englishName:"Black, White, & Red Card Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"在宝宝清醒的时候，将卡片放在宝宝眼前20-30厘米处，让宝宝追视。可以慢慢移动卡片，锻炼宝宝的视觉追踪能力。",developmentGoal:"刺激宝宝的视觉发育，帮助宝宝建立新的大脑连接。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，新生儿对这些高对比度的卡片非常感兴趣，可以有效安抚宝宝情绪。",howToUseEn:"When your baby is awake, hold the card about 20-30 centimeters in front of their eyes and encourage them to follow it with their gaze. You can slowly move the card to help develop their visual tracking skills.",developmentGoalEn:"Stimulate your baby’s visual development and support the formation of new brain connections.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents have noticed that newborns are very captivated by these high-contrast cards, which can effectively soothe their little ones."},{name:"“会说话”的书",englishName:"'Talking' Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"模仿书中的声音和词语，和宝宝进行“对话”，鼓励宝宝发声。",developmentGoal:"促进宝宝的语言发展和沟通能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这本书可以很好地引导宝宝发声，但需要家长投入时间和精力与宝宝互动。",howToUseEn:"Imitate the sounds and words from the book to “converse” with your baby, encouraging them to vocalize.",developmentGoalEn:"Supports your baby’s language development and communication skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents feel this book is great for encouraging their little ones to vocalize, though it does require them to spend time and actively engage with their baby."},{name:"皱纹袋",englishName:"Crinkle Bag",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"让宝宝抓握、揉捏皱纹袋，感受不同材质和声音。也可以在袋子里放一些小玩具，让宝宝练习取出和放入。",developmentGoal:"锻炼宝宝的听觉和触觉，以及手部精细动作。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个袋子很有趣，宝宝喜欢它发出的声音。但也有家长认为，这个袋子有点简单，性价比不高。",howToUseEn:"Encourage your baby to grasp and squeeze wrinkle bags to explore different textures and sounds. You can also place small toys inside the bags for your little one to practice taking them out and putting them back in.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps develop your baby’s auditory and tactile senses, as well as fine motor skills in their hands.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this bag quite interesting, and their little ones enjoy the sounds it makes. However, some parents feel the bag is a bit simple and doesn’t offer great value for the price."},{name:"橡胶三角牙胶",englishName:"Rubber Triangle Teether",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"提供给宝宝啃咬，以缓解出牙期间的不适。其三角形的形状和纹理有助于宝宝抓握和探索。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝发展口腔运动技能，为将来的语言发展做准备，同时锻炼手部抓握能力。",parentReview:"家长们喜欢这款牙胶的材质和形状，认为它对宝宝出牙很有帮助。",howToUseEn:"Designed for babies to chew on, helping to soothe discomfort during teething. Its triangular shape and textured surface make it easy for little hands to grasp and explore.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps your baby develop oral motor skills to support future speech development, while also strengthening hand grasping abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Parents appreciate the material and shape of this teether, finding it very helpful for their baby’s teething process."},{name:"手传手圆盘",englishName:"Hand-to-Hand Discs",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"鼓励宝宝用一只手抓住圆盘，然后传递到另一只手。这个过程有助于宝宝练习双手协调。",developmentGoal:"促进宝宝的双手协调能力和跨身体中线的能力，这是许多后续技能（如穿衣、吃饭）的基础。",parentReview:"家长们认为这是一个经典的蒙特梭利玩具，对于宝宝发展双手协调性非常有益。",howToUseEn:"Encourage your baby to grasp the disc with one hand and then pass it to the other. This activity helps them practice coordinating both hands.",developmentGoalEn:"Encouraging your baby’s hand coordination and the ability to cross the midline of their body lays the foundation for many future skills like dressing and eating.",parentReviewEn:"Parents consider this a classic Montessori toy that greatly supports the development of hand coordination in babies."},{name:"带框镜子",englishName:"Framed Mirror",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"将镜子放在宝宝面前，鼓励宝宝在俯卧时抬头看自己。",developmentGoal:"增强宝宝的视觉和自我意识，并激励宝宝在俯卧时抬头，加强颈部和背部肌肉。",parentReview:"家长们发现这个镜子对延长宝宝的俯卧时间很有帮助，宝宝对自己很感兴趣。",howToUseEn:"Place a mirror in front of your baby to encourage them to lift their head and look at themselves while on their tummy.",developmentGoalEn:"Enhance your baby’s visual and self-awareness while encouraging them to lift their head during tummy time, strengthening neck and back muscles.",parentReviewEn:"Parents have found that this mirror helps extend their baby’s tummy time, as babies become very interested in their own reflection."}]},{id:"senser",name:"The Senser",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-senser",ageRange:"5-6 个月",ageRangeEn:"5-6 months",ageMonths:"5-6m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#D89568",bgColor:"#FFF1E8",lightColor:"#FDE7DA",description:"5-6个月的宝宝开始能坐了，双手解锁了新技能——左手拿东西递给右手。这个月龄最标志性的变化是对因果关系着了迷——发现按一下会响、拉一下会动，那种「我做了什么居然有反应」的惊喜表情让你觉得他发现了宇宙的真理。",descriptionEn:"Babies at 5-6 months are starting to sit up, and their hands have unlocked a new skill—passing objects from their left hand to their right. The most iconic change at this age is their fascination with cause and effect—they discover that pressing something makes a sound and pulling something makes it move. That surprised look on their face, as if they've discovered a universal truth when they realize 'I did something and it reacted,' is priceless.",toys:[{name:"旋转彩虹",englishName:"Spinning Rainbow",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"把它放在宝宝面前，轻轻拨动，让彩虹滚轮旋转起来，吸引宝宝的注意力。你可以在宝宝趴着的时候玩给他看，也可以鼓励他自己伸手去拨动，锻炼他的小手肌肉。快速旋转时，彩色的木条会像瀑布一样，非常漂亮。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作技能、手眼协调能力和因果关系认知。同时，鲜艳的色彩也能刺激宝宝的视觉发育。",parentReview:"很多家长说这是宝宝最喜欢的玩具之一，宝宝很喜欢看它旋转。但也有一些家长反映，宝宝一开始可能对它兴趣不大，或者觉得木头转动的声音有点大。总体来说，这是一个很经典、很受欢迎的玩具，只是可能需要家长引导一下。",howToUseEn:"Place it in front of your baby and give it a gentle spin to make the rainbow wheel rotate and capture their attention. You can show it to your baby during tummy time or encourage them to reach out and spin it themselves, exercising their small hand muscles. When spun quickly, the colorful wooden slats look like a beautiful waterfall.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and understanding of cause and effect. At the same time, the bright colors stimulate their visual development.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this is one of their baby's favorite toys, and they love watching it spin. However, some parents have reported that their baby might not be very interested in it at first, or that the sound of the spinning wood is a bit loud. Overall, it's a classic and popular toy, but it might require some guidance from parents."},{name:"魔术纸巾盒",englishName:"Magic Tissue Box",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"把不同材质的“纸巾”塞进木盒子里，然后鼓励宝宝把它们一张一张地抽出来。你也可以和宝宝玩“放回去”的游戏，虽然一开始他可能更喜欢“只出不进”。这个游戏可以玩很久，宝宝会乐此不疲。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具能很好地锻炼宝宝的手指精细动作和手眼协调能力。通过抽取和触摸不同材质的“纸巾”，宝宝的感官也得到了发展，同时理解了“有”和“没有”的客体永久性概念。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具是“娃的挚爱”，因为宝宝天生就喜欢抽纸巾，这个玩具正好满足了他们的欲望，而且还能重复玩，很环保。不过也有家长说，把纸巾塞回去有点费劲，而且宝宝玩的时候需要大人帮忙按着盒子，不然整个盒子都会被拽走。",howToUseEn:"Stuff the different textured 'tissues' into the wooden box and encourage your baby to pull them out one by one. You can also play a 'put it back' game with your baby, although they might prefer 'only taking out' at first. This game can be played for a long time, and your baby will enjoy it endlessly.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy is great for developing your baby's fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination. By pulling out and touching the different textured 'tissues,' your baby's senses are also developed, and they begin to understand the concept of object permanence—'there' and 'not there.'",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally consider this toy a 'baby's favorite' because babies naturally love pulling tissues. This toy satisfies their desire, is reusable, and environmentally friendly. However, some parents say that stuffing the tissues back in is a bit difficult, and an adult needs to hold the box while the baby plays, otherwise the whole box gets pulled away."},{name:"魔术纸巾",englishName:"Magic Tissues",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"这些是搭配魔术纸巾盒使用的“纸巾”，但也可以单独玩。你可以用它和宝宝玩躲猫猫的游戏，或者把它系在什么地方让宝宝拉扯。因为是有机棉的，所以宝宝放在嘴里咬也没关系。",developmentGoal:"通过拉扯、触摸和啃咬，宝宝的感官知觉和精细动作得到发展。玩躲猫猫游戏还能帮助宝宝理解客体永久性，并促进社交和情感发展。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个设计很贴心，既能满足宝宝抽纸巾的爱好，又安全卫生。有些家长说，他们的宝宝对这些“纸巾”本身的兴趣甚至超过了纸巾盒。不过也有人觉得，就是几块布而已，性价比不是很高。",howToUseEn:"These are the 'tissues' for the Magic Tissue Box, but they can also be played with separately. You can use them to play peek-a-boo with your baby or tie them to something for your baby to pull. Since they are made of organic cotton, it's okay for your baby to put them in their mouth.",developmentGoalEn:"By pulling, touching, and chewing, your baby's sensory perception and fine motor skills are developed. Playing peek-a-boo also helps your baby understand object permanence and promotes social and emotional development.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this design very thoughtful, as it satisfies the baby's love for pulling tissues while being safe and hygienic. Some parents say their babies are even more interested in the 'tissues' themselves than the box. However, others feel that they are just a few pieces of cloth and not very cost-effective."},{name:"柔软棉制彩虹球",englishName:"Soft Cotton Rainbow Ball",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个球很柔软，而且有很多“瓣”，方便宝宝的小手抓握。你可以轻轻地把球滚给宝宝，鼓励他去抓。也可以在宝宝趴着的时候，把球放在他面前，吸引他抬头和伸手。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的抓握能力、手眼协调和视觉追踪能力。柔软的材质和鲜艳的彩虹色也能给宝宝带来丰富的感官刺激。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这个球的设计，说它比普通的球更容易让小宝宝抓住，而且很安全，不怕砸到宝宝。很多宝宝都喜欢抓着它，或者把它放进嘴里啃。有家长提到，这个球很容易清洗，也是一个优点。",howToUseEn:"This ball is very soft and has many 'petals,' making it easy for your baby's small hands to grasp. You can gently roll the ball to your baby and encourage them to grab it. You can also place the ball in front of them during tummy time to attract them to lift their head and reach for it.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's grasping ability, hand-eye coordination, and visual tracking skills. The soft material and bright rainbow colors also provide rich sensory stimulation for your baby.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the design of this ball, saying it's easier for little babies to grasp than a regular ball and is very safe, so there's no fear of it hitting the baby. Many babies love to hold it or put it in their mouths to chew on. Some parents mentioned that the ball is easy to clean, which is also a plus."},{name:"《我身体的一部分》",englishName:"'Parts of Me' Book",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"抱着宝宝一起读这本书，指着书上的图片，告诉他这是眼睛、鼻子、嘴巴。你也可以指着宝宝自己和你的身体部位，让他建立联系。这本书是硬纸板做的，可以放心让宝宝自己翻看、啃咬。",developmentGoal:"这本书可以帮助宝宝认识自己的身体部位，建立自我认知，同时也能扩充他的词汇量。亲子共读的时光也能增进情感交流。",parentReview:"很多家长都喜欢Lovevery的书，认为图片真实、质量好。不过，也有一些家长吐槽这本书的设计，觉得图片重复度高，没有新意，而且所谓的“专注于身体部位”也做得不够好。但总体来说，作为一本给小宝宝的认知书，还是可以的。",howToUseEn:"Hold your baby and read this book together, pointing to the pictures in the book and telling them these are eyes, nose, and mouth. You can also point to your baby's and your own body parts to help them make connections. This book is made of cardboard, so you can let your baby flip through it and chew on it without worry.",developmentGoalEn:"This book can help your baby learn about their body parts, build self-awareness, and expand their vocabulary. The time spent reading together also enhances emotional connection.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love Lovevery's books, considering the pictures to be realistic and of good quality. However, some parents have complained about the design of this book, feeling that the pictures are repetitive and unoriginal, and that the so-called 'focus on body parts' is not well done. But overall, as a cognitive book for a young baby, it is acceptable."},{name:"游戏袜子",englishName:"Play Socks",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"给宝宝穿上这双可爱的袜子，一边的袜子上有一个小铃铛，另一边是黑白图案。当宝宝踢腿或抓住自己的小脚时，就会发出声音或看到有趣的图案，鼓励他更多地探索自己的身体。",developmentGoal:"这双袜子可以激励宝宝探索自己的脚，锻炼腿部力量和身体控制能力。铃铛的声音和黑白图案也能为宝宝提供听觉和视觉刺激。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个设计很巧妙，能吸引宝宝注意到自己的脚，并开始玩自己的脚。不过，也有一些家长说，他们的宝宝对这双袜子并不感兴趣，或者铃铛很快就不响了。还有的家长反映袜子有点小，很快就穿不上了。",howToUseEn:"Put these cute socks on your baby. One sock has a small bell, and the other has a black and white pattern. When your baby kicks their legs or grabs their little feet, they will hear a sound or see an interesting pattern, encouraging them to explore their body more.",developmentGoalEn:"These socks can encourage your baby to explore their feet, developing leg strength and body control. The sound of the bell and the black and white patterns also provide auditory and visual stimulation for your baby.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this design very clever, as it attracts the baby's attention to their feet and encourages them to start playing with them. However, some parents have said that their baby is not interested in these socks, or that the bell quickly stops ringing. Other parents have reported that the socks are a bit small and are quickly outgrown."},{name:"趴趴时间摇摆器",englishName:"Tummy Time Wobbler",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"在宝宝趴着的时候，把这个不倒翁放在他面前，轻轻一推，它就会摇摆起来，吸引宝宝的注意。宝宝会想要伸手去抓住它，这能鼓励他抬头，锻炼核心肌肉力量。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具能让“趴趴时间”变得更有趣，有助于增强宝宝的核心肌肉力量，为之后的爬行和走路打下基础。同时，它还能锻炼宝宝的视觉追踪能力和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具对锻炼宝宝趴着很有帮助，能有效延长Tummy Time的时间。宝宝们似乎都很喜欢这个摇摇晃晃的玩具。不过，也有家长反映，这个玩具比较轻，很容易被宝宝推倒或弄走，需要大人在旁边一直扶着。",howToUseEn:"During tummy time, place this wobbler in front of your baby and give it a gentle push. It will wobble and attract your baby's attention. Your baby will want to reach out and grab it, which encourages them to lift their head and exercise their core muscles.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy makes tummy time more fun and helps strengthen your baby's core muscles, laying the foundation for crawling and walking later on. It also exercises your baby's visual tracking and hand-eye coordination skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe this toy is very helpful for practicing tummy time and can effectively extend the duration of tummy time. Babies seem to love this wobbly toy. However, some parents have reported that the toy is relatively light and can be easily pushed over or moved by the baby, requiring an adult to hold it steady."}]},{id:"inspector",name:"The Inspector",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-inspector",ageRange:"7-8 个月",ageRangeEn:"7-8 months",ageMonths:"7-8m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#CF8B5A",bgColor:"#FFEFE4",lightColor:"#FDE5D5",description:"7-8个月的宝宝坐得很稳了，两只手终于能同时空出来好好研究面前的东西。手指灵活性迎来关键突破——从整只手「抓」变成用拇指和食指「捏」小东西。最让家长上瘾的是「藏起来→找出来」的游戏：物体恒存认知正在建立。",descriptionEn:"At 7-8 months, your baby is sitting up confidently, freeing up both hands to explore objects in front of them. Their finger dexterity is making a key breakthrough as they move from grasping with their whole hand to pinching small items with their thumb and forefinger. The most addicting game for parents is 'hide and seek' as their understanding of object permanence is being established.",toys:[{name:"投球盒",englishName:"Ball Drop Box",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"爸爸妈妈可以向宝宝演示如何将球放入盒子顶部的洞里，然后打开小门把球取出来。重复几次，鼓励宝宝自己尝试。这个过程可以伴随着有趣的音效，让宝宝觉得更好玩。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于宝宝理解‘物体恒存’的概念，即使看不见球了，它也仍然存在。同时，它还能锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力和精细动作。",parentReview:"很多家长说，他们的宝宝一开始可能需要一些时间来掌握玩法，但一旦学会了就爱不释手。这款玩具制作精良，能长时间吸引宝宝的注意力。有些宝宝特别喜欢听球掉进盒子里时发出的声音。",howToUseEn:"You can show your baby how to drop the ball into the hole at the top of the box, then open the little door to retrieve it. Repeat this a few times and encourage your baby to try it themselves. Making fun sound effects can make this process even more engaging for your baby.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps your baby understand the concept of 'object permanence'—even when the ball is out of sight, it still exists. It also helps develop their hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say that their babies might need some time to get the hang of it, but once they do, they can't get enough. The toy is well-made and holds a baby's attention for a long time. Some babies especially love the sound the ball makes when it drops into the box."},{name:"木球套装",englishName:"Wood Ball Set",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"这套木球可以单独玩，也可以和投球盒搭配使用。爸爸妈妈可以鼓励宝宝抓握、摇晃、敲击木球，感受木头的质感和声音。将木球滚来滚去，吸引宝宝爬行追逐，也是一个有趣的玩法。",developmentGoal:"抓握和传递木球可以锻炼宝宝的精细动作和双手协调能力。感受木球的重量、质地和声音，能够促进宝宝的感官发展。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这套木球的简约设计和天然材质。很多宝宝喜欢啃咬木球，所以家长们很看重它的安全性。有些家长提到，他们的宝宝对木球的兴趣不是很大，但与其他玩具（如投球盒）结合使用时，宝宝会更愿意玩。",howToUseEn:"This set of wooden balls can be played with on its own or with the Ball Drop Box. You can encourage your baby to grasp, shake, and tap the wooden balls to feel their texture and hear the sounds they make. Rolling the balls back and forth to encourage your baby to crawl after them is another fun way to play.",developmentGoalEn:"Grasping and passing the wooden balls helps develop your baby's fine motor skills and bilateral coordination. Feeling the weight, texture, and sound of the wooden balls promotes sensory development.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the simple design and natural material of these wooden balls. Many babies like to teethe on them, so their safety is a big plus. Some parents mentioned that their babies weren't very interested in the balls on their own, but were more engaged when they were used with other toys, like the Ball Drop Box."},{name:"《我一直都爱你》绘本",englishName:"‘I Love You All the Time’ Board Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"抱着宝宝一起阅读，用温柔的声音读出书里的文字。可以指着书中的宝宝图片，告诉自己的宝宝：‘看，就像妈妈/爸爸爱你一样！’ 这本书很适合在睡前阅读，给宝宝带来安全感。",developmentGoal:"这本书通过重复的句式和温馨的画面，帮助宝宝建立情感认知和安全感。同时，亲子共读也能促进宝宝的语言发展和亲子关系。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这本书非常温馨感人，能有效安抚宝宝的情绪。书中的真实宝宝照片很受小读者欢迎。很多家长表示，这本书已经成为他们和宝宝睡前故事时间的必选读物。",howToUseEn:"Hold your baby while you read together, using a gentle voice to read the words in the book. You can point to the pictures of the babies in the book and say to your own baby, ‘Look, just like Mommy/Daddy loves you!’ This book is perfect for bedtime reading to give your baby a sense of security.",developmentGoalEn:"Through repetitive phrases and warm illustrations, this book helps your baby develop emotional awareness and a sense of security. Reading together also promotes your baby's language development and strengthens the parent-child bond.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this book to be very warm and touching, and effective at soothing their babies. The real photos of babies in the book are a big hit with little readers. Many parents say this book has become a must-read during their bedtime story routine with their baby."},{name:"‘我看到的东西’触觉卡",englishName:"'Things I See' Texture Cards",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"向宝宝展示卡片，让他触摸不同材质的贴片，比如毛茸茸的、光滑的、粗糙的。可以一边展示一边告诉宝宝卡片上物体的名称，比如‘这是小狗，毛茸茸的’。",developmentGoal:"这套卡片通过不同的材质和图案，刺激宝宝的触觉和视觉发展。将物体的名称与触觉联系起来，可以帮助宝宝建立早期的词汇联系。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这套卡片设计精美，材质多样，能很好地吸引宝宝的注意力。卡片上的真实图片比卡通图案更能帮助宝宝认识真实世界。有些家长提到，卡片很容易被宝宝弄脏或损坏，需要小心保管。",howToUseEn:"Show the cards to your baby and let them touch the different textured patches, like fuzzy, smooth, and rough. As you show them, you can name the objects on the cards, for example, ‘This is a puppy, it’s fuzzy.’",developmentGoalEn:"This set of cards stimulates your baby's sense of touch and sight with its different textures and patterns. Connecting the names of objects with their textures helps your baby build early vocabulary connections.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think these cards are beautifully designed with a variety of textures that are great for capturing a baby's attention. The real images on the cards are more helpful for teaching babies about the real world than cartoon drawings. Some parents mentioned that the cards can get dirty or damaged easily, so they need to be handled with care."},{name:"层叠漏水杯",englishName:"Nesting Stacking Drip Drop Cups",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套杯子玩法多样。可以在地板上玩，教宝宝如何把杯子从小到大一个一个套起来，或者把它们堆得高高的。洗澡的时候更好玩，每个杯子底部都有小孔，装满水后会像花洒一样漏下来，宝宝会觉得很神奇。",developmentGoal:"这套杯子可以帮助宝宝理解大小、顺序和空间关系的概念。堆叠和嵌套的动作可以锻炼宝宝的手眼协调和精细动作。在洗澡时玩水，还能让宝宝初步感受物理现象。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这套杯子是洗澡神器，能让不爱洗澡的宝宝也玩得很开心。杯子的颜色很漂亮，宝宝很喜欢。有家长提到，最小的杯子比较容易裂开，使用时需要注意。",howToUseEn:"There are many ways to play with these cups. On the floor, you can teach your baby how to nest the cups from smallest to largest, or stack them up high. They are even more fun in the bath. Each cup has small holes in the bottom, so when you fill them with water, they drip like a shower, which babies find fascinating.",developmentGoalEn:"These cups help your baby understand concepts like size, sequence, and spatial relationships. The actions of stacking and nesting help develop hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills. Playing with water in the bath also gives them a preliminary understanding of physical phenomena.",parentReviewEn:"Parents widely agree that these cups are a bath time lifesaver, making even bath-averse babies happy to play. The cups have beautiful colors that babies love. Some parents have mentioned that the smallest cup can crack easily, so it needs to be used with care."},{name:"第一个拼图",englishName:"First Puzzle",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是宝宝的第一个拼图，非常简单。爸爸妈妈可以先演示如何将圆形木块从底座上拿起来，再放回去。鼓励宝宝用手指捏住小把手，自己尝试。这个过程需要耐心和重复。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作，特别是捏握能力。同时，它也能培养宝宝解决问题的能力和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这个拼图是宝宝入门的绝佳选择。设计简单，大小合适，宝宝很容易上手。很多宝宝在成功完成拼图后会很有成就感。有些家长提到，他们的宝宝一开始只会把木块拿出来，需要一些时间才学会放回去。",howToUseEn:"This is your baby's first puzzle, and it’s very simple. You can start by showing them how to lift the round wooden piece from the base and then put it back. Encourage your baby to use their fingers to pinch the small handle and try it themselves. This process requires patience and repetition.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's fine motor skills, especially their pincer grasp. It also cultivates problem-solving abilities and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this puzzle is an excellent choice for a baby's first puzzle. The design is simple, the size is appropriate, and it's easy for babies to get the hang of. Many babies feel a sense of accomplishment after successfully completing the puzzle. Some parents mentioned that their babies would only take the piece out at first and needed some time to learn how to put it back in."},{name:"宝物篮",englishName:"Treasure Basket",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个小篮子本身就是一个有趣的玩具。爸爸妈妈可以把各种安全的日常用品或者小玩具放进篮子里，比如丝巾、小刷子、木勺等，让宝宝自己去探索、抓取、感受。记得要定期更换篮子里的‘宝物’，保持新鲜感。",developmentGoal:"‘宝物篮’鼓励宝宝主动探索，满足他们的好奇心。通过触摸和把玩不同材质的物品，可以极大地促进宝宝的感官发展和认知能力。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这个宝物篮的理念，认为它能激发宝宝的好奇心和探索欲。篮子本身做工很好，大小也适合宝宝。很多家长会用它来搭配其他玩具，或者放入家里的安全物品，玩法非常灵活。",howToUseEn:"This little basket is a fun toy in itself. You can put a variety of safe, everyday objects or small toys in the basket, like a silk scarf, a small brush, or a wooden spoon, and let your baby explore, grasp, and feel them on their own. Remember to change the ‘treasures’ in the basket regularly to keep it interesting.",developmentGoalEn:"The Treasure Basket encourages your baby to explore independently and satisfies their curiosity. Touching and playing with objects of different materials greatly promotes your baby's sensory development and cognitive abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the concept of the Treasure Basket, believing it sparks their baby's curiosity and desire to explore. The basket itself is well-made and a good size for a baby. Many parents use it with other toys or put safe household items inside, making it very versatile."},{name:"羊毛毡球套装",englishName:"Felt Ball Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套羊毛毡球颜色鲜艳，质地柔软，非常适合小宝宝抓握和探索。可以把球滚来滚去，鼓励宝宝爬行追逐。也可以和宝宝玩投掷游戏，或者把它们藏在宝物篮里让宝宝寻找。",developmentGoal:"抓握和传递羊毛毡球可以锻炼宝宝的精细动作。鲜艳的颜色可以刺激宝宝的视觉发展。柔软的质地和轻盈的重量，让宝宝可以安全地探索和玩耍。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这套球的鲜艳颜色和柔软材质，认为它们对宝宝非常安全。很多宝宝喜欢抓着、捏着、甚至啃咬这些球。有些家长提到，羊毛毡球容易粘上灰尘和毛发，需要经常清洁。",howToUseEn:"This set of felt balls is brightly colored and soft, perfect for little babies to grasp and explore. You can roll the balls back and forth to encourage your baby to crawl after them. You can also play a game of catch with your baby, or hide them in the Treasure Basket for your baby to find.",developmentGoalEn:"Grasping and passing the felt balls helps develop your baby's fine motor skills. The bright colors can stimulate your baby's visual development. The soft texture and light weight allow your baby to explore and play safely.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the bright colors and soft material of these balls, considering them very safe for babies. Many babies enjoy holding, squeezing, and even chewing on them. Some parents have mentioned that the felt balls tend to collect dust and hair and need to be cleaned often."},{name:"木制声音筒",englishName:"Wooden Sound Cylinders",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"摇晃不同的声音筒，让宝宝听一听它们发出的不同声音。可以先摇晃一个，然后把它滚到宝宝面前，鼓励宝宝自己去抓握和摇晃。和宝宝一起玩‘声音配对’的游戏，找出哪两个声音筒的声音是一样的。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的听觉辨别能力，让他们学会区分不同的声音。摇晃和滚动声音筒的动作，也能促进宝宝的精细动作和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这个玩具有助于培养宝宝的专注力和听力。木制的材质很安全，大小也适合宝宝抓握。有些家长提到，他们的宝宝对声音的细微差别还不太敏感，需要家长耐心引导。",howToUseEn:"Shake the different sound cylinders and let your baby listen to the different sounds they make. You can shake one first, then roll it to your baby and encourage them to grasp and shake it themselves. Play a ‘sound matching’ game with your baby to find out which two sound cylinders make the same sound.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's auditory discrimination skills, teaching them to distinguish between different sounds. The actions of shaking and rolling the sound cylinders also promote your baby's fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents believe this toy helps to cultivate their baby's concentration and listening skills. The wooden material is safe, and the size is suitable for a baby to grasp. Some parents have mentioned that their babies are not yet sensitive to the subtle differences in sound and require patient guidance from parents."}]},{id:"explorer",name:"The Explorer",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-explorer",ageRange:"9-10 个月",ageRangeEn:"9-10 months",ageMonths:"9-10m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#C6814C",bgColor:"#FFEDDF",lightColor:"#FDE3D0",description:"9-10个月的宝宝爬得又快又稳，不少已经扶着沙发站起来了。手指越来越灵——从整手抓变成会用大拇指和食指「捏」小东西。这个月龄最让家长感叹的是宝宝对「容器」的魔性执念：什么都要放进去、拿出来、叠起来、推倒，再来一遍。",descriptionEn:"Babies at 9-10 months are crawling quickly and steadily, and many are already pulling themselves up to stand while holding onto the sofa. Their fingers are becoming more and more nimble—they are moving from a whole-hand grasp to being able to 'pinch' small things with their thumb and forefinger. What amazes parents most at this age is the baby's magical obsession with 'containers': everything has to be put in, taken out, stacked up, knocked down, and then done all over again.",toys:[{name:"不锈钢旋转球",englishName:"Stainless Steel Tip & Turn",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝可以用双手握住这个不锈钢玩具，通过倾斜和旋转，让里面的小球滚动起来，发出悦耳的声音。家长可以示范给宝宝看，鼓励宝宝自己探索和玩耍。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的双手协调能力和手腕控制能力，同时也能激发宝宝的好奇心和听觉发展。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个玩具很有趣，宝宝很喜欢听小球滚动的声音。但也有一些家长反映，他们的宝宝对这个玩具兴趣不大，觉得有点无聊。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can hold this stainless steel toy with both hands, and by tilting and turning it, make the small balls inside roll and create a pleasant sound. Parents can demonstrate this to the baby and encourage them to explore and play on their own.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's bilateral coordination and wrist control, while also stimulating their curiosity and auditory development.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this toy very interesting, and their babies love listening to the sound of the small balls rolling. However, some parents have reported that their babies are not very interested in this toy, finding it a bit boring."},{name:"透明管塔",englishName:"Transparent Tube Tower",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝可以把三个透明的管子堆叠起来，或者把它们一个套一个地收起来。家长可以引导宝宝观察管子的大小和颜色，学习简单的空间关系。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于培养宝宝的精细动作、手眼协调能力和对物体恒存性的理解，同时也能激发宝宝的早期数学和科学思维。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具设计得很好，宝宝很喜欢玩堆叠和嵌套的游戏。有些家长提到，他们的宝宝会用这个管子玩很长时间，非常有吸引力。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can stack the three transparent tubes or nest them one inside the other. Parents can guide the baby to observe the size and color of the tubes and learn simple spatial relationships.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and understanding of object permanence, while also stimulating their early mathematical and scientific thinking.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this toy is well-designed, and babies love playing stacking and nesting games. Some parents mentioned that their babies will play with these tubes for a long time, finding them very engaging."},{name:"蒙氏鸡蛋杯",englishName:"Montessori Egg Cup",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝需要用一只手扶着蛋杯，另一只手把木头鸡蛋放进杯子里。这个简单的动作需要宝宝双手并用，集中注意力才能完成。",developmentGoal:"这个经典的蒙特梭利玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的双手协调能力、手眼协调能力和专注力。",parentReview:"很多家长都喜欢这个玩具，认为它简单而有效，能帮助宝宝练习精细动作。但也有家长觉得这个玩具太简单了，宝宝很快就玩腻了。",howToUseEn:"Your baby needs to hold the egg cup with one hand and use the other hand to place the wooden egg into the cup. This simple action requires the baby to use both hands and concentrate to complete it.",developmentGoalEn:"This classic Montessori toy helps to develop your baby's bilateral coordination, hand-eye coordination, and concentration.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love this toy, considering it simple and effective for helping babies practice fine motor skills. However, some parents feel the toy is too simple and their babies get bored with it quickly."},{name:"不锈钢叮当钥匙",englishName:"Stainless Steel Jingle Keys",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝可以安全地抓握、摇晃和啃咬这串不锈钢钥匙，感受真实的物品。钥匙串的大小和重量都非常适合宝宝的小手。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于满足宝宝对真实物品的好奇心，锻炼宝宝的抓握能力和听觉感知。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这串钥匙是宝宝的最爱之一，既可以当玩具，又可以当牙胶。很多宝宝都喜欢拿着它到处走，发出叮叮当当的声音。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can safely grasp, shake, and teethe on this set of stainless steel keys, experiencing a real-world object. The size and weight of the keychain are perfect for your baby's little hands.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to satisfy your baby's curiosity about real objects and develops their grasping ability and auditory perception.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally agree that these keys are one of their baby's favorites, serving as both a toy and a teether. Many babies love to carry them around, making a jingling sound."},{name:"夹捏铃铛球",englishName:"Pincer Chime Ball",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个球的大小刚好需要宝宝用双手才能抱住，上面的小机关需要宝宝用手指夹捏才能拉出来。球滚动时还会发出清脆的铃铛声。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的双手协调能力和手指的夹捏能力，同时也能激发宝宝的听觉和好奇心。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个球的设计很巧妙，能吸引宝宝去探索和玩耍。但也有家长反映，他们的宝宝对拉动小机关的兴趣不大。",howToUseEn:"This ball is just the right size for your baby to hold with both hands, and the small knob on top requires them to use a pincer grasp to pull it out. The ball also makes a crisp chime sound when it rolls.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's bilateral coordination and pincer grasp, while also stimulating their hearing and curiosity.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find the design of this ball clever and engaging for their babies to explore and play with. However, some parents have reported that their babies are not very interested in pulling the small knob."},{name:"《我的感觉》纸板书",englishName:"'How I Feel' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"家长可以和宝宝一起阅读这本书，指着书里不同表情的宝宝照片，模仿他们的表情，并告诉宝宝这是什么感觉。",developmentGoal:"这本书有助于帮助宝宝认识和理解不同的情绪，培养宝宝的情商和同理心。",parentReview:"家长们认为这本书对于帮助宝宝认识情绪很有帮助，图片也很清晰。但有些家长觉得书里的内容有点简单，希望有更多的情景和故事。",howToUseEn:"Parents can read this book with their baby, pointing to the photos of babies with different expressions, imitating their faces, and telling the baby what each feeling is.",developmentGoalEn:"This book helps babies recognize and understand different emotions, developing their emotional intelligence and empathy.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this book very helpful for teaching babies about emotions, and the pictures are clear. However, some parents feel the content is a bit simple and would like more scenarios and stories."},{name:"滚动和构建锥体套装",englishName:"Roll & Build Cone Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝可以把这些五颜六色的锥体堆叠起来，或者把它们滚来滚去。家长可以引导宝宝按照大小或者颜色来排序和堆叠。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作、手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力，同时也能让宝宝学习到关于大小、颜色和形状的知识。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个玩具玩法多样，既可以堆叠又可以滚动，能玩很长时间。但也有家长反映，他们的宝宝对这个玩具的兴趣一般。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can stack these colorful cones or roll them around. Parents can guide the baby to sort and stack them by size or color.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to develop your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving abilities, while also teaching them about size, color, and shape.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents feel that this toy is versatile, as it can be stacked and rolled, providing long hours of play. However, some parents have reported that their babies have a moderate interest in this toy."},{name:"亮丽轻柔游戏围巾",englishName:"Bright & Light Play Scarf",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"家长可以用这条轻薄的纱巾和宝宝玩躲猫猫的游戏，或者把它扔到空中，让宝宝观察它飘落的样子。也可以把它系在宝宝的手腕或脚腕上，增加宝宝对自己身体的感知。",developmentGoal:"这条纱巾有助于激发宝宝的视觉追踪能力、物体恒存性认知和身体意识。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这条纱巾是一个非常棒的开放式玩具，玩法非常多，可以从很小玩到很大。很多宝宝都喜欢看它飘来飘去的样子。",howToUseEn:"Parents can use this lightweight scarf to play peek-a-boo with their baby, or toss it in the air and let the baby watch it float down. It can also be tied to the baby's wrist or ankle to increase their body awareness.",developmentGoalEn:"This scarf helps to stimulate your baby's visual tracking skills, understanding of object permanence, and body awareness.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally consider this scarf a fantastic open-ended toy with many ways to play, suitable for a wide range of ages. Many babies love to watch it float and dance in the air."}]},{id:"thinker",name:"The Thinker",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-thinker",ageRange:"11-12 个月",ageRangeEn:"11-12 months",ageMonths:"11-12m",stage:"baby",stageLabel:"婴儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Baby Stage",color:"#BD773E",bgColor:"#FFEBDA",lightColor:"#FDE1CB",description:"11-12个月的宝宝正站在一个重要的门槛上——有些已经摇摇晃晃迈出第一步了。精细运动更加成熟，能听懂简单的话。社交能力大跃进——会故意逗你笑、模仿你拿手机打电话。「指」这个动作越来越频繁——这是沟通意愿的重要标志。",descriptionEn:"Babies at 11-12 months are on the verge of a major milestone - some are already taking their first wobbly steps. Their fine motor skills are more refined, and they can understand simple words. Their social skills are taking a big leap forward - they'll intentionally make you laugh and imitate you talking on the phone. Pointing becomes more frequent, a key sign of their desire to communicate.",toys:[{name:"有机棉宝宝玩偶",englishName:"Organic Cotton Baby Doll",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这款柔软的有机棉玩偶是宝宝的第一个好朋友。可以抱着它，跟它说话，练习温柔地抚摸和拥抱。大一点的宝宝可以学习给玩偶换尿布、喂奶、或者用小推车带着它，为照顾小弟弟小妹妹做准备。",developmentGoal:"玩偶游戏可以培养宝宝的同理心和社交情感能力，同时也能锻炼他们的精细动作和语言能力。",parentReview:"很多家长都说这款娃娃质量很好，宝宝很喜欢。但也有家长抱怨说，娃娃的肤色选择太少了，希望能有更多样化的选择。总体来说，这是一个很受欢迎的玩具，但如果宝宝已经有自己喜欢的娃娃了，可能就不会对这个新的有太大兴趣。",howToUseEn:"This soft, organic cotton doll is your baby's first best friend. They can hold it, talk to it, and practice gentle pats and hugs. Older babies can learn to change the doll's diaper, feed it, or take it for a stroll in a toy stroller, preparing them for a new sibling.",developmentGoalEn:"Playing with dolls helps develop your baby's empathy and social-emotional skills, while also exercising their fine motor and language abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this doll is high-quality and their babies love it. However, some parents have complained that there are too few skin tone options and wish for more diversity. Overall, it's a very popular toy, but if your baby already has a favorite doll, they might not be very interested in this new one."},{name:"木钉掉落",englishName:"Wooden Peg Drop",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝可以用手指把彩色的木钉一个个放进小孔里，然后按下旁边的按钮，看着木钉“噗通”一声掉进下面的盒子里。这个过程可以重复很多次，让宝宝乐此不疲。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作技能、手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力。同时，也能让宝宝理解因果关系。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具质量很好，设计精美，能够吸引宝宝的注意力。很多宝宝都喜欢反复玩这个玩具。但也有家长提到，有些宝宝很快就对这个玩具失去了兴趣，或者觉得有点太简单了。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can use their fingers to put the colorful wooden pegs into the small holes one by one, then press the button on the side to watch the pegs drop into the box below with a 'plunk'. This process can be repeated many times, to your baby's delight.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps exercise your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving abilities. At the same time, it also helps them understand cause and effect.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally agree that this toy is well-made, beautifully designed, and captures a baby's attention. Many babies enjoy playing with this toy over and over. However, some parents have mentioned that their babies lost interest in it quickly or found it a bit too simple."},{name:"滑盖盒",englishName:"Sliding Top Box",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"宝宝可以把小球从洞里放进去，然后需要自己动脑筋把盖子滑开，才能把小球拿出来。这个过程可以帮助宝宝理解“看不见不等于不存在”这个概念。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力、解决问题的能力和工作记忆。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，这款玩具对宝宝很有吸引力，可以让他们专注玩很久。特别是当宝宝掌握了滑开盖子的技巧后，会非常有成就感。但也有一些家长觉得，对小一点的宝宝来说，滑盖的动作可能有点难。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can put the small ball in through the hole, and then needs to figure out how to slide the lid open to get the ball out. This process can help your baby understand the concept of object permanence - 'out of sight, not out of mind'.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to exercise your baby's hand-eye coordination, problem-solving skills, and working memory.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report that this toy is very engaging for their babies and can keep them focused for a long time. They feel a great sense of accomplishment, especially after mastering the skill of sliding the lid open. However, some parents feel that the sliding action might be a bit difficult for younger babies."},{name:"我看到的动物”迷你书",englishName:"'Animals I See' Mini Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这本小书尺寸很适合宝宝的小手抓握和翻阅。可以和宝宝一起看书里的动物图片，模仿动物的叫声，或者问宝宝“小狗在哪里？”来引导他们指认。",developmentGoal:"阅读可以培养宝宝的语言能力和对书籍的热爱。这本小书里的真实动物图片，可以帮助宝宝认识世界，建立词汇和图片的联系。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这本小书，因为它的尺寸非常适合宝宝自己拿着玩。书里的图片也很清晰、真实。有些家长提到，因为是纸板书，如果宝宝喜欢啃咬，可能会比较容易损坏。但总体来说，这是一本很棒的入门读物。",howToUseEn:"This little book is the perfect size for your baby's small hands to hold and flip through. You can look at the animal pictures with your baby, imitate the animal sounds, or ask 'Where is the doggy?' to encourage them to point.",developmentGoalEn:"Reading cultivates your baby's language skills and a love for books. The realistic animal pictures in this little book can help your baby learn about the world and build connections between words and images.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love this little book because its size is perfect for babies to hold and play with on their own. The pictures in the book are also clear and realistic. Some parents have mentioned that because it's a board book, it can be easily damaged if the baby likes to chew on it. But overall, it's a great introductory reader."},{name:"感官开关板",englishName:"Sensory Switchboard",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个玩具上有各种各样的开关、按钮和旋钮，宝宝可以尽情地按、拨、转。每一次操作都会有不同的反馈，比如灯光亮起或者发出声音，让宝宝充满探索的乐趣。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作技能和手眼协调能力，同时也能让他们理解因果关系，并满足他们的好奇心。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具非常有创意，能够很好地满足宝宝喜欢按开关的欲望。很多宝宝都对它爱不释手。但也有家长反映，这款玩具的电池消耗比较快，而且如果宝宝玩腻了，可能就不会再碰了。",howToUseEn:"This toy has a variety of switches, buttons, and knobs that your baby can press, flick, and turn to their heart's content. Each action provides a different feedback, such as a light turning on or a sound, which fills your baby with the joy of exploration.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to exercise your baby's fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination, while also allowing them to understand cause and effect and satisfying their curiosity.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this toy is very creative and can well satisfy a baby's desire to press switches. Many babies can't get enough of it. However, some parents have reported that the toy's batteries run out relatively quickly, and if the baby gets tired of it, they may not touch it again."},{name:"捏式拼图",englishName:"Pincer Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个拼图的每个小块上都有一个适合宝宝小手捏住的小把手。宝宝需要用拇指和食指捏住把手，把拼图块从底板上拿起来，然后再准确地放回原位。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的捏式抓握能力，这是精细动作发展的一个重要里程碑。同时，也能培养宝宝的手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这款拼图设计得很好，能够有效地锻炼宝宝的精细动作。很多宝宝都喜欢玩，并且在反复练习中取得进步。有些家长提到，刚开始宝宝可能会有点挫败感，但只要坚持引导，他们很快就能掌握技巧。",howToUseEn:"Each piece of this puzzle has a small handle that is perfect for your baby's little hands to grasp. Your baby needs to use their thumb and index finger to pinch the handle, lift the puzzle piece from the board, and then accurately place it back in its original position.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps to exercise your baby's pincer grasp, which is an important milestone in fine motor development. At the same time, it also cultivates your baby's hand-eye coordination and problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this puzzle is well-designed and can effectively exercise their baby's fine motor skills. Many babies enjoy playing with it and make progress through repeated practice. Some parents have mentioned that their baby might get a little frustrated at first, but with persistent guidance, they can quickly master the technique."},{name:"相反球",englishName:"Opposites Balls",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"这两个球看起来一模一样，但一个重，一个轻。可以和宝宝一起感受它们的重量差异，或者在洗澡时观察一个下沉，一个漂浮。这能帮助宝宝理解“轻”和“重”的相对概念。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于宝宝的感官探索，让他们通过触摸和观察来学习物理概念。同时，也能激发他们的好奇心和探索欲。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个设计很有趣，尤其是在洗澡时玩，能给宝宝带来很多乐趣。但也有家长反映，轻的那个球容易进水，而且如果宝宝对重量差异不敏感，可能会觉得这两个球没什么区别。",howToUseEn:"These two balls look identical, but one is heavy and one is light. You can feel the weight difference with your baby, or watch one sink and one float during bath time. This helps your baby understand the relative concepts of 'light' and 'heavy'.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy aids in your baby's sensory exploration, allowing them to learn physical concepts through touch and observation. At the same time, it also stimulates their curiosity and desire to explore.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this design interesting, especially when playing with it during bath time, as it can bring a lot of fun to the baby. However, some parents have reported that the lighter ball easily gets water inside, and if the baby is not sensitive to the weight difference, they may not see any difference between the two balls."}]},{id:"babbler",name:"The Babbler",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-babbler",ageRange:"13-15 个月",ageRangeEn:"13-15 months",ageMonths:"13-15m",stage:"toddler",stageLabel:"幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Toddler Stage",color:"#C38D9E",bgColor:"#FFF0F4",lightColor:"#FCE8EE",description:"宝宝蹦出了第一个词——「妈妈」「爸爸」「不要」往往是最先学会的。走路从摇摇晃晃变得越来越利索。两只小手空下来之后就闲不住了：什么都要摸、什么都要拿、什么都要投进容器再掏出来——循环20遍面不改色。",descriptionEn:"Your baby’s first words are emerging—'Mama,' 'Dada,' and 'No' are often the first to be learned. Their walking is becoming more stable, transitioning from wobbly steps to confident strides. With their hands now free, they are eager to explore everything: touching, grabbing, and repeatedly putting objects into containers and taking them out again, tirelessly.",toys:[{name:"滑梯寻球玩具",englishName:"Slide & Seek Ball Run",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"向宝宝演示如何玩这个玩具，把球放在滑道顶部，轻轻一推，球就会滚下来，消失在木盒子里。然后可以打开不同的小门找到滚出来的球。鼓励宝宝自己尝试推球和开关小门。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具可以帮助宝宝理解“物体恒存”概念，即看不见的东西依然存在。同时，通过推球和开门等动作，可以锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力和精细运动技能，并初步理解因果关系。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这款玩具设计很巧妙，宝宝们很喜欢看小球消失又出现的过程，能玩很久。但也有一些家长提到，这款玩具有过召回历史，因为小木钮在运输中可能损坏脱落，存在窒息风险，所以检查玩具的安全性很重要。",howToUseEn:"Show your baby how to place the ball at the top of the ramp and give it a gentle push — it rolls down and disappears inside the wooden box. Then open the different doors to find where the ball ended up. Encourage your baby to try pushing the ball and opening the doors on their own.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies grasp the concept of object permanence — understanding that things still exist even when out of sight. Pushing the ball and opening doors also develops hand-eye coordination, fine motor skills, and an early sense of cause and effect.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this toy cleverly designed; babies love watching the ball disappear and reappear, and can stay engaged for a long time. Some parents note the toy has had a recall history due to small wooden knobs potentially coming loose during shipping, posing a choking risk, so checking for safety is important."},{name:"毛毡洞穴里的小兔子",englishName:"Bunnies in a Felt Burrow",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"你可以和宝宝一起玩“藏猫猫”的游戏，把小兔子一只一只放进毛毡洞里，再鼓励宝宝把它们拿出来。可以一边放一边数数，或者给小兔子起名字，增加互动乐趣。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的双手协调能力，因为需要一只手扶着洞穴，另一只手放或取兔子。同时，这也是一个关于“容纳”概念的早期启蒙，帮助宝宝理解物体可以被放进另一个物体里。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具非常可爱，毛毡的材质也很有质感。宝宝们很喜欢把兔子放进去再拿出来的重复过程。有些评论提到，这个玩具很简单，但对于一岁左右的宝宝来说，恰好能满足他们探索‘放入’和‘取出’的兴趣。",howToUseEn:"Play a peek-a-boo style game with your baby — place the little bunnies one by one into the felt burrow and encourage your baby to pull them back out. Count along as you go or give each bunny a name to make it more interactive.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops bilateral coordination as your baby needs one hand to steady the burrow while the other places or retrieves the bunnies. It also introduces the concept of containment — understanding that objects can be placed inside other objects.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this toy adorable with a nice tactile quality to the felt material. Babies enjoy the repetitive process of putting bunnies in and taking them out. Some note it's simple, but for babies around one year old, it perfectly matches their interest in exploring 'in' and 'out.'"},{name:"木质套圈插槽",englishName:"Wooden Stack & Slot",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"家长可以先向宝宝展示如何将不同大小的彩虹套圈套入木桩，或者将它们从侧面的插槽中推出去，看它们滚动的样子。鼓励宝宝自己尝试堆叠、拆卸和推动，探索不同的玩法。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具可以锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力、精细运动技能和对大小、顺序等空间关系的理解。与传统套圈玩具不同的是，侧面的插槽设计增加了探索的维度，帮助宝宝理解物体如何通过开口。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，这款玩具比传统的套圈更有趣，宝宝很喜欢把圈圈从侧面推出去看着它们滚动。玩具的木质材料和彩虹色设计也备受好评。一些评论提到，这款玩具的玩法更多样，能吸引宝宝更长时间的注意力。",howToUseEn:"Show your baby how to stack the rainbow-colored rings onto the wooden post, or push them out through the side slot and watch them roll. Encourage your baby to try stacking, removing, and pushing the rings on their own to explore different ways of playing.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops hand-eye coordination, fine motor skills, and understanding of spatial concepts like size and order. Unlike traditional stacking rings, the side slot adds an extra dimension of exploration, helping babies understand how objects pass through openings.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report this toy is more engaging than traditional stackers — babies love pushing the rings out the side and watching them roll. The wooden construction and rainbow colors are well-liked. Parents note the variety of play options keeps babies' attention longer."},{name:"朋友圈拼图",englishName:"Circle of Friends Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一款可以个性化的拼图。家长可以把家人、朋友的照片打印出来，放在拼图块下面。然后引导宝宝拿起带抓手的拼图块，看看下面藏着谁的笑脸，并告诉宝宝这是谁。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细运动技能，特别是捏握能力。同时，通过识别不同大小的圆形拼图块，可以培养宝宝对大小的辨别能力和解决问题的能力。个性化的照片还能增强宝宝的社交认知。",parentReview:"家长们非常喜欢这个拼图的创意，可以把家人的照片放进去，让玩具变得更有意义。宝宝们很喜欢揭开拼图看看下面是谁，这是一个学习家人称谓的好方法。有评论说，这是他们最喜欢的Lovevery玩具之一，互动性非常强。",howToUseEn:"This puzzle can be personalized — print out photos of family and friends and place them beneath the puzzle pieces. Guide your baby to lift each knobbed piece to reveal the smiling face underneath, and tell them who it is.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops fine motor skills, especially the pincer grasp needed to lift the knobbed pieces. Matching different-sized circular pieces builds size discrimination and problem-solving. The personalized photos also strengthen social cognition and recognition of familiar faces.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the creative concept of adding family photos to make the toy more meaningful. Babies enjoy lifting the pieces to see who's underneath — a great way to learn names of family members. Some call it one of their favorite Lovevery toys for its strong interactive quality."},{name:"木质投币盒套装",englishName:"Wooden Coin Bank Set",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个玩具有不同的盖子，可以练习不同的精细动作。家长可以引导宝宝将木质硬币投入硬币盖的插槽，将小胡萝卜插入胡萝卜盖的圆孔，或者将更小的物品（比如棉签）放入投入盖。",developmentGoal:"这套玩具极大地锻炼了宝宝的精细运动能力、手眼协调和解决问题的能力。通过更换不同的盖子和投入物，可以持续地为宝宝提供新的挑战，帮助他们理解不同形状和大小的物体如何与开口匹配。",parentReview:"家长们认为这个玩具设计得非常巧妙，一个盒子搭配不同的盖子，玩法多样，性价比高。宝宝们很喜欢重复投币和插入胡萝卜的动作。有评论指出，这个玩具对锻炼宝宝的专注力和精细动作非常有帮助，是Lovevery盒子里的明星玩具之一。",howToUseEn:"This toy comes with interchangeable lids for practicing different fine motor actions. Guide your baby to drop wooden coins into the coin slot lid, insert little carrots into the round holes of the carrot lid, or post smaller items through the posting lid.",developmentGoalEn:"Greatly develops fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving. Swapping between different lids and objects provides ongoing new challenges, helping babies understand how different shapes and sizes match with different openings.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this toy cleverly designed — one box with multiple interchangeable lids offers varied play at great value. Babies love the repetitive dropping and inserting actions. Many call it a standout toy in the Lovevery box for building focus and fine motor skills."},{name:"硬币盖和硬币",englishName:"Coin Lid & Coins",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个玩具需要宝宝将木质硬币准确地对准盖子上的插槽，然后投进去。家长可以先做示范，然后鼓励宝宝自己尝试，在宝宝遇到困难时可以给予适当的帮助，比如调整硬币的角度。",developmentGoal:"这个动作对宝宝的精细运动能力和手眼协调能力是极好的锻炼。它要求宝宝能够精确地控制手腕和手指的动作，对培养专注力和解决问题的能力也很有帮助。",parentReview:"很多家长表示，宝宝们会对这个投币的动作非常着迷，可以重复玩很长时间。这是一个经典的蒙特梭利玩具，简单但非常有效。有些家长提到，对于刚满一岁的宝宝来说，这个动作可能有点挑战，但一旦掌握，宝宝会非常有成就感。",howToUseEn:"Your baby needs to align the wooden coins with the slot in the lid and drop them in. Demonstrate first, then encourage your baby to try independently. Offer gentle assistance when needed, such as helping angle the coin correctly.",developmentGoalEn:"An excellent exercise for fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination. It requires precise control of wrist and finger movements, and also builds focus and problem-solving ability.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say babies become fascinated with the coin-dropping action and can repeat it for extended periods. A classic Montessori toy — simple but highly effective. Some note it can be challenging for babies who just turned one, but once mastered, it gives them a strong sense of accomplishment."},{name:"胡萝卜盖和胡萝卜",englishName:"Carrot Lid & Carrots",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这个玩具可以玩“种胡萝卜”和“拔胡萝卜”的游戏。家长可以引导宝宝把小胡萝卜一根根“种”到盖子的洞里，然后再把它们“拔”出来。可以一边玩一边讲关于农场和兔子的故事，增加趣味性。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的视觉空间能力和手眼协调能力。将胡萝卜对准圆孔并插入的动作，可以练习宝宝的精细运动技能。同时，这个玩具也为角色扮演和想象力游戏提供了很好的素材。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个玩具很可爱，小胡萝卜的造型很讨喜。宝宝们很喜欢“种”和“拔”的重复动作。有评论说，胡萝卜的材质很适合正在长牙的宝宝啃咬。这是一个既能锻炼动手能力，又能激发想象力的好玩具。",howToUseEn:"Play 'planting carrots' and 'pulling carrots' — guide your baby to 'plant' the little carrots one by one into the holes in the lid, then 'pull' them back out. Add fun by telling stories about farms and bunnies while playing.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops visual-spatial skills and hand-eye coordination. Aligning the carrots with the round holes and inserting them exercises fine motor skills. The toy also provides great material for pretend play and imaginative games.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this toy adorable — the little carrot shapes are a hit. Babies love the repetitive 'planting' and 'pulling' actions. Some note the carrot material is great for teething babies to chew on. A toy that builds dexterity while sparking imagination."},{name:"插入盖和小树",englishName:"Posting Lid & Trees",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是投币盒系列里最有挑战性的一个盖子。家长可以鼓励宝宝尝试把小树的‘树干’插进盖子上的小孔里。这个动作需要很高的精确度，宝宝可能需要多次尝试才能成功。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具极大地挑战和锻炼了宝宝的精细运动能力、手眼协调能力和毅力。成功将小树插入小孔能给宝宝带来巨大的成就感，并培养他们解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这是投币盒系列里最难的一个，对宝宝的精细动作是很好的挑战。很多拥有旧版（使用棉签）的家长很高兴新款换成了小树，觉得更安全有趣。评论提到，虽然有难度，但宝宝一旦掌握会非常喜欢。",howToUseEn:"The most challenging lid in the coin bank set. Encourage your baby to insert the small trees by their 'trunks' into the tiny holes in the lid. This requires high precision and your baby may need multiple attempts to succeed.",developmentGoalEn:"Significantly challenges and develops fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and perseverance. Successfully inserting the tree into the small hole gives babies a great sense of achievement and builds problem-solving ability.",parentReviewEn:"Parents consider this the hardest lid in the coin bank series — a great fine motor challenge. Many who had the older version (which used cotton swabs) are happy the new version uses small trees, finding them safer and more fun. Despite the difficulty, babies love it once they get the hang of it."},{name:"《佐伊的睡前时光》纸板书",englishName:"'Bedtime for Zoe' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"在宝宝睡觉前，可以和他一起阅读这本书。书里用真实的照片展示了一个叫佐伊的小女孩睡前会做的一系列事情，比如洗澡、刷牙、读故事。可以一边读，一边和宝宝聊聊他自己的睡前习惯。",developmentGoal:"这本书通过一个完整的故事，帮助宝宝理解“顺序”和“流程”的概念，建立对睡前程序的认知和安全感。书中的真实照片能让宝宝更容易产生联想和共鸣，同时也能丰富他们的词汇量。",parentReview:"很多家长说这本书是他们的“洗澡救星”，因为书里有教宝宝洗头时不让肥皂水进眼睛的小技巧。真实的照片和贴近生活的故事线让宝宝很有代入感。有评论认为，这本书对于培养宝宝规律的睡前习惯非常有帮助。",howToUseEn:"Read this book with your baby before bedtime. It uses real photographs to show a little girl named Zoe going through her bedtime routine — bathing, brushing teeth, reading stories. Chat with your baby about their own bedtime habits as you read along.",developmentGoalEn:"Through a complete narrative, this book helps babies understand concepts of sequence and routine, building a sense of security around bedtime. The real photographs make it easy for babies to relate and connect, while also expanding their vocabulary.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents call this book their 'bath-time savior' because it shows a trick for keeping soap out of eyes during hair washing. The real photos and relatable storyline give babies a strong sense of immersion. Parents find it very helpful for establishing a regular bedtime routine."}]},{id:"adventurer",name:"The Adventurer",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-adventurer",ageRange:"16-18 个月",ageRangeEn:"16-18 months",ageMonths:"16-18m",stage:"toddler",stageLabel:"幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Toddler Stage",color:"#B8839A",bgColor:"#FFEEF3",lightColor:"#FCE5EC",description:"16-18个月的宝宝走得越来越稳了，有些甚至开始小跑。语言理解力飞速发展——你说「把鞋拿来」，他真的会去找鞋。对分类、配对、形状充满好奇，同时也是「不要」和「我自己来」高频出现的阶段。",descriptionEn:"Babies at 16-18 months are walking more steadily, and some are even starting to trot. Their language comprehension is developing rapidly—if you say, 'Bring me the shoes,' they will actually go and find them. They are curious about sorting, matching, and shapes, and this is also a stage where 'no' and 'I'll do it myself' are frequently heard.",toys:[{name:"滚滚追逐赛道",englishName:"Race & Chase Ramp",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝，你看，小汽车从上面滑下来啦！我们把它放在最上面的跑道上，然后松手，它就会自己跑下去。你也来试试看，可以一次放一辆，也可以两辆一起比赛哦！",developmentGoal:"这款玩具可以帮助宝宝理解因果关系，锻炼他们的手眼协调能力和精细动作。",parentReview:"很多家长说这款玩具是宝宝们的最爱，可以玩很久。有的宝宝快三岁了还是很喜欢玩。不过有家长提到新版的赛道比旧版的要小一些。",howToUseEn:"Look, baby, the little car is sliding down from the top! Let's put it on the top track, and when we let go, it will race down on its own. You can try it too. You can race one car at a time, or have two cars race together!",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps your baby understand cause and effect, and develops their hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this toy is a favorite and can be played with for a long time. Some children who are almost three years old still love to play with it. However, some parents have mentioned that the new version of the ramp is smaller than the old one."},{name:"拉拉拼图",englishName:"Pull Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝，我们先把这个拼图拼好，看，三个小圆柱要放进对应的洞里。拼好之后，你可以拉着这个小绳子，让它像小火车一样在地上跑起来！",developmentGoal:"这款玩具结合了拼图和拉拉车的功能，既能锻炼宝宝解决问题的能力和手眼协调，又能鼓励他们多走动，发展大肌肉运动技能。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这款玩具的多功能性，既能当拼图玩，又能拉着走。很多评论都说Lovevery的玩具质量很好，可以用很久。但也有一些家长觉得木制玩具整体偏重，孩子玩的时候需要注意安全。",howToUseEn:"Baby, let's first put this puzzle together. See, the three little cylinders need to go into their matching holes. After it's assembled, you can pull the little string and make it run on the floor like a little train!",developmentGoalEn:"This toy combines the functions of a puzzle and a pull-along toy. It not only exercises your baby's problem-solving skills and hand-eye coordination but also encourages them to move around more, developing their gross motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the versatility of this toy, as it can be used as a puzzle and a pull-along toy. Many reviews say that Lovevery toys are of high quality and can be used for a long time. However, some parents feel that wooden toys are generally heavy, and children need to be supervised for safety while playing."},{name:"《麦克斯和娜娜去公园》图画书",englishName:"'Max and Nana Go to the Park' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和宝宝一起读这本图画书，讲述麦克斯在公园摔倒、得到安慰后又重新开心的故事。你可以指着书上的图片，模仿麦克斯的表情，帮助宝宝理解书里人物的情绪变化。",developmentGoal:"这本书通过一个简单的故事，教导宝宝如何处理像摔倒这样的挫折，并从中恢复过来。这有助于培养他们的情绪恢复能力和同理心。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这本书对孩子很有帮助，特别是当孩子自己遇到小挫折时。书里真实的照片和贴近生活的故事，能让孩子产生共鸣，学会更好地处理自己的情绪。很多宝宝都非常喜欢这本书。",howToUseEn:"Read this board book with your baby, telling the story of Max falling down at the park, being comforted, and then becoming happy again. You can point to the pictures in the book and imitate Max's expressions to help your baby understand the emotional changes of the characters.",developmentGoalEn:"Through a simple story, this book teaches your baby how to handle and recover from setbacks like falling down. This helps cultivate their emotional resilience and empathy.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this book very helpful for their children, especially when they encounter small setbacks themselves. The realistic photos and relatable story in the book allow children to empathize and learn to better manage their emotions. Many babies love this book."},{name:"串珠玩具",englishName:"Threadable Bead Kit",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"向宝宝展示如何将绳子穿过珠子。一开始，你可以先帮他拿着珠子，让他练习穿绳。等他熟练后，就可以让他独立完成，将不同的珠子串在一起，创造出自己的作品。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作技能、手眼协调能力以及双手的协调配合能力。同时，串珠子也是一个很好的专注力训练。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，这款串珠玩具对锻炼孩子的精细动作特别有帮助。Lovevery的玩具质量一向很好，这款也不例外。不过，有家长提到，对于刚满一岁的宝宝来说，这个玩具有一定的挑战性，可能需要家长的耐心引导。",howToUseEn:"Show your baby how to thread the string through the beads. In the beginning, you can hold the bead for them while they practice threading. Once they become more skilled, you can let them do it independently, stringing different beads together to create their own masterpiece.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and bilateral coordination. At the same time, threading beads is also excellent for training concentration.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report that this bead kit is particularly helpful for developing their child's fine motor skills. The quality of Lovevery toys is consistently high, and this one is no exception. However, some parents have mentioned that this toy can be challenging for a one-year-old and may require patient guidance from parents."},{name:"抽绳袋",englishName:"Drawstring Bag",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝，玩完玩具后，我们要把它们送回家哦。这个小袋子就是串珠的家，我们把珠子一颗一颗放进去，然后拉紧绳子，这样就不会弄丢啦。",developmentGoal:"这个抽绳袋可以教宝宝学习整理和收纳，培养他们的责任感和好习惯。打开和拉紧袋子的过程也能锻炼他们的精细动作。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个袋子非常实用，可以很好地收纳零散的玩具，避免丢失。很多评论提到，从小教孩子用袋子整理玩具，有助于培养他们的整洁习惯。袋子本身的质量也很好。",howToUseEn:"Baby, after we finish playing with the toys, we need to put them back home. This little bag is the home for the beads. Let's put the beads in one by one, and then pull the string tight so we don't lose them.",developmentGoalEn:"This drawstring bag teaches your baby to tidy up and organize, fostering a sense of responsibility and good habits. The process of opening and tightening the bag also exercises their fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this bag very practical for storing small, loose toys and preventing them from getting lost. Many comments mention that teaching children to use a bag to organize their toys from a young age helps cultivate good tidiness habits. The quality of the bag itself is also very good."},{name:"木制套柱插板",englishName:"Wooden Stacking Pegboard",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"宝宝，看这里有不同颜色的圆环和木棍。我们可以把相同颜色的圆环套在对应的木棍上，看谁套得又快又好。你也可以发挥想象力，创造出自己的颜色搭配。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于宝宝学习颜色分类和配对，锻炼他们的手眼协调能力和精细动作。同时，套环的过程也能培养他们的空间感和早期数学概念。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具对孩子的颜色认知和动手能力很有帮助。玩具的质量很好，木制材料安全放心。有些家长提到，孩子在玩的过程中，不仅学会了分类，还发挥了创造力，玩出了很多新花样。",howToUseEn:"Baby, look, here are rings and pegs of different colors. We can put the rings of the same color on the corresponding pegs. Let's see who can do it the fastest and best. You can also use your imagination to create your own color combinations.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps your baby learn color sorting and matching, and develops their hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills. At the same time, the process of stacking rings also cultivates their spatial awareness and early math concepts.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe that this toy is very helpful for their child's color recognition and hands-on abilities. The quality of the toy is excellent, and the wooden material is safe and reliable. Some parents have mentioned that in the process of playing, their children not only learned to sort but also showed creativity and came up with many new ways to play."},{name:"毛茸茸虫虫灌木丛",englishName:"Fuzzy Bug Shrub",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"宝宝，看这个绿色的灌木丛里藏着好多小虫子！你可以把它们一个个拿出来，再粘回去。试着把它们藏在不同的口袋里，看看你能不能全部找到它们。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于锻炼宝宝双手的协调能力和精细动作，比如捏、拉、粘等动作。同时，捉迷藏的游戏方式也能提升宝宝的记忆力和物体恒存性概念。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具非常可爱，而且很能吸引宝宝的注意力。很多宝宝都喜欢玩这种‘藏与找’的游戏。有评论说，这款玩具不仅好玩，还能作为收纳，把小虫子都收在灌木丛里，非常方便。",howToUseEn:"Baby, look, there are many little bugs hidden in this green shrub! You can take them out one by one and stick them back on. Try hiding them in different pockets and see if you can find them all.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's bilateral coordination and fine motor skills, such as pinching, pulling, and sticking. At the same time, the hide-and-seek game also enhances your baby's memory and understanding of object permanence.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this toy very cute and engaging for their babies. Many babies love playing this 'hide-and-seek' game. Some reviews say that this toy is not only fun but also serves as a storage solution, as all the little bugs can be conveniently stored in the shrub."},{name:"跟我学叠杯",englishName:"Copy Me Cups",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝，我们来玩一个模仿游戏吧！你看这个杯子上的图片，是‘摸摸鼻子’，你跟着我一起做。我们一个一个来，看看你能不能都学会。这些杯子还可以叠在一起，或者当洗澡玩具玩哦。",developmentGoal:"这款叠杯可以帮助宝宝学习听从指令，认识身体部位，并练习模仿。同时，叠杯子本身也能锻炼他们的手眼协调和精细动作。",parentReview:"很多家长都说这款玩具互动性很强，宝宝很喜欢跟着做动作。杯子上的图片简单清晰，很容易引导孩子。除了模仿游戏，这些杯子还可以用来玩水、叠高高，玩法很多样。",howToUseEn:"Baby, let's play a copycat game! Look at the picture on this cup, it says 'touch your nose,' you do it with me. Let's do them one by one and see if you can learn them all. These cups can also be stacked or used as bath toys.",developmentGoalEn:"This set of stacking cups helps your baby learn to follow instructions, recognize body parts, and practice imitation. At the same time, stacking the cups also develops their hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say that this toy is very interactive, and their babies love to follow along with the actions. The pictures on the cups are simple and clear, making it easy to guide the child. In addition to the imitation game, these cups can also be used for playing with water and stacking, offering a variety of ways to play."}]},{id:"realist",name:"The Realist",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-realist",ageRange:"19-21 个月",ageRangeEn:"19-21 months",ageMonths:"19-21m",stage:"toddler",stageLabel:"幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Toddler Stage",color:"#AD7996",bgColor:"#FFECF2",lightColor:"#FCE2EA",description:"宝宝开始理解「真实世界」的运作方式——模仿大人做家务、照顾玩偶、「做饭」。假装游戏能力飞速发展，能用一根棍子当「电话」。锁盒类玩具在这个阶段特别受欢迎——宝宝会反复开关，打开时那种「我做到了！」的得意表情是这个月龄的标志。",descriptionEn:"Your baby is starting to understand how the 'real world' works—imitating adults doing chores, taking care of dolls, and 'cooking.' Their pretend play skills are developing rapidly, and they can use a stick as a 'telephone.' Lockbox toys are especially popular at this stage—your baby will repeatedly open and close them, and that proud 'I did it!' look on their face when they succeed is a hallmark of this age.",toys:[{name:"锁盒",englishName:"The Lockbox",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个有很多小门和不同类型锁的盒子。宝宝可以尝试用不同的方式打开它们，比如转动钥匙、滑动插销、按下按钮等。你可以在里面藏一些小惊喜，鼓励宝宝去探索和发现。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力、精细动作和解决问题的能力。通过探索不同的锁，宝宝可以学习到因果关系。",parentReview:"很多家长说他们的孩子非常喜欢这个锁盒，可以玩很久。它不仅能锻炼孩子的手部精细动作，还能培养他们的专注力。有些家长提到，他们的孩子对其中一两种锁特别感兴趣，会反复练习。也有家长说，如果孩子还小，可能需要大人的引导才能玩起来。",howToUseEn:"This is a box with many small doors and different types of locks. Your baby can try to open them in different ways, such as turning a key, sliding a latch, or pressing a button. You can hide small surprises inside to encourage your baby to explore and discover.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's hand-eye coordination, fine motor skills, and problem-solving abilities. By exploring the different locks, your baby can learn about cause and effect.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say their children love this lockbox and can play with it for a long time. It not only exercises their child's fine motor skills but also cultivates their concentration. Some parents mentioned that their children are particularly interested in one or two types of locks and will practice with them repeatedly. Other parents said that if the child is still young, they may need adult guidance to get started."},{name:"城镇巴士",englishName:"Wheel Around Town Bus",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这辆小巴士有三个可以插拔的小人。宝宝可以把小人放在巴士上，然后推着巴士到处走。你也可以鼓励宝宝把不同颜色的小人放到对应颜色的座位上，进行颜色匹配的游戏。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的全身运动能力、手眼协调和颜色识别能力。通过玩角色扮演游戏，还可以促进宝宝的语言和社交能力发展。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这辆巴士很可爱，质量也很好。孩子们喜欢推着它到处跑，也喜欢把小人放进去再拿出来。一些家长提到，他们的孩子会用这个巴士玩很长时间，还会模仿巴士的声音。有家长抱怨说，小人很容易丢失。",howToUseEn:"This small bus has three removable little people. Your baby can place the little people on the bus and then push the bus around. You can also encourage your baby to place the different colored little people in the corresponding colored seats for a color-matching game.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's gross motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and color recognition. Through role-playing games, it can also promote your baby's language and social skills development.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this bus is cute and of good quality. Children love to push it around and enjoy taking the little people in and out. Some parents mentioned that their children will play with this bus for a long time and will also imitate the sound of the bus. One parent complained that the little people are easily lost."},{name:"几何形状拼图",englishName:"Geo Shapes Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个3D的几何形状拼图。宝宝需要把不同形状的积木块放到对应的凹槽里。你可以先从简单的形状开始，然后慢慢增加难度。你也可以教宝宝认识不同的形状和颜色。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的形状识别能力、空间想象力和手眼协调能力。通过抓握和放置积木块，还可以锻炼宝宝的精细动作。",parentReview:"很多家长说这个拼图对他们的孩子来说很有挑战性，但也能让他们很专注。他们喜欢看着孩子一次又一次地尝试，直到成功。一些家长提到，他们的孩子一开始可能会感到沮丧，但一旦掌握了技巧，就会很有成就感。有家长建议，可以先从一两个形状开始，等孩子熟练了再增加难度。",howToUseEn:"This is a 3D geometric shape puzzle. Your baby needs to place the blocks of different shapes into the corresponding slots. You can start with simple shapes and then gradually increase the difficulty. You can also teach your baby to recognize different shapes and colors.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's shape recognition, spatial imagination, and hand-eye coordination. By grasping and placing the blocks, it also exercises your baby's fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this puzzle is very challenging for their children, but it also keeps them very focused. They enjoy watching their child try again and again until they succeed. Some parents mentioned that their children might get frustrated at first, but once they master the skill, they feel a great sense of accomplishment. One parent suggested starting with one or two shapes and then adding more as the child becomes proficient."},{name:"《比娅做体检》图画书",englishName:"'Bea Gets a Checkup' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一本关于小熊比娅去看医生的图画书。你可以在宝宝去看医生之前和他一起读这本书，帮助他了解体检的过程，减轻他的恐惧感。你可以一边读一边模仿书里的情节，让阅读过程更有趣。",developmentGoal:"这本书有助于帮助宝宝建立对看医生的积极认知，缓解他们的焦虑情绪。通过阅读，还可以增加宝宝的词汇量，培养他们的阅读习惯。",parentReview:"很多家长说这本书非常有用，能有效地帮助孩子克服对看医生的恐惧。他们会在带孩子去打疫苗或者体检之前反复读这本书。一些家长提到，他们的孩子很喜欢书里的小熊形象，会把自己想象成比娅。有家长说，这本书的画风很可爱，质量也很好。",howToUseEn:"This is a picture book about a little bear named Bea who goes to the doctor. You can read this book with your baby before a doctor's visit to help them understand the checkup process and reduce their fear. You can act out the scenes in the book as you read to make it more interesting.",developmentGoalEn:"This book helps your baby develop a positive perception of visiting the doctor and alleviates their anxiety. Reading also expands your baby's vocabulary and cultivates a reading habit.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this book is very useful and effectively helps their children overcome their fear of visiting the doctor. They read it repeatedly before taking their children for vaccinations or checkups. Some parents mentioned that their children love the little bear character in the book and imagine themselves as Bea. One parent said the book's illustrations are lovely and the quality is excellent."},{name:"棉布动物口袋",englishName:"Quilted Critter Pockets",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个挂在墙上或门把手上的棉布口袋，里面有几个不同的小动物。宝宝可以把小动物从口袋里拿出来，然后再放回去。你也可以教宝宝认识不同的小动物，或者玩“躲猫猫”的游戏。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的精细动作、手眼协调能力和物体恒存性概念。通过把动物放进和拿出袋子，宝宝可以练习抓握和放置的动作。",parentReview:"家长们认为这个玩具很可爱，也很实用。孩子们喜欢把小动物放进去再拿出来，这个过程能让他们安静地玩上一会儿。一些家长提到，他们会把这个玩具挂在婴儿床边或者游戏区，方便孩子随时玩耍。有家长抱怨说，这个玩具比较容易脏，需要经常清洗。",howToUseEn:"This is a cloth pocket that can be hung on a wall or doorknob, with several different small animals inside. Your baby can take the small animals out of the pocket and put them back in. You can also teach your baby to recognize the different animals or play a game of 'peek-a-boo'.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's fine motor skills, hand-eye coordination, and the concept of object permanence. By putting the animals in and taking them out of the bag, your baby can practice grasping and placing actions.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this toy is cute and practical. Children enjoy taking the small animals in and out, which can keep them quietly occupied for a while. Some parents mentioned that they hang this toy by the crib or in the play area for easy access. One parent complained that the toy gets dirty easily and needs frequent washing."},{name:"真实手电筒",englishName:"Really Real Flashlight",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个为宝宝设计的真实手电筒，开关很容易操作。宝宝可以自己打开和关闭手电筒，探索光和影的世界。你可以在一个比较暗的房间里和宝宝一起玩，用手电筒照亮不同的物体，或者玩手影游戏。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于激发宝宝的好奇心和探索欲，让他们了解因果关系（按下开关灯会亮）。通过在黑暗中玩耍，还可以帮助宝宝克服对黑暗的恐惧。",parentReview:"很多家长说他们的孩子非常喜欢这个手电筒，几乎走到哪里都带着。他们喜欢在家里探险，用手电筒照亮床底和角落。一些家长提到，这个手电筒的灯光比较柔和，不会伤害宝宝的眼睛。有家长抱怨说，手电筒的电池耗得比较快。",howToUseEn:"This is a real flashlight designed for your baby, with an easy-to-operate switch. Your baby can turn the flashlight on and off by themselves and explore the world of light and shadow. You can play with your baby in a relatively dark room, using the flashlight to illuminate different objects or play hand shadow games.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps stimulate your baby's curiosity and desire to explore, allowing them to understand cause and effect (pressing the switch turns the light on). Playing in the dark can also help your baby overcome their fear of the dark.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say their children absolutely love this flashlight and carry it with them almost everywhere. They enjoy exploring at home, using the flashlight to illuminate under the bed and in corners. Some parents mentioned that the flashlight's light is relatively soft and won't harm the baby's eyes. One parent complained that the flashlight's batteries run out rather quickly."},{name:"带凹槽的水壶和杯子",englishName:"Grooved Pitcher & Glass",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一套为宝宝设计的倒水玩具。水壶和杯子的大小和形状都适合宝宝的小手抓握。你可以先在水壶里装少量的水，然后引导宝宝把水倒进杯子里。这个过程可以在洗澡时或者在户外进行，不用担心会把水洒得到处都是。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力、控制力和专注力。通过倒水，宝宝可以学习到液体的特性，并且为以后自己喝水和吃饭做准备。",parentReview:"家长们认为这是一个非常经典的蒙特梭利玩具，能有效地锻炼宝宝的各种能力。他们喜欢看着孩子专注地倒水，并且为自己的成功感到高兴。一些家长提到，他们的孩子在玩过这个玩具后，自己喝水时洒得更少了。有家长建议，一开始可以先用米或者豆子代替水，降低难度。",howToUseEn:"This is a pouring toy set designed for your baby. The size and shape of the pitcher and glass are suitable for your baby's small hands to grasp. You can start by putting a small amount of water in the pitcher and then guide your baby to pour the water into the glass. This can be done during bath time or outdoors, so you don't have to worry about spilling water everywhere.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's hand-eye coordination, control, and concentration. By pouring water, your baby can learn about the properties of liquids and prepare for drinking and eating on their own later.",parentReviewEn:"Parents consider this a classic Montessori toy that effectively develops various skills in babies. They enjoy watching their children concentrate on pouring and feel happy about their success. Some parents mentioned that after playing with this toy, their children spill less when drinking by themselves. One parent suggested starting with rice or beans instead of water to reduce the difficulty."}]},{id:"companion",name:"The Companion",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-companion",ageRange:"22-24 个月",ageRangeEn:"22-24 months",ageMonths:"22-24m",stage:"toddler",stageLabel:"幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Toddler Stage",color:"#A26F92",bgColor:"#FFEAF0",lightColor:"#FCDFE8",description:"宝宝快2岁了，开始意识到「我」是一个独立的人。语言进入爆发期，几乎每天都在蹦新词。最让人心化的变化是社交意识觉醒：开始模仿照顾别人——给玩偶盖被子拍拍背、发现你不开心会过来摸摸你的脸——这是同理心发展的最初迹象。",descriptionEn:"Your baby is almost 2 years old and is beginning to realize that 'I' am an independent person. Their language is exploding, with new words popping up almost every day. The most heartwarming change is the awakening of their social awareness: they start to imitate caring for others—tucking in a doll and patting its back, or touching your face when they notice you're unhappy—these are the first signs of developing empathy.",toys:[{name:"马赛克纽扣板",englishName:"Mosaic Button Board",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"把彩色纽扣按到板上对应的位置。先让宝宝自由探索按和拔的动作，然后引导按颜色排列。",developmentGoal:"精细运动——按纽扣需要拇指和食指精准施力。颜色认知和配对。图案感知。创造力启蒙。",parentReview:"宝宝很喜欢按纽扣的「咔嗒」感。使用时间长，22个月到3岁+都在玩。",howToUseEn:"Press the colorful buttons into the corresponding positions on the board. First, let your baby freely explore the actions of pressing and pulling, then guide them to arrange the buttons by color.",developmentGoalEn:"Fine motor skills—pressing the buttons requires precise force from the thumb and index finger. Color recognition and matching. Pattern perception. Introduction to creativity.",parentReviewEn:"My baby loves the 'click' sound of the buttons. It has a long usage time, from 22 months to 3+ years old."},{name:"木质投递柱",englishName:"Wooden Posting Stand",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"木质柱子上有多个插孔，配有彩色木质圆柱可以插入和拔出。可以练习颜色配对。",developmentGoal:"精细运动——对准孔洞插入。颜色认知。力量控制。专注力。",parentReview:"Companion套装的核心精细运动玩具。插入和拔出的操作对22-24个月的宝宝有恰到好处的挑战性。",howToUseEn:"The wooden stand has multiple holes, and comes with colorful wooden cylinders that can be inserted and removed. It can be used to practice color matching.",developmentGoalEn:"Fine motor skills—aligning and inserting into the holes. Color recognition. Force control. Concentration.",parentReviewEn:"The core fine motor toy of the Companion kit. The actions of inserting and removing provide just the right amount of challenge for a 22-24 month old baby."},{name:"搭扣桶",englishName:"The Buckle Barrel",category:"精细运动/社交情感",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"柔软材质的圆桶玩具，上面有各种搭扣、按扣和系带。可以在桶里藏小玩具作为「奖励」。",developmentGoal:"精细运动——操作搭扣、按扣需要手指灵活性。问题解决。因果关系。独立性培养。",parentReview:"学会解扣子后自己穿脱衣服的意愿明显提升。软质材料让宝宝可以随意揉捏不怕坏。",howToUseEn:"A soft barrel-shaped toy with various buckles, snaps, and ties. You can hide small toys inside the barrel as a 'reward'.",developmentGoalEn:"Fine motor skills—operating buckles and snaps requires finger dexterity. Problem-solving. Cause and effect. Fostering independence.",parentReviewEn:"After learning to unbuckle, my child's willingness to dress and undress independently has significantly increased. The soft material allows the baby to knead it without fear of breaking it."},{name:"《格雷厄姆两岁了》绘本",englishName:"'Graham Turns Two' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和宝宝一起阅读这本关于两岁生日的绘本，帮助宝宝理解成长中的大情绪。可以指着书中的画面问宝宝'他在做什么？'、'他开心吗？'，引导宝宝表达自己的感受。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝理解和表达与成长相关的复杂情绪，如兴奋、紧张和不安。通过故事中的角色，宝宝可以学习情绪词汇，发展社交情感能力。",parentReview:"很多家长反馈这本书在宝宝两岁前后特别有用，帮助孩子理解'长大'这个概念。故事简单温馨，画面柔和，宝宝很喜欢反复听。有家长说孩子会指着书说'我也两岁了'。",howToUseEn:"Read this board book about a second birthday with your baby to help them understand the big emotions that come with growing up. Point to the pictures and ask, 'What is he doing?', 'Is he happy?', to guide your baby in expressing their own feelings.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies understand and express complex emotions related to growing up, such as excitement, nervousness, and unease. Through the characters in the story, babies can learn emotional vocabulary and develop social-emotional skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report this book is particularly useful around their child's second birthday, helping them understand the concept of growing up. The story is simple and heartwarming, with soft illustrations, and babies love to listen to it over and over. One parent said their child would point to the book and say, 'I'm two years old too.'"},{name:"转移镊子和毛毡星星",englishName:"Transfer Tweezers & Felt Stars",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"示范用镊子夹起毛毡星星，从一个容器转移到另一个容器。让宝宝自己尝试，刚开始可能会用手直接拿，慢慢引导使用镊子。这是一个经典的蒙特梭利精细运动练习。",developmentGoal:"锻炼精细运动中的钳形抓握能力，为将来使用筷子和写字打基础。同时培养手眼协调和专注力，练习双手配合。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个玩具很好地锻炼了孩子的手指力量。有些家长说刚开始孩子会直接用手拿星星，但几周后就能熟练使用镊子了。毛毡星星颜色鲜艳，孩子很喜欢。Reddit上有家长说这是他们最喜欢的蒙特梭利活动之一。",howToUseEn:"Demonstrate using the tweezers to pick up the felt stars and transfer them from one container to another. Let your baby try it themselves; they may use their hands at first, but slowly guide them to use the tweezers. This is a classic Montessori fine motor exercise.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops the pincer grasp in fine motor skills, laying the foundation for using chopsticks and writing in the future. It also cultivates hand-eye coordination and concentration, and practices bilateral coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents feel that this toy is great for developing their child's finger strength. Some parents said that at first their child would just grab the stars with their hands, but after a few weeks they could use the tweezers proficiently. The felt stars are brightly colored and children love them. A parent on Reddit said this is one of their favorite Montessori activities."},{name:"蒙特梭利动物配对",englishName:"Montessori Animal Match",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"将动物模型和对应的图片卡摊开，让宝宝把动物模型放到对应的图片上。可以一边配对一边教宝宝动物的名字和叫声。也可以按类别分类（农场动物、野生动物等）。",developmentGoal:"通过配对活动培养分类和归纳能力，学习相似与不同的概念。同时扩展动物词汇，促进语言发展和认知能力。",parentReview:"这是很多家长推荐的蒙特梭利经典活动。小红书上有家长分享说孩子特别喜欢把小动物排成一排，还会给每个动物编故事。木制动物手感好，做工精细。有家长建议可以搭配动物主题的绘本一起使用。",howToUseEn:"Lay out the animal figures and their corresponding picture cards, and have your baby place the animal figures on the correct pictures. You can teach your baby the names and sounds of the animals as you match them. You can also sort them by category (farm animals, wild animals, etc.).",developmentGoalEn:"Develops classification and categorization skills through matching activities, and teaches the concepts of same and different. It also expands animal vocabulary and promotes language and cognitive development.",parentReviewEn:"This is a classic Montessori activity recommended by many parents. A parent on Xiaohongshu/RED shared that their child especially loves lining up the small animals and even makes up stories for each one. The wooden animals have a nice feel and are well-made. Some parents suggest using it with animal-themed picture books."},{name:"抽绳袋",englishName:"Drawstring Bag",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"宝宝，玩完玩具后，我们要把它们送回家哦。这个小袋子就是串珠的家，我们把珠子一颗一颗放进去，然后拉紧绳子，这样就不会弄丢啦。",developmentGoal:"这个抽绳袋可以教宝宝学习整理和收纳，培养他们的责任感和好习惯。打开和拉紧袋子的过程也能锻炼他们的精细动作。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个袋子非常实用，可以很好地收纳零散的玩具，避免丢失。很多评论提到，从小教孩子用袋子整理玩具，有助于培养他们的整洁习惯。袋子本身的质量也很好。",howToUseEn:"After playtime, encourage your baby to put the beads back into the drawstring bag one by one, then pull the string tight so nothing gets lost. This teaches tidying up as part of the play routine.",developmentGoalEn:"Teaches organization and responsibility through cleanup routines. Opening and closing the drawstring bag also exercises fine motor skills and hand coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this bag very practical for storing small toy pieces and preventing loss. Many note that teaching children to tidy up with the bag from an early age helps build neat habits. The bag itself is well-made and durable."},{name:"厚实木制拼图",englishName:"Chunky Wooden Jigsaw Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"先让宝宝观察完整的拼图，然后取出一两块让宝宝尝试放回去。拼图块厚实易抓握，适合小手操作。可以一边拼一边描述图案，增加语言互动。",developmentGoal:"锻炼空间认知和问题解决能力，培养形状识别和手眼协调。厚实的拼图块设计专门针对幼儿的抓握能力，帮助发展精细运动技能。",parentReview:"家长们普遍觉得这款拼图的厚度设计很贴心，小手容易抓握。难度适中，不会让孩子太沮丧。有家长说这是孩子的第一个真正的拼图，完成后特别有成就感。做工和用料都很好。",howToUseEn:"First, let your baby observe the completed puzzle, then take out one or two pieces and let them try to put them back. The puzzle pieces are thick and easy to grasp, perfect for little hands. You can describe the picture as you piece it together to increase language interaction.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops spatial awareness and problem-solving skills, and cultivates shape recognition and hand-eye coordination. The chunky puzzle pieces are specifically designed for a toddler's grasp, helping to develop fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally feel that the thickness of this puzzle is very thoughtful and easy for little hands to grasp. The difficulty is moderate, so it doesn't frustrate the child too much. One parent said this was their child's first real puzzle and they had a great sense of accomplishment after completing it. The workmanship and materials are excellent."}]},{id:"helper",name:"The Helper",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-helper",ageRange:"25-27 个月",ageRangeEn:"25-27 months",ageMonths:"25-27m",stage:"bigToddler",stageLabel:"大幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Big Toddler Stage",color:"#7FB685",bgColor:"#EEFAF0",lightColor:"#E2F5E5",description:"2岁+的宝宝有一个让人又感动又头疼的强烈愿望：「我要帮忙！」——帮你擦桌子、帮你倒水、帮你叠衣服。这个阶段是蒙特梭利教育里最核心的「实际生活」窗口期，越帮越忙没关系，重要的是让他觉得「我是家里有用的人」。",descriptionEn:"Toddlers aged 2+ have a strong desire that is both touching and a bit of a headache: 'I want to help!' - helping you wipe the table, pour water, and fold clothes. This stage is the core 'practical life' window in Montessori education. It's okay if they're more of a hindrance than a help; the important thing is to make them feel like 'I am a useful person in the family'.",toys:[{name:"可持续水槽带杯盘套装",englishName:"Super Sustainable Sink With Cups & Plates",category:"精细运动/社交情感",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这款玩具水槽可以真正地出水和循环，宝宝可以模仿大人洗碗的样子。爸爸妈妈可以引导宝宝将小杯子和小盘子放在水槽里，打开水龙头，用小手搓洗，体验玩水的乐趣。",developmentGoal:"通过玩这个水槽，宝宝可以锻炼手部精细动作和手眼协调能力，同时培养独立自主的意识和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长说这款水槽是Lovevery最值得入手的玩具之一，孩子能玩很久。但也有家长抱怨说水容易溅出来，弄得到处都是，而且有些水槽用了一段时间就坏了。",howToUseEn:"This toy sink can actually dispense and circulate water, allowing your baby to imitate adults washing dishes. Parents can guide their baby to place the small cups and plates in the sink, turn on the faucet, and scrub with their little hands to experience the fun of playing with water.",developmentGoalEn:"By playing with this sink, babies can exercise their fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination, while also cultivating a sense of independence and problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this sink is one of the most worthwhile Lovevery toys, as children can play with it for a long time. However, some parents complain that water easily splashes out and gets everywhere, and some sinks have broken after a period of use."},{name:"点点接龙",englishName:"Drop & Match Dot Catcher",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"爸爸妈妈可以引导宝宝将不同颜色的圆片投进轨道，观察它们滑落并被接住。可以鼓励宝宝按照颜色分类，或者创造自己的颜色序列，像玩一个垂直版的“四子棋”。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于发展宝宝的颜色识别能力、手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力。通过计划和匹配颜色，还能锻炼宝宝的早期规划和执行功能。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个玩具设计很巧妙，能吸引孩子的注意力。有的孩子不喜欢按照规则玩，但会自己发明很多新玩法。不过也有家长反映，这个玩具的“生命周期”比较短，孩子很快就玩腻了。",howToUseEn:"Parents can guide their baby to drop the different colored discs into the track and watch them slide down and get caught. You can encourage your baby to sort by color or create their own color sequences, like playing a vertical version of 'Connect Four'.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's color recognition, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving skills. By planning and matching colors, it also exercises your baby's early planning and executive functions.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this toy cleverly designed and able to attract children's attention. Some children don't like to play by the rules but invent many new ways to play. However, some parents have reported that this toy has a relatively short 'lifespan' and children get tired of it quickly."},{name:"毛毡排排花",englishName:"Felt Flowers in a Row",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"宝宝可以练习将一朵朵毛毡花插进木制底座的小孔里，或者把它们拿出来。爸爸妈妈可以鼓励宝宝按照颜色、大小或者自己的喜好来排列组合，创造一个属于自己的小花园。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于锻炼宝宝的手部精细动作和手眼协调能力。通过插拔和排列花朵，宝宝还能学习到关于序列和模式的早期数学概念。",parentReview:"很多家长喜欢这个玩具的颜值和开放性玩法，可以插花、可以过家家。但也有家长觉得，对于两岁多的孩子来说，这个玩具的玩法有些单一，吸引力不是特别持久。",howToUseEn:"Your baby can practice inserting the felt flowers into the small holes in the wooden base or taking them out. Parents can encourage their baby to arrange them by color, size, or their own preference to create their own little garden.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps exercise your baby's fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination. By inserting, removing, and arranging the flowers, your baby can also learn early math concepts about sequences and patterns.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love the look and open-ended play of this toy; it can be used for flower arranging or pretend play. However, some parents feel that for a two-year-old, the gameplay is a bit monotonous and doesn't hold their attention for very long."},{name:"双面阳光拼图",englishName:"Double-Sided Sunny Day Puzzle",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个拼图有两面，一面是太阳，一面是冲浪板和沙滩，宝宝可以挑战完成两个不同的图案。爸爸妈妈可以先和宝宝一起观察拼图块的形状和颜色，然后引导他们尝试将拼图块放到正确的位置。",developmentGoal:"玩拼图可以锻炼宝宝的形状识别能力、空间想象力和解决问题的能力。双面设计增加了挑战性，有助于提升宝宝的注意力和毅力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款双面拼图设计得很好，画面也很好看，能吸引孩子。但有些家长反映，对于刚接触拼图的宝宝来说，这个拼图有点难，需要大人比较多的引导。",howToUseEn:"This puzzle has two sides, one with a sun and the other with a surfboard and beach, allowing your baby to challenge themselves with two different patterns. Parents can first observe the shapes and colors of the puzzle pieces with their baby, then guide them to try placing the pieces in the correct positions.",developmentGoalEn:"Playing with puzzles can exercise your baby's shape recognition, spatial imagination, and problem-solving skills. The double-sided design adds a challenge that helps improve your baby's attention and perseverance.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this double-sided puzzle is well-designed with beautiful pictures that attract children. However, some parents have reported that for babies new to puzzles, this one is a bit difficult and requires a lot of adult guidance."},{name:"随心艺术套装（含可水洗蛋彩画棒）",englishName:"Anywhere Art Kit With Washable Tempera Paintsticks",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这套便携的艺术套装包含一个画板和几支固体蛋彩画棒，画棒像口红一样旋转出来，不会弄脏小手。宝宝可以随时随地在画板上自由涂鸦和创作。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于激发宝宝的艺术创造力和想象力。使用画棒可以锻炼宝宝的手部精细动作和握笔姿势，为以后的书写做准备。",parentReview:"家长们非常喜欢这个画板和画棒的设计，干净、便携，非常适合带出门。画棒的颜色很鲜艳，宝宝很喜欢。有些家长提到，画板的尺寸不是很大，但对于小宝宝来说足够了。",howToUseEn:"This portable art kit includes a drawing board and several solid tempera paint sticks. The paint sticks twist up like lipstick and won't stain little hands. Your baby can freely doodle and create on the drawing board anytime, anywhere.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps stimulate your baby's artistic creativity and imagination. Using the paint sticks can exercise your baby's fine motor skills and pencil grip, preparing them for future writing.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the design of this drawing board and paint sticks; it's clean, portable, and perfect for taking on the go. The colors of the paint sticks are vibrant, and babies love them. Some parents mentioned that the drawing board is not very large, but it's sufficient for a small baby."},{name:"我们来规划日常流程卡",englishName:"Let's Map It Out Routine Cards",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套卡片上画着各种日常活动，比如刷牙、洗澡、睡觉。爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起，用这些卡片来规划一天的行程，或者睡前的固定流程，让宝宝对接下来要做什么有清晰的预期。",developmentGoal:"使用流程卡可以帮助宝宝理解时间和顺序的概念，培养他们的计划性和条理性。当宝宝能够预测和掌控自己的日常活动时，他们的安全感和自信心也会得到提升。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这套卡片对于培养孩子的常规非常有帮助，尤其是在应对“可怕的两岁”时。卡片的质量很好，画面也很可爱。不过，也有家长认为，对于一些比较小的宝宝，可能还不太能理解这个概念。",howToUseEn:"This set of cards illustrates various daily activities, such as brushing teeth, bathing, and sleeping. Parents can use these cards with their baby to plan the day's schedule or a bedtime routine, giving the baby a clear expectation of what's to come.",developmentGoalEn:"Using routine cards can help your baby understand the concepts of time and sequence, cultivating their planning and organizational skills. When babies can predict and control their daily activities, their sense of security and self-confidence will also be enhanced.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this set of cards very helpful for establishing a child's routine, especially when dealing with the 'terrible twos.' The cards are of good quality and the pictures are cute. However, some parents think that younger babies may not yet understand the concept."},{name:"《做松饼》纸板书",englishName:"'Making Muffins' Board Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一本可以翻页的纸板书，讲述了和家人一起做松饼的故事。爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起阅读，一边指着书上的图画，一边讲述制作松饼的步骤，还可以一起数数书里的蓝莓。",developmentGoal:"阅读这本书可以帮助宝宝发展语言能力和早期数学概念，比如数数和顺序。书里关于家庭合作和分享的主题，也有助于培养宝宝的社会情感能力。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这本书，认为它不仅能教孩子数数，还能让他们了解到一个完整的故事和流程。很多宝宝都喜欢书里的翻翻页设计。有些家长甚至会根据书里的“食谱”和孩子一起真的动手做松饼。",howToUseEn:"This is a board book with flaps that tells the story of making muffins with family. Parents can read with their baby, pointing to the pictures in the book, telling the steps of making muffins, and counting the blueberries in the book together.",developmentGoalEn:"Reading this book can help your baby develop language skills and early math concepts, such as counting and sequencing. The themes of family cooperation and sharing in the book also help cultivate your baby's social-emotional skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love this book, believing it not only teaches children to count but also allows them to understand a complete story and process. Many babies love the flap design in the book. Some parents even follow the 'recipe' in the book and make muffins with their children."}]},{id:"enthusiast",name:"The Enthusiast",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-enthusiast",ageRange:"28-30 个月",ageRangeEn:"28-30 months",ageMonths:"28-30m",stage:"bigToddler",stageLabel:"大幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Big Toddler Stage",color:"#6EAB78",bgColor:"#ECF9EE",lightColor:"#DFF3E2",description:"28-30个月的宝宝正处于假装游戏的巅峰期——每天的固定节目是「泡茶」「做饭」「照顾宝宝」三部曲。情感认知方面有了质的飞跃：开始能识别和说出不同的情绪了。分类能力也上了一个台阶：能同时按颜色和大小两个维度来分组。",descriptionEn:"Babies between 28-30 months are at the peak of pretend play—their daily routine often includes a trilogy of 'making tea,' 'cooking,' and 'caring for a baby.' They experience a significant leap in emotional cognition, starting to identify and name different emotions. Their classification skills also advance, as they can now group objects by both color and size simultaneously.",toys:[{name:"分类叠叠插板拼图",englishName:"Sort & Stack Peg Puzzle",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"木质插板上有不同颜色和大小的柱子，宝宝需要把对应的圆环套到正确的柱子上。",developmentGoal:"多维度分类能力。精细运动。序列概念——从大到小排列。早期数学概念。",parentReview:"做工精良，颜色鲜艳。宝宝从随意套到有意识地配对排序，进步非常明显。",howToUseEn:"The wooden board has posts of different colors and sizes. Your baby needs to place the corresponding rings onto the correct posts.",developmentGoalEn:"Multi-dimensional classification skills. Fine motor skills. Understanding of sequence—arranging from largest to smallest. Early mathematical concepts.",parentReviewEn:"Excellent craftsmanship and vibrant colors. My baby's progress from randomly placing the rings to intentionally matching and sorting them has been remarkable."},{name:"情绪认知镜子和卡片套装",englishName:"Emotion Match Mirror & Card Set",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"卡片上展示不同的情绪表情。和宝宝一起看卡片，命名每种情绪，然后让宝宝对着镜子模仿这个表情。",developmentGoal:"情绪识别和命名。情感表达。同理心发展。自我认知。",parentReview:"非常有价值的社交情感工具，「宝宝学会说'我生气了'而不是直接发脾气」。",howToUseEn:"The cards display different emotional expressions. Look at the cards with your baby, name each emotion, and then have your baby imitate the expression in the mirror.",developmentGoalEn:"Emotion recognition and naming. Emotional expression. Empathy development. Self-awareness.",parentReviewEn:"A very valuable social-emotional tool. 'My baby has learned to say 'I'm angry' instead of just throwing a tantrum.'"},{name:"木质茶具套装",englishName:"Wooden Tea Set",category:"社交情感/精细运动",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Fine Motor",howToUse:"用茶壶、茶杯、茶碟进行「泡茶」假装游戏。可以引入礼貌用语——「请」、「谢谢」。",developmentGoal:"假装游戏能力。社交技能——轮流、分享和礼貌用语。精细运动——倒茶需要手腕控制。语言发展。",parentReview:"茶具套装是假装游戏的经典选择，宝宝特别喜欢给大人「泡茶」。做工好，木质手感温暖。",howToUseEn:"Engage in pretend play of 'making tea' with the teapot, teacups, and saucers. You can introduce polite words like 'please' and 'thank you.'",developmentGoalEn:"Pretend play skills. Social skills—taking turns, sharing, and using polite language. Fine motor skills—pouring tea requires wrist control. Language development.",parentReviewEn:"The tea set is a classic choice for pretend play. My baby especially loves 'making tea' for the adults. The quality is great, and the wooden material has a warm feel."},{name:"万向称重天平和小桶",englishName:"Every Which Weigh Scale & Pails",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"让孩子把不同的物品放进两边的小桶里，观察天平的变化。可以问'哪边更重？'、'怎样才能平衡？'。用滑块来校准天平，引入测量的概念。也可以用来比较家里不同物品的重量。",developmentGoal:"引入早期STEM概念——平衡和测量。培养比较、预测和验证的科学思维，同时锻炼精细运动能力和手眼协调。",parentReview:"很多家长说这个天平是Lovevery最有教育意义的玩具之一。孩子会自发地到处找东西来称重比较。Reddit上有家长分享说孩子用它来'称'水果和积木，玩得不亦乐乎。做工精良，木制材质手感好。",howToUseEn:"Let your child put different objects into the pails on both sides and observe how the scale moves. You can ask, 'Which side is heavier?' or 'How can we make it balance?' Use the slider to calibrate the scale, introducing the concept of measurement. It can also be used to compare the weights of different household items.",developmentGoalEn:"Introduces early STEM concepts—balance and measurement. Cultivates scientific thinking skills like comparison, prediction, and verification, while also exercising fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this scale is one of Lovevery's most educational toys. Children spontaneously find things around the house to weigh and compare. A parent on Reddit shared that their child loves using it to 'weigh' fruits and blocks. The craftsmanship is excellent, and the wooden material feels great."},{name:"优雅野餐茶具套装",englishName:"Pinkies Up Picnic Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和孩子一起玩假装茶话会游戏——倒茶、递杯子、摆放餐具。可以邀请毛绒玩具一起参加，练习社交礼仪和语言表达。配有不锈钢小勺和棉质餐垫，增加真实感。",developmentGoal:"通过角色扮演促进想象力和社交技能发展。练习倒水、递送等精细运动，学习餐桌礼仪和社交互动。",parentReview:"小红书上很多家长晒这套茶具，说孩子每天都要'请客喝茶'。不锈钢勺子和棉质餐垫的细节让家长很惊喜。有家长说这套玩具让孩子的语言能力突飞猛进，因为茶话会需要大量的对话和互动。",howToUseEn:"Play a pretend tea party with your child—pour tea, pass cups, and arrange the utensils. You can invite stuffed animals to join in to practice social etiquette and language expression. It comes with stainless steel spoons and a cotton placemat for a more realistic feel.",developmentGoalEn:"Promotes imagination and social skills through role-playing. Practices fine motor skills like pouring and passing, and teaches table manners and social interaction.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents on Xiaohongshu/RED have posted about this tea set, saying their children want to 'host a tea party' every day. Parents are pleasantly surprised by the details like the stainless steel spoons and cotton placemat. One parent mentioned that this toy led to a significant improvement in their child's language skills due to the extensive conversation and interaction required for a tea party."},{name:"干净利落清洁套装",englishName:"Squeaky Clean Squeegee Set",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"给孩子一个小喷壶（喷出的是温和的水雾）和刮水器，让孩子帮忙'打扫'窗户、镜子或桌面。这是蒙特梭利'实际生活'练习的一部分，让孩子参与家务。",developmentGoal:"培养独立性和责任感，锻炼大运动和精细运动协调。喷壶的按压动作锻炼手指力量，刮水器的使用练习双手协调。",parentReview:"家长们说这是让孩子'帮忙做家务'的完美工具。喷壶设计得很好，喷出的水雾很细，不会弄得到处都是。有家长说孩子每天都要'擦窗户'，虽然越擦越脏但玩得很开心。Reddit上有家长推荐这个作为让孩子参与家务的入门工具。",howToUseEn:"Give your child a small spray bottle (which mists a gentle spray of water) and a squeegee to help 'clean' windows, mirrors, or tabletops. This is part of the Montessori 'practical life' exercises, allowing children to participate in household chores.",developmentGoalEn:"Fosters independence and a sense of responsibility, and exercises gross and fine motor coordination. The pressing action of the spray bottle strengthens finger muscles, and using the squeegee practices bilateral coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents say this is the perfect tool to get their kids to 'help with chores.' The spray bottle is well-designed, producing a fine mist that doesn't make a mess. One parent said their child wants to 'clean the windows' every day, and although they get dirtier, the child has a lot of fun. A parent on Reddit recommended this as a great introductory tool for getting children involved in household tasks."},{name:"《我最喜欢的自然伙伴》绘本",englishName:"'My Favorite Nature Buddy' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和孩子一起阅读这本关于大自然的绘本，可以在户外散步时带上，对照书中的内容寻找真实的自然元素。鼓励孩子说出自己最喜欢的自然事物。",developmentGoal:"培养对大自然的热爱和观察力，扩展自然相关词汇。通过将书中内容与真实世界联系，发展认知和语言能力。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这本书很适合带孩子去公园时一起看。画面温馨，内容贴近生活。有家长说孩子看完后会主动指着树和花说'这是我的自然伙伴'，非常可爱。",howToUseEn:"Read this nature-themed board book with your child. You can take it with you on walks outdoors to find real natural elements that match the content of the book. Encourage your child to name their favorite things in nature.",developmentGoalEn:"Cultivates a love for nature and observation skills, and expands nature-related vocabulary. Develops cognitive and language skills by connecting the book's content with the real world.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this book perfect for reading with their children at the park. The illustrations are heartwarming and the content is relatable. One parent said that after reading the book, their child would point to trees and flowers and say, 'This is my nature buddy,' which is very cute."}]},{id:"researcher",name:"The Researcher",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-researcher",ageRange:"31-33 个月",ageRangeEn:"31-33 months",ageMonths:"31-33m",stage:"bigToddler",stageLabel:"大幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Big Toddler Stage",color:"#5DA06B",bgColor:"#EAF8EC",lightColor:"#DCF1DF",description:"31-33个月的宝宝成了家里的「十万个为什么」——对什么都好奇，追着问「为什么」。手部力量和协调性明显增强，可以玩锤子敲打、旋转拧动。记忆力也在进步，能玩简单的配对翻牌游戏了。",descriptionEn:"Babies aged 31-33 months become the 'whys' of the family—curious about everything and always asking 'why.' Their hand strength and coordination have significantly improved, allowing them to play with hammering, twisting, and turning toys. Their memory is also improving, and they can play simple matching and memory games.",toys:[{name:"扭转旋转叠叠乐",englishName:"Twist & Pivot Pattern Puzzle",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这款拼图玩具挑战宝宝的精细动作和解决问题的能力。父母可以先向宝宝展示如何扭转和旋转不同形状的积木，然后鼓励他们自己尝试将积木从底座上取下并重新放回。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于发展宝宝的手眼协调能力、精细动作、空间推理和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长反映这款拼图比看起来要难，对宝宝的耐心和挫折容忍度是不小的考验。但一旦宝宝掌握了玩法，就会获得巨大的成就感。一些家长建议，刚开始可以把底座拿走，让宝宝先熟悉积木的玩法。",howToUseEn:"This puzzle toy challenges your baby's fine motor skills and problem-solving abilities. Parents can first show their baby how to twist and pivot the different shaped blocks, then encourage them to try removing the blocks from the base and putting them back on their own.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's hand-eye coordination, fine motor skills, spatial reasoning, and problem-solving abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report that this puzzle is harder than it looks, and it's a real test of a baby's patience and frustration tolerance. But once they master it, they feel a great sense of accomplishment. Some parents suggest removing the base at first to let the baby get familiar with how the blocks work."},{name:"配对敲击小锤盒",englishName:"Match & Tap Hammer Box",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这款玩具鼓励宝宝通过敲打来锻炼。父母可以引导宝宝将不同颜色的圆柱体与盒子上的颜色进行配对，然后用小锤子将它们敲进去。这不仅充满乐趣，还能帮助宝宝释放多余的精力。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于提高宝宝的手眼协调能力、力量控制、以及颜色识别和配对的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长表示，他们的孩子非常喜欢这款敲打玩具，可以玩上很久。它被认为是 ‘研究者’ 系列中最受欢迎的玩具之一。不过，也有一些家长认为Lovevery的玩具价格偏高。",howToUseEn:"This toy encourages your baby to get active through hammering. Parents can guide their baby to match the different colored cylinders to the colors on the box, then use the small hammer to tap them in. It's not only fun but also helps your baby release excess energy.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps improve your baby's hand-eye coordination, strength control, and color recognition and matching skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say their children love this hammering toy and can play with it for a long time. It's considered one of the most popular toys in the 'Researcher' kit. However, some parents feel that Lovevery toys are a bit pricey."},{name:"液体实验室",englishName:"Liquid Lab",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个玩具让宝宝化身小小科学家，探索液体的奇妙世界。父母可以引导宝宝使用滴管将不同颜色的水滴入试管中，观察颜色的混合和变化。也可以让他们感受不同容器中水的形态，初步理解容量和守恒的概念。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具有助于培养宝宝的早期STEM技能、精细动作、专注力以及对因果关系的理解。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具非常有创意，能让孩子安静地玩很久。它被认为是‘研究者’系列中最具科学启蒙意义的玩具之一。一些家长提到，孩子对混合颜色非常着迷，但需要注意防止孩子把有颜色的水弄得到处都是。",howToUseEn:"This toy lets your baby become a little scientist and explore the wonderful world of liquids. Parents can guide their baby to use the dropper to put different colored water into the test tubes and observe the mixing and changing of colors. They can also feel the shape of water in different containers to get a preliminary understanding of the concepts of capacity and conservation.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps cultivate your baby's early STEM skills, fine motor skills, concentration, and understanding of cause and effect.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this toy is very creative and can keep their children quietly engaged for a long time. It is considered one of the most scientifically enlightening toys in the 'Researcher' series. Some parents mentioned that their children are fascinated by mixing colors, but they need to be careful to prevent them from getting colored water everywhere."},{name:"倒计时颜色沙漏",englishName:"Countdown Color Timer",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这款计时器可以帮助幼儿理解时间概念，并缓解转换活动时的困难。父母可以用它来为各种活动设置一个视觉倒计时，比如游戏时间、看屏幕时间或者准备出门。消失的颜色为时间的流逝提供了一个清晰而具体的可视化呈现。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于培养孩子对时间的理解、耐心和自我调节能力。它还可以减少孩子在活动转换期间的挫败感和焦虑感。",parentReview:"家长们发现这款计时器对于管理幼儿的日常生活和活动转换非常有用。他们很欣赏这种视觉提示，认为它比口头提醒对年幼的孩子更有效。一些家长提到他们希望更早得到这款计时器。少数家长指出，产品需要自备电池。",howToUseEn:"This timer can help young children understand the concept of time and ease the difficulty of transitioning between activities. Parents can use it to set a visual countdown for various activities, such as playtime, screen time, or getting ready to go out. The disappearing color provides a clear and concrete visualization of the passage of time.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps cultivate a child's understanding of time, patience, and self-regulation skills. It can also reduce a child's frustration and anxiety during activity transitions.",parentReviewEn:"Parents have found this timer to be very useful for managing their young children's daily routines and activity transitions. They appreciate the visual cue, believing it to be more effective for young children than verbal reminders. Some parents mentioned they wished they had gotten this timer sooner. A few parents pointed out that the product requires batteries, which are not included."},{name:"交通工具记忆翻翻乐",englishName:"Things That Move Memory Game",category:"认知/语言",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Language",howToUse:"这款记忆游戏帮助宝宝锻炼记忆力和匹配能力。父母可以先把所有的卡片面朝下放置，然后轮流翻开两张卡片，如果图案相同就可以拿走，不同则需要翻回去。刚开始可以只用几对卡片，等宝宝熟悉后再增加难度。",developmentGoal:"这款游戏主要锻炼宝宝的短期记忆力、专注力、以及图形识别和匹配能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这款记忆游戏玩法多样，除了经典的记忆游戏，还可以用来学习交通工具的名称、做分类、甚至是学习简单的数学规律。一些家长提到，对于年龄稍大的孩子来说，这个游戏可能会有点简单，但对于刚接触记忆游戏的孩子来说是个不错的选择。",howToUseEn:"This memory game helps your baby exercise their memory and matching skills. Parents can start by placing all the cards face down, then take turns flipping over two cards. If the patterns match, they can take them; if not, they need to be flipped back. You can start with just a few pairs of cards and increase the difficulty as your baby becomes more familiar with the game.",developmentGoalEn:"This game mainly exercises your baby's short-term memory, concentration, and pattern recognition and matching skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this memory game has diverse gameplay. Besides the classic memory game, it can also be used to learn the names of vehicles, for sorting, and even for learning simple mathematical patterns. Some parents mentioned that for slightly older children, this game might be a bit simple, but it's a good choice for children who are new to memory games."},{name:"跳圈圈和沙包",englishName:"Jump-In Hoops & Bean Bags",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这款玩具鼓励宝宝进行大肌肉运动。父母可以把圈圈放在地上，鼓励宝宝从一个跳到另一个，或者把沙包扔进圈圈里。这些活动可以在室内或室外进行，玩法非常多样。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具有助于发展宝宝的全身协调性、平衡感、以及投掷和跳跃等大肌肉运动技能。",parentReview:"家长们认为这款玩具是消耗孩子旺盛精力的好方法。他们喜欢这款玩具玩法的多样性，可以根据孩子的年龄和能力进行调整。一些家长提到，他们的孩子非常喜欢扔沙包的游戏。",howToUseEn:"This toy encourages your baby to engage in gross motor activities. Parents can place the hoops on the floor and encourage their baby to jump from one to another, or to toss the beanbags into the hoops. These activities can be done indoors or outdoors and are very versatile.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your baby's full-body coordination, balance, and gross motor skills such as throwing and jumping.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this toy is a great way to burn off their child's abundant energy. They like the versatility of the toy's gameplay, which can be adjusted according to the child's age and ability. Some parents mentioned that their children really enjoy the beanbag toss game."},{name:"《游戏日》纸板书",englishName:"'The Play Date' Board Book",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"这本书通过真实的照片和简单的故事，向宝宝展示了和小伙伴一起玩的场景，包括分享、合作和解决冲突。父母可以和宝宝一起阅读，并讨论书中的情节，帮助宝宝理解社交规则。",developmentGoal:"这本书有助于培养宝宝的社交情感能力、同理心以及解决问题的能力。它也为宝宝即将经历的社交场景提供了很好的预演。",parentReview:"很多家长认为这本书对于引导孩子学习如何与他人相处非常有帮助。他们喜欢书中使用的真实照片，认为这比插画更能吸引孩子的注意力。一些家长提到，这本书是他们和孩子讨论分享和轮流等概念的起点。",howToUseEn:"Through real photos and a simple story, this book shows your baby scenes of playing with friends, including sharing, cooperating, and resolving conflicts. Parents can read with their baby and discuss the plot of the book to help them understand social rules.",developmentGoalEn:"This book helps cultivate your baby's social-emotional skills, empathy, and problem-solving abilities. It also provides a good rehearsal for the social scenes your baby will soon experience.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents think this book is very helpful for guiding children on how to get along with others. They like the use of real photos in the book, believing it attracts children's attention more than illustrations. Some parents mentioned that this book was the starting point for them to discuss concepts like sharing and taking turns with their children."}]},{id:"freeSpirit",name:"The Free Spirit",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-free-spirit",ageRange:"34-36 个月",ageRangeEn:"34-36 months",ageMonths:"34-36m",stage:"bigToddler",stageLabel:"大幼儿阶段",stageLabelEn:"Big Toddler Stage",color:"#4C965E",bgColor:"#E8F7EA",lightColor:"#D9EFDC",description:"34-36个月的孩子进入了「我自己来！」的主权宣示期——什么都想自己做。审美偏好强烈到让你怀疑是不是遗传了某种设计基因。假装游戏进入高级模式，能维持一个连贯的故事线长达十几分钟。",descriptionEn:"Children between 34-36 months enter the 'I do it myself!' phase of asserting their independence—they want to do everything themselves. Their aesthetic preferences are so strong you might wonder if they've inherited some kind of design gene. Pretend play enters an advanced mode, where they can maintain a coherent storyline for over ten minutes.",toys:[{name:"带锁的木制露营车",englishName:"Wooden Camper With Locking Doors",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"鼓励孩子用钥匙打开和锁上车门，锻炼手眼协调能力。可以把小玩偶放进车里，假装去露营，培养想象力。",developmentGoal:"发展精细动作技能、解决问题能力和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"很多家长说这是“自由精神”盒子里的最爱，孩子很喜欢玩开锁和载着小玩偶到处走。但也有家长提到，钥匙比较小，容易弄丢。",howToUseEn:"Encourage your child to use the key to open and lock the camper doors, which helps develop hand-eye coordination. You can put small dolls inside and pretend to go camping, fostering their imagination.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops fine motor skills, problem-solving abilities, and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this is their favorite toy in the 'Free Spirit' kit. Their children love playing with the lock and carrying small dolls around in the camper. However, some parents mentioned that the key is small and easy to lose."},{name:"梵高户外探险",englishName:"Van Go Outdoor Adventure",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和露营车搭配，可以创造一个完整的户外探险场景。把小木人放在帐篷里，或者围着篝火，讲述野营的故事。",developmentGoal:"激发想象力和创造力，鼓励角色扮演和讲故事的能力。",parentReview:"家长们喜欢它能和露营车完美搭配，创造出更丰富的游戏场景。有些评论提到，布料的帐篷和睡袋质量很好，很耐用。",howToUseEn:"Pair it with the camper to create a complete outdoor adventure scene. Place the little wooden people in the tent or around the campfire and tell camping stories.",developmentGoalEn:"Sparks imagination and creativity, and encourages role-playing and storytelling skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love that it pairs perfectly with the camper to create richer play scenarios. Some reviews mentioned that the fabric tent and sleeping bags are high-quality and durable."},{name:"木制计数盒",englishName:"Wooden Counting Box",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"帮助孩子学习计数和颜色分类。可以把不同颜色的小木棍插到对应颜色的孔里，或者数一数每个孔里有多少根木棍。",developmentGoal:"培养早期数学技能，如计数、分类和颜色识别。",parentReview:"一些家长觉得这个玩具对他们快三岁的孩子来说有点太简单了，但另一些家长则认为这是一个很好的学习工具，可以为更复杂的数学概念打下基础。",howToUseEn:"Help your child learn counting and color sorting. You can insert the small wooden sticks into the holes of the corresponding color, or count how many sticks are in each hole.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops early math skills such as counting, sorting, and color recognition.",parentReviewEn:"Some parents feel this toy is a bit too simple for their nearly three-year-old, but others find it a great learning tool that lays the foundation for more complex math concepts."},{name:"天地两块拼图板",englishName:"Land And Sky Two-Part Puzzle Board",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个简单的拼图，帮助孩子理解部分与整体的关系。可以引导孩子观察拼图的形状和颜色，找到正确的位置。",developmentGoal:"发展空间推理能力、形状识别和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"家长们喜欢这个拼图的设计，认为它对幼儿来说是一个很好的入门级拼图。有些家长提到，他们的孩子很快就掌握了，并希望能有更复杂的拼图。",howToUseEn:"This is a simple puzzle that helps children understand the relationship between parts and the whole. You can guide your child to observe the shapes and colors of the puzzle pieces to find the correct spot.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops spatial reasoning, shape recognition, and problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the design of this puzzle, considering it a great entry-level puzzle for toddlers. Some parents mentioned that their children mastered it quickly and wished for more complex puzzles."},{name:"实木堆叠“鹅卵石”",englishName:"Solid Wood Stacking Boulders",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这些不规则形状的木块可以用来堆叠和平衡，挑战孩子的创造力和耐心。可以和孩子比赛，看谁能把“鹅卵石”堆得更高。",developmentGoal:"培养精细动作技能、平衡感和专注力。",parentReview:"很多家长和孩子都喜欢这个玩具，认为它比传统的积木更有趣、更有挑战性。但也有评论说，如果孩子喜欢把东西扔来扔去，这些木块可能会有点危险。",howToUseEn:"These irregularly shaped wooden blocks can be used for stacking and balancing, challenging your child's creativity and patience. You can have a competition with your child to see who can stack the 'boulders' higher.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops fine motor skills, a sense of balance, and concentration.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents and children love this toy, finding it more fun and challenging than traditional building blocks. However, some reviews say that the wooden blocks can be a bit dangerous if your child likes to throw things."},{name:"“摘星”配对卡",englishName:"Reach For The Stars Matching Cards",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这套卡片有三种玩法：分类、配对和计数。可以教孩子认识不同的形状和颜色，并把它们匹配起来。",developmentGoal:"发展认知能力，包括分类、配对和计数。",parentReview:"家长们认为这是一个多功能的学习工具，可以在孩子成长的不同阶段使用。有些家长提到，卡片的质量很好，不容易被撕坏。",howToUseEn:"This set of cards can be played in three ways: sorting, matching, and counting. You can teach your child to recognize different shapes and colors and match them up.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops cognitive skills, including sorting, matching, and counting.",parentReviewEn:"Parents consider this a versatile learning tool that can be used at different stages of their child's development. Some parents mentioned that the cards are of good quality and not easily torn."},{name:"《我三岁了》纸板书",englishName:"'Now That I'm Three' Board Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"和孩子一起阅读这本书，讨论书中描绘的三岁孩子的生活和情感。可以鼓励孩子分享自己的感受和经历。",developmentGoal:"培养语言能力和情商，帮助孩子理解和表达自己的情感。",parentReview:"家长们喜欢这本书能帮助他们和孩子开启关于情感和成长的对话。书中的插图和故事都很贴近三岁孩子的生活。",howToUseEn:"Read this book with your child and discuss the life and emotions of a three-year-old as depicted in the book. You can encourage your child to share their own feelings and experiences.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops language skills and emotional intelligence, helping children understand and express their own emotions.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love that this book helps them start conversations with their children about emotions and growing up. The illustrations and stories are very relatable to a three-year-old's life."}]},{id:"observer",name:"The Observer",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-observer",ageRange:"37-39 个月",ageRangeEn:"37-39 months",ageMonths:"37-39m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#6C8EAD",bgColor:"#EEF4F9",lightColor:"#E2EDF5",description:"3岁左右的孩子眼睛变得特别尖——能发现一只小蚂蚁在爬、注意到你换了发型、记住上次经过的那家冰淇淋店的位置。对周围世界越来越好奇，问题也越来越刁钻。孩子开始能沉浸在「小世界」游戏里自己玩一阵子了。",descriptionEn:"Around the age of three, a child's eyes become particularly sharp—they can spot a tiny ant crawling, notice you've changed your hairstyle, and remember the location of that ice cream shop you passed by last time. They become increasingly curious about the world around them, and their questions become more and more tricky. The child is now able to immerse themselves in 'small world' play for a while on their own.",toys:[{name:"未来天气规划板",englishName:"Plan Ahead Weather Board",category:"认知/语言",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Language",howToUse:"家长可以和宝宝一起，根据今天的天气情况，在板上选择对应的天气、温度和穿着。还可以讨论明天的计划，让宝宝对时间概念有初步的认知。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝理解天气变化、学习日常规划，并培养对时间和顺序的初步概念。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个天气板是帮助孩子理解日常安排的好工具，但也有不少人抱怨贴纸容易损坏，显得有些廉价，希望能换成磁吸或者木制的卡片。",howToUseEn:"Parents can work with their baby to select the corresponding weather, temperature, and clothing on the board based on today's weather conditions. They can also discuss tomorrow's plans to give the baby a preliminary understanding of the concept of time.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies understand weather changes, learn daily planning, and develop a preliminary concept of time and sequence.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this weather board to be a great tool for helping children understand daily routines, but many also complain that the stickers are easily damaged and seem a bit cheap, hoping for magnetic or wooden cards instead."},{name:"模块化游戏屋",englishName:"Modular Playhouse",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这个游戏屋可以让宝宝自由组合和搭建，创造出不同形状的房子。家长可以引导宝宝思考房子的结构，或者用它来玩过家家的游戏。",developmentGoal:"激发宝宝的想象力和创造力，锻炼空间思维和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这个玩具的开放性，可以有很多种玩法，并且能和其他玩具搭配。不过也有人提到，如果组件再多一些，或者能和其他系列的组件兼容就更好了。",howToUseEn:"This playhouse allows babies to freely combine and build, creating houses of different shapes. Parents can guide their baby to think about the structure of the house, or use it to play house.",developmentGoalEn:"Stimulates the baby's imagination and creativity, and exercises spatial thinking and problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the open-ended nature of this toy, as it can be played with in many ways and can be combined with other toys. However, some have mentioned that it would be even better if there were more components or if it were compatible with components from other series."},{name:"木制配件",englishName:"Wooden Accessories",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这些木制配件可以搭配模块化游戏屋一起玩，比如可以作为家具或者装饰品。家长可以和宝宝一起，用这些配件来丰富游戏屋的场景。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的精细动作和场景构建能力，激发想象力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这些小配件做工精致，能给游戏屋增添很多乐趣。但也有人觉得数量有点少，希望能有更多不同种类的配件。",howToUseEn:"These wooden accessories can be played with together with the modular playhouse, for example, as furniture or decorations. Parents can work with their baby to use these accessories to enrich the playhouse scene.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops the baby's fine motor skills and scene-building abilities, and stimulates imagination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think these small accessories are exquisitely made and can add a lot of fun to the playhouse. But some also feel that the quantity is a bit small and hope for more different types of accessories."},{name:"双座小跑车",englishName:"Two-Seater Speedster",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"宝宝可以推着这个小跑车，带着两个小人偶去任何他们想去的地方。家长可以鼓励宝宝讲述小人偶的冒险故事。",developmentGoal:"鼓励宝宝进行富有想象力的游戏，发展讲故事的能力和社交情感技能。",parentReview:"这款小车很受孩子们欢迎，特别是可以坐两个小人偶的设计。一些家长提到，如果车轮更顺滑一些，或者车子本身更大一些会更好玩。",howToUseEn:"The baby can push this little roadster and take two little figures wherever they want to go. Parents can encourage the baby to tell adventure stories about the little figures.",developmentGoalEn:"Encourages imaginative play and develops storytelling and social-emotional skills.",parentReviewEn:"This little car is very popular with children, especially the design that can seat two little figures. Some parents mentioned that it would be more fun if the wheels were smoother or the car itself was bigger."},{name:"左右脚鞋子贴纸",englishName:"Left & Right Shoe Stickers",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"将贴纸分别贴在宝宝的左右脚鞋子里，帮助他们区分左右脚，并自己穿对鞋子。家长可以把穿鞋变成一个有趣的游戏。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝学习区分左右，培养独立自理能力。",parentReview:"这是一个非常实用的小工具，很多家长反映宝宝很喜欢，并且很快就学会了自己穿鞋。但也有评论说贴纸的粘性不够，容易脱落。",howToUseEn:"Place the stickers in the baby's left and right shoes, respectively, to help them distinguish between left and right and put on their shoes correctly by themselves. Parents can turn putting on shoes into a fun game.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies learn to distinguish left from right and develops independence and self-care skills.",parentReviewEn:"This is a very practical little tool. Many parents report that their babies love it and quickly learn to put on their own shoes. But there are also comments that the stickers are not sticky enough and fall off easily."},{name:"木制情绪娃娃",englishName:"Wooden Emotion Dolls",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套娃娃有不同的情绪表情，家长可以用它们来和宝宝讨论各种情绪，比如开心、难过、生气等，并告诉宝宝这些情绪都是正常的。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝认识和理解不同的情绪，发展情商和同理心。",parentReview:"家长们认为这套娃娃是进行情绪教育的绝佳工具，可以帮助孩子更好地表达自己。少数评论提到，如果娃娃的表情能更丰富一些就更好了。",howToUseEn:"This set of dolls has different emotional expressions. Parents can use them to discuss various emotions with their baby, such as happiness, sadness, anger, etc., and tell the baby that these emotions are all normal.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies recognize and understand different emotions, and develops emotional intelligence and empathy.",parentReviewEn:"Parents believe this set of dolls is an excellent tool for emotional education, which can help children better express themselves. A few comments mentioned that it would be better if the dolls' expressions could be more varied."},{name:"情绪主题绘本",englishName:"Emotion Book Set",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"通过阅读这些关于情绪的绘本，家长可以和宝宝一起探讨故事里角色的感受，并将这些感受和宝宝自己的经历联系起来。",developmentGoal:"通过故事帮助宝宝理解和处理复杂的情绪，提升语言能力和情感认知。",parentReview:"这套书的插画和故事都很棒，能有效帮助孩子理解情绪。一些家长希望这套书能有更多的互动元素。",howToUseEn:"By reading these picture books about emotions, parents can discuss the feelings of the characters in the stories with their baby and connect these feelings to the baby's own experiences.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps babies understand and deal with complex emotions through stories, and improves language skills and emotional cognition.",parentReviewEn:"The illustrations and stories in this set of books are great and can effectively help children understand emotions. Some parents hope that this set of books could have more interactive elements."}]},{id:"storyteller",name:"The Storyteller",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-storyteller",ageRange:"40-42 个月",ageRangeEn:"40-42 months",ageMonths:"40-42m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#6084A3",bgColor:"#ECF2F8",lightColor:"#DFEAF3",description:"40-42个月的孩子进入了「故事模式」——随时随地都在编故事。语言表达从短句进入完整叙事，能讲出有开头、经过和结尾的故事。想象力是这个阶段最耀眼的能力：给一块布就能变成超人斗篷、一个纸箱就是火箭飞船。",descriptionEn:"Children at 40-42 months enter a 'story mode'—they are constantly making up stories. Their language expression moves from short sentences to complete narratives, and they can tell stories with a beginning, middle, and end. Imagination is the most dazzling ability at this stage: a piece of cloth can become a superman's cape, and a cardboard box is a rocket ship.",toys:[{name:"轻松连接城堡套装",englishName:"Easy Connect Fort Set",category:"大运动/认知",categoryEn:"Gross Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"鼓励孩子发挥想象力，用连接杆和接头搭建自己的秘密基地或任何他们能想到的结构。家长可以引导孩子先从简单的造型开始，比如一个立方体，然后慢慢挑战更复杂的结构。",developmentGoal:"培养孩子的空间想象能力、手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力。通过团队合作搭建，还能锻炼社交和沟通技巧。",parentReview:"很多家长表示，这是他们孩子最喜欢的玩具之一，可以玩上好几个小时。不过也有一些家长抱怨说，对于年龄较小的孩子来说，连接件可能有点难插拔，需要大人帮忙。",howToUseEn:"Encourage your child to use their imagination to build their own secret base or any structure they can think of with the connecting rods and joints. Parents can guide their child to start with simple shapes, like a cube, and then gradually challenge them with more complex structures.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops your child's spatial imagination, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving skills. Building through teamwork also exercises social and communication skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this is one of their child's favorite toys and can be played with for hours. However, some parents have complained that the connectors can be a bit difficult for younger children to plug and unplug and require adult help."},{name:"木偶剧院和城堡罩",englishName:"Puppet Theater & Fort Covers",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"把它罩在轻松连接城堡套装上，立刻就能变出一个木偶剧院或者一个温馨的小帐篷。家长可以和孩子一起编排木偶戏，或者在帐篷里讲故事，享受亲子时光。",developmentGoal:"激发孩子的想象力和创造力，鼓励他们进行角色扮演和故事创作。同时，也能为孩子提供一个有安全感的个人空间。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这个配件的多功能性，既能当剧院又能当帐篷。有评论说，布料的质量很好，图案也很可爱。少数家长提到，如果能有更多的窗户或者开口会更好。",howToUseEn:"Drape it over the Easy Connect Fort Set to instantly create a puppet theater or a cozy little tent. Parents can put on puppet shows with their child or tell stories in the tent and enjoy parent-child time.",developmentGoalEn:"Sparks your child's imagination and creativity, encouraging them to engage in role-playing and storytelling. It also provides a safe personal space for your child.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love the versatility of this accessory, which can be used as both a theater and a tent. One review said the fabric is of good quality and the pattern is cute. A few parents mentioned that it would be better if there were more windows or openings."},{name:"故事木偶套装带变脸眼睛",englishName:"Storytelling Puppet Set With Changing Emotion Eyes",category:"语言/社交情感",categoryEn:"Language/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这套木偶的眼睛可以变换不同的情绪，家长可以用它来给孩子讲故事，并引导孩子认识和表达不同的情绪。比如，可以问孩子：“你觉得小兔子现在是什么心情？”",developmentGoal:"帮助孩子认识和理解不同的情绪，提高情商和语言表达能力。通过操纵木偶，还能锻炼孩子的手部精细动作。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这个设计非常巧妙，能帮助孩子更好地理解故事情节和人物情感。有评论说，木偶的材质很柔软，手感很好。一些家长希望这套木偶能有更多的动物选择。",howToUseEn:"This puppet set's eyes can change to different emotions. Parents can use it to tell stories to their children and guide them to recognize and express different emotions. For example, you can ask your child, 'How do you think the little rabbit is feeling right now?'",developmentGoalEn:"Helps children recognize and understand different emotions, improving their emotional intelligence and language skills. Manipulating the puppets also exercises their fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this design is very clever and helps children better understand the storyline and characters' emotions. One review said the puppet's material is very soft and feels good to the touch. Some parents wish there were more animal options in this puppet set."},{name:"挤压喷水拖把",englishName:"Squeeze & Spray Mop",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个儿童尺寸的真拖把，可以装上水真的喷出来。鼓励孩子模仿大人做家务，在玩乐中培养责任感。家长可以和孩子一起“大扫除”，让孩子负责擦自己的小桌子或地板。",developmentGoal:"培养孩子的自理能力和责任感，同时锻炼他们的手部力量和协调性。这也是一种很好的角色扮演游戏，满足孩子模仿大人的愿望。",parentReview:"很多家长说，他们的孩子对这个拖把爱不释手，非常热衷于“帮忙”做家务。有评论提到，这个拖把的设计很安全，喷水量也适合孩子玩。一些家长担心孩子会把水弄得到处都是。",howToUseEn:"This is a child-sized real mop that can be filled with water and really sprays. Encourage your child to imitate adults doing chores and develop a sense of responsibility while playing. Parents can have a ‘big clean-up’ with their child, letting them be responsible for wiping their own small table or floor.",developmentGoalEn:"Cultivates your child's self-care ability and sense of responsibility, while also exercising their hand strength and coordination. It is also a great role-playing game that satisfies a child's desire to imitate adults.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say their children can't get enough of this mop and are very enthusiastic about ‘helping’ with housework. One review mentioned that the mop's design is very safe and the amount of water it sprays is suitable for children to play with. Some parents worry that their children will get water everywhere."},{name:"字母发音动物拼图",englishName:"Letter Sounds Animal Puzzle",category:"认知/语言",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Language",howToUse:"这款拼图将字母、发音和动物结合在一起。家长可以引导孩子将字母块放到对应的动物图案上，并模仿动物的叫声或者读出字母的发音。",developmentGoal:"帮助孩子建立字母和发音之间的联系，为早期阅读打下基础。同时，拼图游戏本身也能锻炼孩子的形状识别能力和手眼协调能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款拼图对孩子的字母启蒙很有帮助，寓教于乐。有评论说，拼图的做工很好，木质光滑没有毛刺。少数家长反映，有些字母的形状比较相似，孩子容易混淆。",howToUseEn:"This puzzle combines letters, sounds, and animals. Parents can guide their child to place the letter blocks on the corresponding animal pictures and imitate the animal's sound or read the letter's sound.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps children build a connection between letters and sounds, laying the foundation for early reading. At the same time, the puzzle game itself can also exercise the child's shape recognition ability and hand-eye coordination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe that this puzzle is very helpful for their children's letter enlightenment and is educational and fun. One review said that the puzzle is well-made, and the wood is smooth and has no burrs. A few parents reported that some letters have similar shapes and are easy for children to confuse."},{name:"《出门啦》",englishName:"‘Out the Door’ Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一本关于日常生活流程的绘本，讲述了小主角Mira早上起床、刷牙、玩耍、最后准备出门的故事。家长可以和孩子一起阅读，并联系孩子自己的生活经验，帮助他们建立时间观念和顺序感。",developmentGoal:"帮助孩子理解日常生活的顺序和流程，培养他们的自理能力和时间观念。书中关于“先玩玩具还是先穿鞋”的冲突，也能引发孩子对解决问题的思考。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这本书非常贴近生活，孩子很有共鸣。书中的小冲突和解决方案，能帮助孩子更好地处理自己的情绪和需求。有评论说，这本书的画风很可爱，孩子很喜欢反复阅读。",howToUseEn:"This is a picture book about daily routines, telling the story of the main character, Mira, waking up in the morning, brushing her teeth, playing, and finally getting ready to go out. Parents can read with their children and connect it to their own life experiences to help them establish a sense of time and sequence.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps children understand the order and flow of daily life, and cultivates their self-care ability and sense of time. The conflict in the book about whether to play with toys first or put on shoes first can also trigger children's thinking about problem-solving.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents feel that this book is very close to life and that their children resonate with it. The small conflicts and solutions in the book can help children better manage their emotions and needs. One review said that the book's art style is very cute and that their child loves to read it over and over again."}]},{id:"problemSolver",name:"The Problem Solver",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-problem-solver",ageRange:"43-45 个月",ageRangeEn:"43-45 months",ageMonths:"43-45m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#54829D",bgColor:"#EAF0F6",lightColor:"#DCE8F1",description:"43-45个月的孩子进入「为什么大师」阶段——对世界运作方式充满好奇。逻辑思维有了质的飞跃，能理解「如果...那么...」的因果链条。对数字越来越敏感。科学兴趣萌发——喜欢把东西混在一起看「会变成什么」。",descriptionEn:"Children aged 43-45 months enter the 'Why Master' stage—full of curiosity about how the world works. Their logical thinking takes a quantum leap, and they can understand the 'if...then...' causal chain. They become more and more sensitive to numbers. Their scientific interest sprouts—they like to mix things together to see 'what will it become'.",toys:[{name:"海龟孵化游戏",englishName:"Turtle Hatch Game",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这是一款合作类桌游，爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起玩。轮流转动转盘，根据转盘的指示移动小海龟，目标是在太阳升起之前，帮助所有的小海龟宝宝回到海里。这个游戏可以帮助宝宝学习轮流等待和团队合作。",developmentGoal:"这款游戏可以锻炼宝宝的轮流等待、分享、计数和团队合作能力，同时也能提升他们的专注力和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长表示，这是他们最喜欢的Lovevery玩具之一。他们觉得这款游戏不仅有趣，还能教会孩子重要的社交技能，比如合作和轮流。有些家长提到，即使是两岁多的宝宝也能很好地参与进来，并且非常喜欢。",howToUseEn:"This is a cooperative board game that parents can play with their baby. Take turns spinning the spinner and moving the baby turtles according to the instructions on the spinner. The goal is to help all the baby turtles get back to the sea before the sun rises. This game can help your baby learn to take turns and work as a team.",developmentGoalEn:"This game can exercise your baby's ability to wait their turn, share, count, and work as a team. It can also improve their concentration and problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say this is one of their favorite Lovevery toys. They feel that this game is not only fun, but also teaches children important social skills, such as cooperation and taking turns. Some parents mentioned that even toddlers over two years old can participate well and enjoy it very much."},{name:"蒙氏数学棒和数字卡片",englishName:"Montessori Math Bars & Number Tiles",category:"认知",categoryEn:"Cognitive",howToUse:"这套玩具可以帮助宝宝建立早期的数学概念。爸爸妈妈可以引导宝宝将不同长度的数学棒和对应的数字卡片进行匹配，直观地感受数字大小和数量的关系。也可以用短的数学棒拼接成长的，来学习简单的加法。",developmentGoal:"这套玩具旨在通过具体、可触摸的物体，帮助宝宝建立对数学和数量的初步理解，锻炼他们的逻辑思维和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长认为这套玩具对培养孩子的数学思维很有帮助，质量也很好。有家长提到，虽然不是严格意义上的蒙特梭利教具，但它很好地体现了数学关系，让孩子在玩乐中学习。也有家长反映，孩子很喜欢玩，不知不觉中就练习了数学。",howToUseEn:"This set of toys can help your baby build early math concepts. Parents can guide their baby to match the math bars of different lengths with the corresponding number cards to intuitively feel the relationship between number size and quantity. You can also use short math bars to piece together longer ones to learn simple addition.",developmentGoalEn:"This set of toys aims to help babies build a preliminary understanding of mathematics and quantity through concrete, tangible objects, and to exercise their logical thinking and problem-solving abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents believe that this set of toys is very helpful for cultivating children's mathematical thinking, and the quality is also very good. Some parents mentioned that although it is not a Montessori teaching aid in the strict sense, it well reflects the mathematical relationship and allows children to learn while playing. Other parents have also reported that their children love to play with it and practice math without realizing it."},{name:"自然主题计数玩具",englishName:"Number Sense Nature Counters",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套计数玩具有55个可爱的小动物和自然造型的配件。爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起用这些配件来数数、分类、做配对游戏，或者结合数学棒一起使用，学习简单的加减法。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具旨在通过有趣、具体的方式，帮助宝宝学习计数和发展数感，同时也可以锻炼他们的分类和匹配能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这套计数玩具非常可爱，能够吸引孩子的注意力。他们喜欢用这些小配件和孩子一起玩各种数学游戏，觉得这是一种有趣的学习方式。有家长提到，这些配件的质量很好，而且有很多种玩法，可以玩很久。",howToUseEn:"This set of counting toys has 55 cute little animals and nature-shaped accessories. Parents can use these accessories with their baby to count, sort, play matching games, or use them with math bars to learn simple addition and subtraction.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy is designed to help babies learn to count and develop number sense in a fun and concrete way, while also exercising their classification and matching skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think that this set of counting toys is very cute and can attract children's attention. They like to use these small accessories to play various math games with their children, and they think it is a fun way to learn. Some parents mentioned that the quality of these accessories is very good, and there are many ways to play with them, so they can be played with for a long time."},{name:"我会量尺寸卷尺",englishName:"Size It Up Measuring Tape",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"爸爸妈妈可以鼓励宝宝用这个卷尺去测量身边的各种东西，比如玩具的长度、桌子的高度等等。卷尺上有厘米和英寸两种单位，可以教宝宝认识不同的长度单位。柔软的拉环设计很适合宝宝的小手。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具可以帮助宝宝建立对长度和测量的初步概念，锻炼他们的手眼协调能力和精细动作。",parentReview:"很多家长说，孩子很喜欢这个为他们量身定做的卷尺，可以像大人一样到处测量。他们觉得这是一个很好的将数学概念融入日常游戏的方式。不过也有家长提到，新版的卷尺没有锁定功能，拉出来后会自动收回，有些孩子会觉得有点失望。",howToUseEn:"Parents can encourage their baby to use this tape measure to measure various things around them, such as the length of a toy, the height of a table, and so on. The tape measure has both centimeters and inches, so you can teach your baby to recognize different units of length. The soft pull-loop design is perfect for your baby's little hands.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy can help your baby build a preliminary concept of length and measurement, and exercise their hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents say that their children love this tailor-made tape measure and can measure everywhere like adults. They think this is a great way to integrate mathematical concepts into daily games. However, some parents also mentioned that the new version of the tape measure does not have a locking function and will automatically retract after being pulled out, which some children will find a bit disappointing."},{name:"摇摆平衡拼图",englishName:"Wooden Wobble Puzzle",category:"精细运动/认知",categoryEn:"Fine Motor/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一个三维的STEM拼图游戏。爸爸妈妈可以引导宝宝将不同形状的木块，在摇摆的底座上拼搭起来，完成一个立方体。这个游戏有多种解法，可以鼓励宝宝不断尝试。",developmentGoal:"这款拼图可以锻炼宝宝的空间想象能力、逻辑思维和解决问题的能力，同时也需要耐心和专注力。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个拼图很有挑战性，像一个儿童版的俄罗斯方块。他们认为这个玩具可以很好地锻炼孩子的空间感和逻辑思维。有些家长提到，这个拼图对大人来说也有一定难度，可以和孩子一起研究，是一个很好的亲子互动玩具。",howToUseEn:"This is a three-dimensional STEM puzzle game. Parents can guide their baby to assemble wooden blocks of different shapes on a wobbly base to complete a cube. This game has multiple solutions, which can encourage your baby to keep trying.",developmentGoalEn:"This puzzle can exercise your baby's spatial imagination, logical thinking, and problem-solving skills, and it also requires patience and concentration.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this puzzle very challenging, like a children's version of Tetris. They believe that this toy can well exercise children's sense of space and logical thinking. Some parents mentioned that this puzzle is also difficult for adults, so they can study it with their children, which is a good parent-child interactive toy."},{name:"液体颜色实验室",englishName:"Liquid Color Lab",category:"认知/感官",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Sensory",howToUse:"这个玩具包含试管、滴管和彩色泡腾片，可以让宝宝安全地进行颜色混合实验。爸爸妈妈可以引导宝宝将不同颜色的泡腾片放入水中，观察颜色的变化，并用滴管将不同颜色的水混合，创造出新的颜色。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具旨在通过动手实验，激发宝宝对科学和艺术的兴趣，帮助他们学习颜色混合的原理，并锻炼他们的精细动作和观察能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这是一个非常有趣和有教育意义的玩具。孩子们非常喜欢自己动手混合颜色，感觉像个小科学家。很多家长提到，这个玩具可以玩很久，而且能延伸出很多创意玩法。不过，也有家长提醒，玩的时候最好做好防护，因为颜色可能会弄到衣服上。",howToUseEn:"This toy includes test tubes, droppers, and colored effervescent tablets, allowing your baby to safely conduct color mixing experiments. Parents can guide their baby to put effervescent tablets of different colors into the water, observe the color changes, and use a dropper to mix water of different colors to create new colors.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy aims to stimulate your baby's interest in science and art through hands-on experiments, help them learn the principles of color mixing, and exercise their fine motor skills and observation skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe that this is a very fun and educational toy. Children love to mix colors by themselves and feel like little scientists. Many parents mentioned that this toy can be played with for a long time and can be extended to many creative ways of playing. However, some parents also reminded that it is best to take protective measures when playing, because the color may get on the clothes."},{name:"《罗伯叔叔的披萨派对》绘本",englishName:"‘Uncle Rob's Pizza Party’ Book",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一本关于特殊人群的绘本。爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起阅读，通过故事了解和接纳与自己不同的人。故事讲述了一个孩子和患有安格曼综合症的罗伯叔叔之间的友谊。",developmentGoal:"这本绘本旨在帮助宝宝理解和尊重人与人之间的差异，培养他们的同理心和社会情感能力。",parentReview:"很多家长认为这本书非常有意义，能够帮助他们和孩子开启关于残障和特殊需求的对话。他们觉得故事很温暖，能够教会孩子用友善和开放的心态去接纳他人。有家长表示，这本书也帮助他们自己更好地理解和谈论这些话题。",howToUseEn:"This is a picture book about people with special needs. Parents can read it with their baby to understand and accept people who are different from themselves through the story. The story tells the friendship between a child and his Uncle Rob, who has Angelman syndrome.",developmentGoalEn:"This picture book aims to help babies understand and respect the differences between people and cultivate their empathy and social-emotional skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents believe that this book is very meaningful and can help them and their children start a conversation about disability and special needs. They feel that the story is very warm and can teach children to accept others with a friendly and open mind. Some parents said that this book also helped them better understand and talk about these topics."}]},{id:"analyst",name:"The Analyst",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-analyst",ageRange:"46-48 个月",ageRangeEn:"46-48 months",ageMonths:"46-48m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#487C95",bgColor:"#E8EEF4",lightColor:"#D9E5EF",description:"46-48个月的孩子有了一点「小科学家」的架势——不光问「为什么」，还想搞清楚「怎么证明」。喜欢做实验。对「一样」和「不一样」特别较真。手指的灵活程度已经可以尝试缝纫这种精细操作了。",descriptionEn:"Children aged 46-48 months start to act like little scientists—not only asking 'why,' but also wanting to figure out 'how to prove it.' They enjoy experimenting and are very particular about things being 'the same' or 'different.' Their finger dexterity has developed enough to try fine motor tasks like sewing.",toys:[{name:"蒙氏感官盒子",englishName:"Montessori Sensory Box",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个神秘盒子，家长可以把家里不同材质的小物件放进去，比如一个毛绒球、一块积木、一个光滑的石头。然后鼓励宝宝把手伸进盒子里触摸、感受，猜猜里面是什么。",developmentGoal:"锻炼宝宝的触觉感知能力和物体识别能力，通过触摸来理解不同的材质和形状，并激发他们的好奇心和探索欲。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个玩具很有趣，可以利用家里的各种小东西，玩法多变。不过也有家长反映，孩子玩几次就没兴趣了，而且需要家长一直引导和更换物品，有点费心。",howToUseEn:"This is a mystery box where parents can place small objects of different materials from around the house, such as a plush ball, a building block, or a smooth stone. Then, encourage your baby to reach into the box to touch, feel, and guess what's inside.",developmentGoalEn:"This exercises your baby's tactile perception and object recognition skills, helping them understand different materials and shapes through touch, while also stimulating their curiosity and desire to explore.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this toy very interesting and versatile, as it can be used with various small items from home. However, some parents report that their child loses interest after a few tries and that it requires constant guidance and changing of objects, which can be a bit demanding."},{name:"图案匹配船和卡片套装",englishName:"Pattern Match Boats & Cards Set",category:"认知",categoryEn:"Cognitive",howToUse:"这套玩具包含几艘小船和一些图案卡片。家长可以引导宝宝观察卡片上的图案，然后在底板上用相应的小船部件拼搭出一样的图案。除了匹配游戏，这些小船也可以作为开放式玩具，让宝宝自由玩耍。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的二维到三维空间转换能力、观察力和精细动作技能。通过匹配图案，锻炼他们解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具设计得很好，既能玩拼图匹配，又能当小船玩，一举两得。有评论说，孩子很喜欢用这些小船编故事。但也有人提到，对于年龄小一点的孩子来说，有些图案的匹配有点难。",howToUseEn:"This set includes several small boats and some pattern cards. Parents can guide their baby to observe the patterns on the cards and then use the corresponding boat parts to build the same pattern on the base. Besides the matching game, these small boats can also be used as open-ended toys for free play.",developmentGoalEn:"This helps develop your baby's ability to translate 2D to 3D, as well as their observation and fine motor skills. By matching patterns, they also practice their problem-solving abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this toy is well-designed, serving as both a puzzle matching game and a set of toy boats. One comment mentioned that their child loves creating stories with these little boats. However, some mentioned that the pattern matching can be a bit difficult for younger children."},{name:"可堆叠分数杯",englishName:"Stackable Fraction Cups",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一套可以嵌套的量杯，每个杯子代表一个分数，比如整体、一半、三分之一。家长可以和宝宝一起玩堆叠游戏，或者在玩沙、玩水的时候使用，通过实际操作感受分数的概念。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝建立对整体和部分的概念，初步理解分数的含义。同时，堆叠和嵌套的动作可以锻炼他们的手眼协调能力和空间感。",parentReview:"很多家长喜欢这个玩具，觉得它把抽象的分数概念变得很直观。在洗澡或者玩沙的时候用，孩子很喜欢。但也有家长觉得，对于三岁的孩子来说，分数的概念还是太早了，孩子只是把它们当作普通的堆叠杯来玩。",howToUseEn:"This is a set of nesting measuring cups, where each cup represents a fraction, such as a whole, a half, or a third. Parents can play stacking games with their baby or use them during sand and water play to help them grasp the concept of fractions through hands-on experience.",developmentGoalEn:"This helps your baby build an understanding of the concepts of whole and parts, and to begin to understand the meaning of fractions. At the same time, the actions of stacking and nesting can exercise their hand-eye coordination and spatial awareness.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love this toy, finding that it makes the abstract concept of fractions very intuitive. It's a hit during bath time or sand play. However, some parents feel that the concept of fractions is too advanced for a three-year-old, and their child just plays with them as regular stacking cups."},{name:"视觉食谱卡片",englishName:"Visual Recipe Cards",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套卡片用图画展示了制作简单食物的步骤，比如水果酸奶杯或煎饼。家长可以和宝宝一起看着卡片，一步一步地准备食材、制作食物，让宝宝有参与感和成就感。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的秩序感和遵循指令的能力，同时让他们了解食物的制作过程。这也是一个很好的亲子互动活动，可以增强宝宝的自信心。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这个创意，觉得它让孩子能够真正参与到厨房活动中。有评论说，孩子跟着卡片做出了自己的第一份早餐，特别自豪。但也有家长提到，需要准备的食材比较多，而且过程可能会有点乱。",howToUseEn:"This set of cards uses pictures to show the steps for making simple foods, like a fruit yogurt cup or pancakes. Parents and babies can follow the cards together, step-by-step, to prepare the ingredients and make the food, giving the child a sense of participation and accomplishment.",developmentGoalEn:"This cultivates your baby's sense of order and ability to follow instructions, while also teaching them about the food-making process. It is also a great parent-child interactive activity that can boost your baby's self-confidence.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love this creative idea, feeling that it allows their children to truly participate in kitchen activities. One comment said their child made their first breakfast following the cards and was extremely proud. However, some parents mentioned that it requires preparing a lot of ingredients and the process can get a bit messy."},{name:"色彩理论拼图",englishName:"Color Theory Puzzle",category:"认知/感官",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Sensory",howToUse:"这是一个关于颜色的圆形拼图，宝宝需要根据颜色的渐变和色调的深浅，把拼图块放到正确的位置。家长可以先引导宝宝认识不同的颜色和深浅变化，然后鼓励他们自己尝试完成拼图。",developmentGoal:"帮助宝宝学习色彩理论，理解颜色的混合和渐变。这个拼图可以锻炼他们的观察力、逻辑思维和解决问题的能力。",parentReview:"很多家长和孩子都非常喜欢这个拼图，觉得它设计得非常漂亮，很有艺术感。有评论说，孩子在玩的过程中对颜色变得非常敏感。缺点是，对于一些孩子来说，这个拼图有点挑战性，需要家长的耐心引导。",howToUseEn:"This is a circular puzzle about colors. Your baby needs to place the puzzle pieces in the correct position according to the color gradient and the shade of the hue. Parents can first guide their baby to recognize different colors and shades, and then encourage them to try to complete the puzzle on their own.",developmentGoalEn:"This helps your baby learn color theory and understand color mixing and gradients. This puzzle can exercise their observation skills, logical thinking, and problem-solving abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents and children love this puzzle, finding it beautifully designed and very artistic. One comment said that their child became very sensitive to colors while playing with it. The downside is that for some children, this puzzle is a bit challenging and requires patient guidance from parents."},{name:"儿童缝纫套装",englishName:"First Sewing Kit",category:"精细运动",categoryEn:"Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个套装里有安全的塑料针、预先打好孔的缝纫卡片和毛线。宝宝可以用针和线，跟着卡片上的图案进行缝纫。家长可以先做示范，然后让宝宝自己尝试，体验缝纫的乐趣。",developmentGoal:"这是一个非常好的精细动作训练活动，可以锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力、注意力和耐心。同时，完成一个缝纫作品也能给他们带来很大的成就感。",parentReview:"家长们认为这是一个很棒的蒙氏活动，能够很好地锻炼孩子的精细动作。有评论说，孩子刚开始可能不太会，但多试几次就上手了，而且非常专注。不过，家长需要在一旁监督，确保安全。",howToUseEn:"This kit contains a safe plastic needle, pre-punched sewing cards, and yarn. Your baby can use the needle and thread to sew along the patterns on the cards. Parents can demonstrate first, and then let the baby try it themselves to experience the fun of sewing.",developmentGoalEn:"This is an excellent fine motor training activity that can exercise your baby's hand-eye coordination, attention, and patience. At the same time, completing a sewing project can also bring them a great sense of accomplishment.",parentReviewEn:"Parents think this is a great Montessori activity that can effectively train a child's fine motor skills. One comment said that their child might not get it at first, but after a few tries, they get the hang of it and become very focused. However, parents need to supervise to ensure safety."},{name:"《四分之一、一半和整体》",englishName:"‘Quarter, Half, and Whole’ Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一本关于烘焙的有趣故事书。你可以和宝宝一起读，故事里会很自然地讲到“一半”苹果，“四分之一”杯面粉这样的概念。一边读，一边可以指着书上的图画，或者用真实的食物来比划，让宝宝更直观地理解。",developmentGoal:"这本书通过一个生活化的故事，帮助宝宝轻松接触和理解分数这个有点抽象的数学概念。它能培养宝宝对数学的兴趣，并让他们在实际情境中感受数学。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这本书非常可爱，用一种有趣、动手的方式介绍了分数的概念，很适合学龄前儿童。有些家长甚至说，这是他们在家进行数学启蒙的好帮手。目前没有看到太多负面评价，普遍认为Lovevery的书都做得很棒。",howToUseEn:"This is a fun storybook about baking. You can read it with your baby, and the story naturally introduces concepts like ‘half’ an apple or a ‘quarter’ cup of flour. While reading, you can point to the pictures in the book or use real food to demonstrate, making it more intuitive for your baby to understand.",developmentGoalEn:"Through a real-life story, this book helps your baby easily encounter and understand the somewhat abstract mathematical concept of fractions. It can cultivate your baby's interest in math and let them experience math in a practical context.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this book very cute, introducing the concept of fractions in a fun, hands-on way that is perfect for preschoolers. Some parents even say it's a great helper for their at-home math enlightenment. There are not many negative reviews, and the general consensus is that Lovevery's books are all very well made."}]},{id:"connector",name:"The Connector",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-connector",ageRange:"49-51 个月",ageRangeEn:"49-51 months",ageMonths:"49-51m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#3C768D",bgColor:"#E6ECF2",lightColor:"#D6E2ED",description:"49-51个月的孩子社交能力迎来质的飞跃——从「你玩你的我玩我的」真正变成了「我们一起来！」。能和小伙伴商量角色分工、学会了轮流当领导者和跟随者。对文字和符号产生强烈好奇。策略思维萌芽。",descriptionEn:"At 49-51 months, your child's social skills take a quantum leap. They move from parallel play to truly cooperative play, wanting to do things together. They can now negotiate roles with friends, learning to take turns as both leaders and followers. A strong curiosity about letters and symbols emerges, and strategic thinking begins to blossom.",toys:[{name:"发现与观察显微镜",englishName:"Discover & Inspect Microscope",category:"认知/感官",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Sensory",howToUse:"这款显微镜可以放大20倍，带宝宝去户外探索吧！观察树叶的纹理、花瓣的细节，甚至小昆虫的腿。在家里，可以用附带的图片幻灯片，引导宝宝认识各种有趣的图案。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的科学探索精神和细致的观察能力，为早期STEM学习打下基础。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这款显微镜是整个套装里最棒的玩具之一，孩子能玩很久。但也有一些家长抱怨说，显微镜的灯光不是很亮，而且需要确保电池安装正确才能使用。",howToUseEn:"This microscope magnifies up to 20x, so take your child outdoors to explore! Observe the texture of leaves, the details of flower petals, and even the legs of small insects. At home, you can use the included image slides to introduce your child to all sorts of interesting patterns.",developmentGoalEn:"Cultivate your child's spirit of scientific exploration and detailed observation skills, laying the foundation for early STEM learning.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents feel this microscope is one of the best toys in the entire set, and their children can play with it for a long time. However, some parents have complained that the microscope's light is not very bright, and you need to ensure the batteries are installed correctly for it to work."},{name:"图像幻灯片轮和标本夹",englishName:"Image Slide Wheels & Specimen Clip",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"把幻灯片轮放在显微镜下，转动轮子，和宝宝一起观察不同的昆虫和植物。也可以用标本夹夹住树叶或者小花，自己制作标本进行观察，探索微观世界的奥秘。",developmentGoal:"锻炼宝宝的手眼协调能力和精细动作，同时激发他们对自然科学的好奇心。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个配件和显微镜是绝配，大大增加了显微镜的可玩性。孩子们很喜欢自己动手制作标本。不过有家长提到，幻灯片轮比较小，需要小心保管，以免丢失。",howToUseEn:"Place the slide wheel under the microscope, turn the wheel, and observe different insects and plants with your child. You can also use the specimen clip to hold leaves or small flowers, creating your own specimens for observation and exploring the mysteries of the microscopic world.",developmentGoalEn:"Develop your child's hand-eye coordination and fine motor skills, while also sparking their curiosity about natural science.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally agree that this accessory is a perfect match for the microscope, greatly increasing its playability. Children love making their own specimens. However, some parents have mentioned that the slide wheels are quite small and need to be stored carefully to avoid getting lost."},{name:"木制模块化村庄和通道",englishName:"Wooden Modular Village & Pathways",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这套玩具包含了很多可以自由拼接的道路和建筑外墙。和宝宝一起搭建一个属于你们自己的小村庄吧！可以把小房子排成一排，也可以用道路把它们连接起来，创造出不同的场景和故事。",developmentGoal:"鼓励宝宝发挥想象力和创造力，进行开放式游戏。同时，拼接的动作可以锻炼宝宝的精细动作和空间思维能力。",parentReview:"很多家长喜欢这套玩具的开放性，可以和很多其他玩具搭配玩，比如小汽车、小人偶。孩子们用它搭建了各种各样的村庄。但也有家长反映，木制外墙比较薄，如果玩得太用力可能会损坏。",howToUseEn:"This toy set includes many freely connectable roads and building facades. Build your own little village with your child! You can line up the small houses in a row, or connect them with roads to create different scenes and stories.",developmentGoalEn:"Encourage your child to use their imagination and creativity for open-ended play. At the same time, the act of piecing things together can exercise your child's fine motor skills and spatial thinking abilities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love the open-ended nature of this toy, as it can be combined with many other toys like small cars and figurines. Children have used it to build all sorts of villages. However, some parents have reported that the wooden facades are quite thin and may get damaged if played with too roughly."},{name:"朋友和秋千套装",englishName:"Friends & Swing Set",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这套玩具里有两个可爱的小人偶（Alia和Jaeyong）和一个秋千。可以把小人偶放在秋千上，轻轻地推他们，假装在公园里玩耍。还可以把他们带到你用模块化村庄搭建的场景里，进行角色扮演游戏。",developmentGoal:"通过角色扮演，帮助宝宝发展社交情感技能和语言能力，并锻炼他们的想象力。",parentReview:"家长们觉得这套小人偶很可爱，特别是其中一个角色坐在轮椅上，这为向孩子介绍多样性和包容性提供了很好的机会。孩子们喜欢把他们放在秋千上玩。一些评论提到，如果能有更多不同肤色和特征的人偶会更好。",howToUseEn:"This toy set includes two adorable little figurines (Alia and Jaeyong) and a swing. You can place the figurines on the swing and gently push them, pretending to play in a park. You can also bring them into the scenes you've built with the modular village for role-playing games.",developmentGoalEn:"Through role-playing, help your child develop social-emotional skills and language abilities, while also exercising their imagination.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find the figurines very cute, especially since one of the characters is in a wheelchair, which provides a great opportunity to introduce children to diversity and inclusion. Children love playing with them on the swing. Some reviews mentioned that it would be even better if there were more figurines with different skin tones and features."},{name:"发明家冒险包",englishName:"Inventor Adventure Pack",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个可以两面使用的腰包，上面有各种可以操作的机关，比如拉链、扣环和口袋。鼓励宝宝自己动手探索，把喜欢的小物件放进包里，像个小发明家一样去冒险。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具可以极大地锻炼宝宝的精细动作技能和手眼协调能力。同时，也能激发他们的好奇心和探索欲。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个冒险包设计得很巧妙，孩子们很喜欢摆弄上面的各种机关。它也很适合带出门，可以把一些小玩具装在里面。一些家长提到，腰包的带子对于小一点的孩子来说可能有点长。",howToUseEn:"This is a reversible fanny pack with various interactive features like zippers, buckles, and pockets. Encourage your child to explore it on their own, put their favorite small items in the pack, and go on an adventure like a little inventor.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy can greatly exercise your child's fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination. At the same time, it can also stimulate their curiosity and desire to explore.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally think this adventure pack is cleverly designed, and children love fiddling with the various mechanisms on it. It's also great for taking on the go, as you can pack some small toys inside. Some parents have mentioned that the strap of the fanny pack might be a bit long for smaller children."},{name:"每日帮手板",englishName:"Daily Helper Board",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"这是一个磁性木质板，可以帮助宝宝建立日常惯例。和宝宝一起讨论每天需要做的事情，比如自己穿衣服、帮忙做家务等，然后把相应的磁力贴放在板子上。这能让宝宝了解哪些事情需要别人帮忙，哪些可以自己独立完成。",developmentGoal:"培养宝宝的责任感、独立性和时间观念，同时促进亲子沟通和协作。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，这个帮手板对于培养孩子的独立性非常有帮助，孩子很乐意参与到家务中来。不过，也有家长提到，磁力贴比较小，需要注意不要让小宝宝误食。",howToUseEn:"This is a magnetic wooden board that can help your child establish daily routines. Discuss with your child the things that need to be done each day, such as getting dressed on their own or helping with chores, and then place the corresponding magnets on the board. This helps your child understand which tasks require help from others and which they can do independently.",developmentGoalEn:"Cultivate your child's sense of responsibility, independence, and time management, while also promoting parent-child communication and collaboration.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents have reported that this helper board is very helpful in fostering their child's independence, and their children are happy to participate in household chores. However, some parents have mentioned that the magnets are quite small and care should be taken to prevent young children from swallowing them."},{name:"英迪学游泳",englishName:"Indie Swims Book",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"和宝宝一起阅读这本书，讲述了小主角英迪在学习游泳时如何克服恐惧的故事。可以和宝宝讨论书中人物的感受，并联系宝宝自己的生活经验，比如第一次尝试新事物时的心情。",developmentGoal:"通过故事帮助宝宝理解和处理自己的情绪，特别是面对恐惧和犹豫时。同时，也能培养宝宝的阅读习惯和语言理解能力。",parentReview:"家长们认为这本书对于帮助孩子克服对水的恐惧很有帮助，故事内容很贴近生活。书中的插画也很精美。一些家长提到，如果能有更多关于游泳技巧的细节会更有趣。",howToUseEn:"Read this book with your child, which tells the story of how the main character, Indie, overcomes fear while learning to swim. You can discuss the feelings of the characters in the book with your child and connect them to your child's own life experiences, such as their feelings when trying something new for the first time.",developmentGoalEn:"Through the story, help your child understand and process their own emotions, especially when facing fear and hesitation. At the same time, it can also cultivate your child's reading habits and language comprehension skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents believe this book is very helpful for helping children overcome their fear of water, and the story is very relatable. The illustrations in the book are also beautiful. Some parents mentioned that it would be more interesting if there were more details about swimming techniques."}]},{id:"examiner",name:"The Examiner",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-examiner",ageRange:"52-54 个月",ageRangeEn:"52-54 months",ageMonths:"52-54m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#307085",bgColor:"#E4EAF0",lightColor:"#D3E0EB",description:"52-54个月的孩子眼睛已经进化成了高倍显微镜——能发现你袜子上的小洞、注意到两本书封面颜色「不完全一样」。最让家长又惊喜又有点头疼的变化是：他不再什么都信了。批判性思维是好事，但你会发现和一个4岁半的孩子辩论时你不一定能赢。",descriptionEn:"A 52-54 month old's eyes have evolved into high-powered microscopes - able to spot the small hole in your sock and notice that the cover colors of two books are 'not exactly the same'. The most surprising and somewhat headache-inducing change for parents is: they no longer believe everything. Critical thinking is a good thing, but you'll find that you may not always win an argument with a 4.5-year-old.",toys:[{name:"一周计划板",englishName:"Plan Ahead Week Board",category:"认知/语言",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Language",howToUse:"和宝宝一起用可定制的磁力贴来计划一周的活动吧！可以把本周的特殊事件，比如去公园、看医生或者家庭聚会，都放在板子上，帮助宝宝直观地理解时间的流逝和未来的计划。",developmentGoal:"帮助孩子理解过去、现在和未来的时间概念，培养初步的计划和组织能力。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个周计划板对于帮助孩子理解一周的日程安排非常有帮助，特别是对于有特殊活动的日子。但也有一些家长反映，对于年龄小一些的宝宝来说，可能需要父母更多的引导才能理解。",howToUseEn:"Plan the week's activities with your baby using customizable magnetic stickers! You can put special events for the week, like going to the park, a doctor's appointment, or a family gathering, on the board to help your baby visually understand the passage of time and future plans.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps children understand the concepts of past, present, and future, and develops preliminary planning and organizational skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this weekly planning board very helpful for helping their children understand the week's schedule, especially for days with special activities. However, some parents have reported that younger babies may need more parental guidance to understand it."},{name:"韵律环",englishName:"Rhyming Rings",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一个有趣的游戏，可以帮助宝宝学习押韵！先把所有的环片拿出来，和宝宝一起念出每个图片的名字。然后，鼓励宝宝找出读音相似的图片，把它们连成一个彩色的圆环。",developmentGoal:"通过识别和匹配押韵的单词，锻炼宝宝的音韵意识和早期语言能力，为阅读打下基础。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具对培养孩子的语言能力很有帮助，特别是对刚刚开始学习押韵的孩子来说。有些家长提到，一开始可能需要父母的耐心引导，但一旦孩子掌握了玩法，就会非常喜欢。",howToUseEn:"This is a fun game to help your baby learn to rhyme! First, take out all the ring pieces and say the name of each picture with your baby. Then, encourage your baby to find the pictures with similar-sounding names and connect them to form a colorful ring.",developmentGoalEn:"Develops your baby's phonological awareness and early language skills by identifying and matching rhyming words, laying the foundation for reading.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe that this toy is very helpful for developing children's language skills, especially for children who are just beginning to learn to rhyme. Some parents mentioned that it may require patient guidance from parents at first, but once the child masters the gameplay, they will love it."},{name:"造型沙和可擦拭垫",englishName:"Modeling Sand & Wipeable Mat",category:"感官/认知",categoryEn:"Sensory/Cognitive",howToUse:"把可擦拭垫铺开，然后把造型沙倒在上面，让宝宝尽情地感受沙子独特的质感吧！鼓励他用手去抓、去捏、去塑造各种形状，或者使用一些小工具来挖掘和创作。垫子可以很好地收集散落的沙子，让游戏后的清理变得轻松。",developmentGoal:"这是一款非常棒的感官游戏玩具，可以满足宝宝的触觉探索需求，同时在抓握和塑造沙子的过程中，锻炼他们的精细动作技能和创造力。",parentReview:"家长们很喜欢这款造型沙，认为它为孩子提供了一种很棒的感官体验，而且配套的垫子解决了清理的大问题。有些评论提到，沙子本身质量很好，不容易干，可以重复玩很久。不过，也有家长提醒，尽管有垫子，最好还是在容易打扫的地方玩，因为沙子还是有可能被带到别处。",howToUseEn:"Spread out the wipeable mat, then pour the modeling sand on top and let your baby enjoy the unique texture of the sand! Encourage them to grab, pinch, and shape it, or use small tools to dig and create. The mat does a great job of collecting scattered sand, making cleanup after playtime a breeze.",developmentGoalEn:"This is a fantastic sensory toy that satisfies your baby's need for tactile exploration while also exercising their fine motor skills and creativity as they grip and shape the sand.",parentReviewEn:"Parents love this modeling sand, believing it provides a great sensory experience for their children, and the accompanying mat solves the big problem of cleanup. Some reviews mentioned that the sand itself is of good quality, doesn't dry out easily, and can be played with for a long time. However, some parents reminded that even with the mat, it's best to play in an easy-to-clean area, as sand can still be tracked elsewhere."},{name:"单元积木和活动卡片",englishName:"Unit Block Builders & Activity Cards",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套玩具将积木和数学概念结合在了一起。可以先让宝宝自由探索这些积木，感受不同的大小和形状。然后，拿出活动卡片，和宝宝一起按照卡片上的图案来搭建，或者用积木来完成一些简单的数学题目，比如数数和比较大小。",developmentGoal:"通过搭建和解决卡片上的问题，帮助宝宝发展空间想象力、手眼协调能力和初步的数学思维。这也是一个很好的培养解决问题能力的玩具。",parentReview:"很多家长都称赞这套积木质量很好，而且将积木和数学、解谜等活动结合起来非常有创意。有评论说，活动卡片增加了积木的可玩性，让孩子能玩更久。但也有家长提到，对于年龄较小的孩子，可能需要家长的更多陪伴和指导才能理解卡片上的任务。",howToUseEn:"This toy combines building blocks with mathematical concepts. You can first let your baby freely explore the blocks and feel the different sizes and shapes. Then, take out the activity cards and build according to the patterns on the cards with your baby, or use the blocks to complete some simple math problems, such as counting and comparing sizes.",developmentGoalEn:"Helps your baby develop spatial imagination, hand-eye coordination, and preliminary mathematical thinking by building and solving the problems on the cards. This is also a great toy for cultivating problem-solving skills.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents praise the high quality of these blocks and the creative combination of blocks with activities like math and puzzles. Some reviews say that the activity cards increase the playability of the blocks, allowing children to play for longer. However, some parents mentioned that for younger children, more parental companionship and guidance may be needed to understand the tasks on the cards."},{name:"表演、讲述和思考共情游戏",englishName:"Show, Tell & Think Empathy Game",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一款培养孩子情商的卡片游戏。和孩子轮流抽取卡片，根据卡片上的提示，表演一个场景、讲述一个关于情绪的故事，或者想象自己在某种情境下会怎么做。通过角色扮演和讨论，引导孩子理解和表达自己的情绪，并学会站在他人的角度思考问题。",developmentGoal:"这款游戏旨在培养孩子的共情能力、情绪智力和社交技能。通过模拟各种社交场景，帮助孩子学会识别、理解和应对自己和他人的情绪，提升人际交往能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款游戏是教导学龄前儿童共情和理解他人感受的绝佳工具。有评论提到，游戏中的场景非常贴近生活，能有效引发孩子的思考和讨论。一些家长表示，这款游戏不仅对孩子有益，也让他们自己学会了如何更好地与孩子沟通情感。",howToUseEn:"This is a card game that cultivates children's emotional intelligence. Take turns with your child drawing cards and, according to the prompts on the cards, act out a scene, tell a story about an emotion, or imagine what you would do in a certain situation. Through role-playing and discussion, guide your child to understand and express their own emotions, and learn to think from others' perspectives.",developmentGoalEn:"This game aims to cultivate children's empathy, emotional intelligence, and social skills. By simulating various social scenarios, it helps children learn to identify, understand, and respond to their own and others' emotions, and improve their interpersonal skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally believe this game is an excellent tool for teaching preschoolers empathy and understanding the feelings of others. Some reviews mentioned that the scenarios in the game are very relatable to real life and can effectively spark children's thinking and discussion. Some parents said that this game is not only beneficial for their children but has also taught them how to better communicate emotions with their children."},{name:"时间和比较秒表",englishName:"Time & Compare Stopwatch",category:"认知",categoryEn:"Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一个真正的秒表，可以用来和宝宝一起玩各种计时游戏！比如，比赛谁能更快地把积木搭高，或者记录宝宝完成一个拼图需要多长时间。通过转动数字拨盘和观察电子显示屏，让宝宝对时间有更具体的认识。",developmentGoal:"这款秒表帮助孩子将抽象的时间概念具象化，通过计时和比较，培养他们的数学思维和竞争意识，同时也能在游戏中锻炼他们的专注力。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，孩子对这个秒表非常着迷，喜欢用它来给各种活动计时，增加了许多日常乐趣。有评论说，这是帮助孩子理解‘多长时间’这个概念的绝佳工具。不过，也有家长提到，需要引导孩子正确使用，避免他们过于沉迷于‘快’和‘慢’的比较，而忽略了活动本身的乐趣。",howToUseEn:"This is a real stopwatch that you can use to play various timing games with your baby! For example, you can race to see who can build a tower of blocks the fastest, or time how long it takes for your baby to complete a puzzle. By turning the number dial and observing the electronic display, your baby can get a more concrete understanding of time.",developmentGoalEn:"This stopwatch helps children visualize the abstract concept of time. Through timing and comparison, it cultivates their mathematical thinking and competitive awareness, while also exercising their concentration during games.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report that their children are fascinated by this stopwatch and love to use it to time all sorts of activities, which adds a lot of daily fun. Some reviews say it's an excellent tool for helping children understand the concept of 'how long.' However, some parents mentioned the need to guide children to use it correctly and prevent them from becoming too obsessed with comparing 'fast' and 'slow' and ignoring the fun of the activity itself."},{name:"《得体的游戏》",englishName:"'The Appropriate Game' Book",category:"社交情感/认知",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Cognitive",howToUse:"这是一本关于社交规则的绘本。和宝宝一起阅读这个故事，看看书中的伊莎贝尔和路易斯是如何在不同的情境下，学习哪些言行是得体的。读完后，可以和宝宝讨论书中的场景，并联系生活中的例子，帮助他理解在不同的场合需要有不同的行为举止。",developmentGoal:"这本书通过故事的形式，帮助孩子理解和学习社交规则，培养他们的情景意识和社交判断力，让他们知道在不同的家庭和公共场合，应该如何得体地表达自己。",parentReview:"家长们认为这本书对于教导孩子理解复杂的社交规则非常有帮助。书中的故事和情景都很贴近生活，容易引起孩子的共鸣。有评论说，这本书引发了许多有意义的家庭讨论，帮助家长和孩子一起探讨了‘得体’这个概念。一些家长表示，这是他们处理孩子在公共场合行为问题的一个很好的切入点。",howToUseEn:"This is a picture book about social rules. Read the story with your baby and see how Isabel and Louis in the book learn what words and actions are appropriate in different situations. After reading, you can discuss the scenes in the book with your baby and connect them to real-life examples to help them understand that different behaviors are required in different situations.",developmentGoalEn:"Through storytelling, this book helps children understand and learn social rules, cultivating their situational awareness and social judgment, so they know how to express themselves appropriately in different family and public settings.",parentReviewEn:"Parents find this book very helpful for teaching children to understand complex social rules. The stories and situations in the book are very relatable and easily resonate with children. Some reviews say that this book has sparked many meaningful family discussions, helping parents and children explore the concept of 'appropriateness' together. Some parents said it was a good starting point for them to address their children's behavioral issues in public."}]},{id:"persister",name:"The Persister",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-persister",ageRange:"55-57 个月",ageRangeEn:"55-57 months",ageMonths:"55-57m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#246A7D",bgColor:"#E2E8EE",lightColor:"#D0DEE9",description:"55-57个月的孩子终于能「坐得住」了。以前遇到稍微有点难的东西就秒放弃，现在能看到他皱着眉头、咬着下嘴唇、反复尝试。专注力出现质的飞跃。面对挫折时虽然还是会哭，但开始能在哭完之后自己说「我再试一次」。",descriptionEn:`At 55-57 months, children finally reach a stage where they can "sit still" and focus! Before, they might have given up in a flash the moment something seemed a little challenging. Now, you can observe them with furrowed brows, biting their lower lip, and trying again and again. Their concentration has truly made a qualitative leap! While they might still cry when faced with frustration, they're beginning to say, "I'll try again," after they've had their cry.`,toys:[{name:"蒙特梭利活动字母与实物套装",englishName:"Montessori Movable Alphabet Game",category:"认知/语言",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Language",howToUse:"一套彩色字母块搭配相应的小实物。先从孩子名字里的字母开始，然后做拼读练习。",developmentGoal:"字母认知。拼读意识。早期读写准备。精细运动。语言与实物对应。",parentReview:"蒙特梭利活动字母是经典语言教具——通过动手操作字母比看卡片学得快。",howToUseEn:"This set includes a collection of colorful letter blocks and corresponding small objects. Start with the letters in your child's name, then move on to spelling and reading exercises.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps with letter recognition, phonological awareness, and early literacy preparation. It also develops fine motor skills and the connection between language and real-world objects.",parentReviewEn:"The Montessori movable alphabet is a classic language tool—learning is faster through hands-on manipulation of letters compared to just looking at flashcards."},{name:"蒙氏语言教具",englishName:"Montessori Language Objects",category:"语言/认知",categoryEn:"Language/Cognitive",howToUse:"这套玩具包含一些可爱的小物件，比如小动物、小水果等，可以和蒙氏可移动字母游戏搭配使用。爸爸妈妈可以先用字母拼出物体的英文单词，然后让宝宝找到对应的物品，或者反过来，先拿出物品，让宝宝尝试拼写出它的名字。",developmentGoal:"这套教具旨在帮助孩子建立实物和抽象词汇之间的联系，是语言学习中的重要一步。通过触摸和观察真实的物体，孩子能更深刻地理解词语的含义，从而扩大词汇量。",parentReview:"很多家长反映，这些小物件非常精致可爱，能有效吸引孩子的注意力，让学习过程变得更有趣。不过，也有家长提到，因为物件比较小，需要特别注意，防止宝宝误食。一些家长还希望物件的种类能更丰富一些。",howToUseEn:"This toy set includes a variety of adorable small objects, such as little animals and fruits, which can be used in conjunction with the Montessori Movable Alphabet Game. Parents can start by spelling out the English word for an object with the letter tiles and then have their child find the corresponding item. Or, they can do the reverse: present the object first and encourage their child to try and spell its name.",developmentGoalEn:"This educational tool is designed to help children build a strong connection between tangible objects and abstract words, a crucial step in language acquisition. By touching and observing real items, children can gain a deeper understanding of word meanings, which in turn expands their vocabulary.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents have commented on how exquisite and adorable these small objects are, noting that they effectively capture a child's attention and make the learning process more engaging. However, some parents have also mentioned that because the objects are quite small, it's important to supervise closely to prevent accidental ingestion. A few parents have also expressed a desire for a wider variety of objects in the set."},{name:"路径搭建弹珠迷宫",englishName:"Path Builder Marble Maze",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这款玩具是一个可以自己动手搭建的弹珠迷宫。爸爸妈妈可以鼓励宝宝尝试不同的拼接方式，为弹珠创造出一条可以滚动的通道。这是一个需要不断试错的游戏，当弹珠成功到达终点时，宝宝会非常有成就感。",developmentGoal:"这款玩具能够锻炼宝宝解决问题的能力、空间想象力和精细动作技能。同时，在不断尝试和失败的过程中，也能培养宝宝的耐心和抗挫折能力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这款玩具趣味性十足，又能锻炼娃的动脑能力，能让孩子玩上很久。不过也有家长提醒，弹珠比较小，需要注意别让年龄小的宝宝误食。",howToUseEn:"This toy is a build-it-yourself marble maze. Parents can encourage their little one to try different ways of connecting the pieces to create a rolling path for the marble. It's a game of trial and error, and when the marble successfully reaches the end, your child will feel a great sense of accomplishment.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy helps develop your little one’s problem-solving skills, spatial imagination, and fine motor skills. At the same time, the process of continuous trial and error also cultivates their patience and resilience in the face of challenges.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally agree that this toy is a lot of fun and a great way to get their kids thinking, keeping them engaged for a long time. However, some parents have also pointed out that the marbles are quite small, so it's important to be careful and make sure younger children don’t accidentally swallow them."},{name:"绘画描摹擦写板",englishName:"Draw, Trace & Erase Board",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个可以反复擦写的画板，宝宝可以在上面自由地画画，也可以用附带的卡片来练习描摹字母和单词。画板配有便携袋，很适合带出门玩。",developmentGoal:"这款画板主要锻炼宝宝的精细动作和手眼协调能力，为将来学习书写打下基础。通过描摹练习，宝宝可以形成对字母和文字的视觉和肌肉记忆。",parentReview:"家长们普遍觉得这个画板很实用，既能满足宝宝的涂鸦兴趣，又能为写字做准备。便携的设计也受到了好评，方便带出去在路上玩。有些家长提到，如果能配有更多不同主题的描摹卡片就更好了。",howToUseEn:"This is a fantastic reusable drawing board that lets your child unleash their creativity and draw to their heart's content. It also comes with handy cards for practicing tracing letters and words, which is a wonderful way to build early literacy skills. The drawing board includes a portable bag, making it easy to take along for fun on the go.",developmentGoalEn:"This drawing board is designed to help your little one develop essential fine motor skills and hand-eye coordination. It's a fantastic tool that lays a strong foundation for future writing! Through tracing activities, children can build both visual and muscle memory for letters and words.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this drawing board very practical. It not only satisfies their little one's urge to doodle but also helps them prepare for writing. The portable design has also received positive feedback, making it easy to take along and keep kids entertained on the go. Some parents have mentioned that it would be even better if it came with more tracing cards featuring different themes."},{name:"平静小圈",englishName:"Calming Circle",category:"社交情感/感官",categoryEn:"Social-Emotional/Sensory",howToUse:"这是一个可以握在手里的小玩具，配合呼吸练习卡片使用。当宝宝感到焦虑或者沮丧时，爸爸妈妈可以引导他/她握住这个小圈，然后跟着卡片上的指示，进行深呼吸，帮助情绪平复下来。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具主要是为了帮助宝宝学会情绪调节和自我安抚。通过具体可感的物体和呼吸练习，宝宝可以学习到管理自己情绪的有效方法。",parentReview:"很多家长觉得这个小工具在帮助孩子冷静下来方面非常有效，尤其是在孩子发脾气或者感到不安的时候。它的尺寸和材质也很适合小手抓握。但也有家长认为，它的作用因人而异，对于有些孩子可能效果不明显。",howToUseEn:"A small toy designed to be held in little hands, perfect for use with the breathing exercise cards. When your child feels anxious or upset, guide them to hold this ring and follow the card instructions to practice deep breathing, helping their emotions settle.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy is primarily designed to help your little one learn emotional regulation and self-soothing skills. By engaging with a tangible object and practicing breathing exercises, your baby can discover effective ways to manage their feelings.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents find this little tool to be incredibly effective in helping their children calm down, especially during tantrums or when they're feeling anxious. Its size and material are also perfectly suited for little hands to grasp. However, some parents feel that its effectiveness can vary from child to child, and it might not work as well for everyone."},{name:"呼吸活动指南",englishName:"Breathing Activities Guide",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一套卡片，上面介绍了几种不同的呼吸练习方法，比如“彩虹呼吸”和“大象呼吸”。爸爸妈妈可以在宝宝情绪激动时，或者在睡前，引导宝宝跟着卡片上的图示和说明，一起做这些有趣的呼吸练习，帮助宝宝放松和平静。",developmentGoal:"这套指南旨在教给宝宝具体的情绪调节技巧。通过将呼吸练习游戏化，宝宝能更容易地学会如何通过深呼吸来管理自己的情绪，这对他们的心理健康发展非常有益。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这套呼吸指南非常实用，图示清晰可爱，很容易吸引孩子的兴趣。很多家长表示，这些练习不仅能帮助孩子平复情绪，也让亲子关系更加融洽。有些家长建议，如果卡片能更厚实耐用一些就更好了。",howToUseEn:"A set of cards introducing several breathing exercises like 'Rainbow Breath' and 'Elephant Breath.' Parents can guide children to follow the illustrated instructions and practice these fun exercises together — a great way to help your child relax, especially when feeling overwhelmed or before bedtime.",developmentGoalEn:"This guide is designed to teach your little one specific emotion regulation skills. By turning breathing exercises into fun games, your child will more easily learn how to use deep breaths to manage their feelings. This is incredibly beneficial for their developing mental well-being.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this set of breathing guides incredibly practical. The illustrations are clear and adorable, making them very engaging for children. Many parents have shared that these exercises not only help their children calm down but also foster a more harmonious parent-child relationship. Some parents suggested that the cards would be even better if they were a bit thicker and more durable."},{name:"《吉莉和杰特》",englishName:"'Jilly & Jett' Book",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一本关于情绪管理的绘本。爸爸妈妈可以和宝宝一起阅读这个故事，故事讲述了小主人公杰特如何在一个朋友的帮助下，学会使用平静小圈来处理自己的失望情绪。共读时，可以和宝宝讨论故事内容，引导他们理解和表达自己的情绪。",developmentGoal:"这本绘本旨在通过故事的形式，教给宝宝如何识别和应对挫败感等复杂的负面情绪。它能帮助宝宝发展情商和同理心，并学会寻求和接受帮助。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这本书的故事内容非常贴近生活，能帮助孩子更好地理解和处理自己的情绪。书中的插画也很精美，能吸引孩子的注意力。一些家长提到，这本书和‘平静小圈’玩具结合使用，效果更好。",howToUseEn:'This is a picture book all about managing emotions. Grown-ups and little ones can read this story together. It follows our main character, Jett, as he learns to use a "calming circle" to handle his feelings of disappointment, with a little help from a friend. As you read together, you can chat with your child about the story, gently guiding them to understand and express their own emotions.',developmentGoalEn:"This wonderful picture book is designed to help your little one understand and navigate tricky emotions like frustration, all through a captivating story. It's a fantastic tool for nurturing their emotional intelligence and empathy, and for teaching them the important lesson of seeking and accepting help when they need it.",parentReviewEn:"Parents widely praise this book for its relatable stories, which truly help children understand and manage their emotions better. The illustrations are also beautiful and do a wonderful job of capturing children's attention. Several parents have even mentioned that using this book alongside the 'Calm Circle' toy enhances the experience and makes it even more effective."}]},{id:"planner",name:"The Planner",officialUrl:"https://lovevery.com/products/the-play-kits-the-planner",ageRange:"58-60 个月",ageRangeEn:"58-60 months",ageMonths:"58-60m",stage:"preschool",stageLabel:"学前阶段",stageLabelEn:"Preschool Stage",color:"#186475",bgColor:"#E0E6EC",lightColor:"#CDDCE7",description:"快5岁了！孩子站在学龄的门口了。最让家长欣慰的变化不是会认几个字、会数到几——而是「规划」意识的真正萌芽。这是Lovevery的最后一个Play Kit——用时钟、任务板和颜色计时器把「时间」和「计划」从抽象概念变成孩子能亲手操作的实物。",descriptionEn:"Almost 5 years old! Your child is standing at the doorstep of school age. The most gratifying change for parents is not how many words they can recognize or how high they can count—but the true budding of a sense of 'planning.' This is Lovevery's last Play Kit—using a clock, a task board, and a color timer to turn the abstract concepts of 'time' and 'planning' into tangible objects that children can operate with their own hands.",toys:[{name:"计划与准备时钟套装",englishName:"Plan & Prepare Clock with Mini Clock",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这款时钟可以帮助孩子学习时间管理。你可以用不同颜色的时间块来标记不同的活动，比如15分钟的阅读时间或10分钟的清理时间，让孩子直观地看到时间的流逝。迷你时钟可以让孩子随身携带，练习认读时间。",developmentGoal:"培养时间意识和自我管理能力，为入学做准备。通过可视化的时间块，帮助孩子理解抽象的时间概念，学习规划和安排日常活动。",parentReview:"很多家长说这个时钟帮助孩子建立了时间概念。Reddit上有家长分享说孩子现在会自己说'再过两个蓝色块就该吃饭了'。迷你时钟的设计很受孩子欢迎，会随身带着。有家长建议配合日常作息表使用效果更好。",howToUseEn:"This clock helps children learn time management. You can use different colored time blocks to mark various activities, like 15 minutes for reading or 10 minutes for cleanup, allowing your child to visually track the passage of time. The mini clock is portable for practicing time-telling on the go.",developmentGoalEn:"Cultivates time awareness and self-management skills in preparation for school. The visual time blocks help children grasp the abstract concept of time and learn to plan their daily activities.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents report this clock helped their children develop a concept of time. One parent on Reddit shared that their child now says things like, 'Two more blue blocks until dinner!' The mini clock's design is a big hit, and kids love carrying it around. Some suggest using it with a daily routine chart for even better results."},{name:"动态能量木制球坡道",englishName:"Energy-In-Motion Wooden Ball Ramps",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套玩具包含多个可拼接的木制坡道，孩子可以自由组合，搭建不同的轨道。然后将小球放在最高处，观察它如何沿着轨道滚落。你可以鼓励孩子尝试不同的组合，看看小球的滚动速度和路径会有什么变化。",developmentGoal:"这个玩具能激发孩子的好奇心和探索欲，帮助他们理解因果关系和基础的物理概念，如重力、速度和动量。搭建不同的轨道也能锻炼他们的解决问题能力和创造力。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这个玩具很有趣，能让孩子玩上很久。特别是对于喜欢看东西滚来滚去的孩子来说，吸引力十足。很多评论提到，它不仅好玩，还能引导孩子思考，‘怎么样才能让小球滚得更快？’。不过也有家长反映，对于年龄大一点的孩子，如果只是简单地看着小球滚动，可能会觉得有些单调。",howToUseEn:"This set includes multiple connectable wooden ramps that your child can arrange to build various tracks. Place the small ball at the top and watch it roll down. Encourage your child to experiment with different configurations to see how the ball's speed and path change.",developmentGoalEn:"This toy sparks curiosity and exploration, helping children understand cause-and-effect and basic physics concepts like gravity, speed, and momentum. Building different tracks also enhances their problem-solving skills and creativity.",parentReviewEn:"Parents generally find this toy very engaging, keeping children occupied for a long time. It's especially appealing to kids who love watching things roll. Many reviews mention that it's not just fun but also encourages thinking, like 'How can I make the ball roll faster?' However, some parents note that older children might find it a bit monotonous if they only watch the ball roll."},{name:"漫游车路线",englishName:"Rover Route",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这是一个有趣的棋盘游戏，可以为编程思维打下基础。你和孩子可以轮流掷骰子，然后根据骰子上的指示（比如直行、左转、右转）来放置路径卡片，为漫游车规划一条从起点到终点的路线。这个过程需要提前思考和计划。",developmentGoal:"这个游戏可以锻炼孩子的视觉规划、顺序思考和解决问题的能力，这些都是早期编程思维的重要组成部分。同时，它也能帮助孩子学习遵循规则和轮流等待。",parentReview:"很多家长都喜欢这个玩具，认为它用一种非常直观和有趣的方式介绍了编程的基本概念。孩子们很喜欢自己动手为小车铺路。一些评论提到，这个游戏可以有很多变化，比如增加障碍物，让它变得更有挑战性。暂时没有看到太多负面评价，普遍认为它是一款设计得很好的益智游戏。",howToUseEn:"This is a fun board game that lays the foundation for computational thinking. You and your child can take turns rolling the dice and placing path cards according to the instructions (e.g., straight, left, right) to plan a route for the rover from start to finish. This process requires forethought and planning.",developmentGoalEn:"This game develops your child's visual planning, sequential thinking, and problem-solving skills, which are all crucial components of early computational thinking. It also helps them learn to follow rules and take turns.",parentReviewEn:"Many parents love this toy for introducing basic programming concepts in a very intuitive and fun way. Kids enjoy building the path for the rover themselves. Some comments suggest that the game can be varied, for example, by adding obstacles to make it more challenging. There are not many negative reviews, and it is generally considered a well-designed educational game."},{name:"灵活四格图案配对",englishName:"Flex-Four Pattern Match",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这个玩具包含一个有四个可以活动的彩色方块的底板和一系列图案卡片。孩子需要根据卡片上的图案，移动和旋转底板上的彩色方块，来复制出卡片上的图案。你可以先从简单的图案开始，然后逐渐增加难度。",developmentGoal:"这个游戏可以锻炼孩子的空间想象能力、手眼协调能力和解决问题的能力。通过匹配图案，孩子可以学习识别和复制复杂的视觉信息，这对未来的数学和逻辑学习很有帮助。",parentReview:"家长们普遍认为这是一个非常棒的便携玩具，很适合在旅行或者外出就餐时给孩子玩。它安静、小巧，而且很有挑战性。很多评论提到，这个游戏不仅孩子喜欢，连大人也觉得很有趣。一些家长建议，如果家里有两个孩子，最好能有两个，因为孩子们会抢着玩。",howToUseEn:"This toy includes a base with four movable colored blocks and a series of pattern cards. Your child needs to move and rotate the colored blocks on the base to replicate the pattern on the card. You can start with simple patterns and gradually increase the difficulty.",developmentGoalEn:"This game enhances your child's spatial reasoning, hand-eye coordination, and problem-solving abilities. By matching patterns, children learn to recognize and replicate complex visual information, which is beneficial for future math and logic skills.",parentReviewEn:"Parents widely agree that this is a fantastic portable toy, perfect for keeping kids entertained during travel or while dining out. It's quiet, compact, and challenging. Many reviews mention that not only do kids love it, but adults find it fun too. Some parents suggest that if you have two children, it's best to have two sets because they will fight over it."},{name:"快速识数多米诺",englishName:"Subitizing Dominoes",category:"认知/精细运动",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Fine Motor",howToUse:"这套多米诺骨牌可以用来玩传统的配对游戏，但它的主要目的是练习‘快速识数’（Subitizing），也就是不通过数数，而是一眼看出有多少个点。你可以和孩子一起玩，轮流出牌，匹配相同点数的骨牌。",developmentGoal:"这个游戏可以极大地提升孩子的数感和视觉识别能力，为未来的数学学习打下坚实的基础。‘快速识数’是一项重要的早期数学技能，能帮助孩子更快地进行心算和理解数字。",parentReview:"家长们对这套多米诺骨牌的评价很高，认为它是一种有趣又有效的方式来练习数学技能。很多评论提到，孩子们很喜欢这些色彩鲜艳的木制骨牌，而且在玩的过程中不知不觉就学会了快速识别数量。一些家长还分享了他们自己发明的玩法，比如用骨牌来做简单的加法。",howToUseEn:"These dominoes can be used for the traditional matching game, but their main purpose is to practice 'subitizing'—instantly seeing how many without counting. You can play with your child, taking turns to play a domino that matches the number of dots.",developmentGoalEn:"This game significantly improves your child's number sense and visual recognition skills, laying a solid foundation for future math learning. 'Subitizing' is a key early math skill that helps children perform mental calculations and understand numbers more quickly.",parentReviewEn:"Parents have high praise for these dominoes, calling them a fun and effective way to practice math skills. Many reviews mention that children love the colorful wooden dominoes and learn to quickly recognize quantities without even realizing it. Some parents have also shared their own invented games, such as using the dominoes for simple addition."},{name:"《萨维的寻宝之旅》绘本",englishName:"'Savy’s Scavenger Hunt' Book",category:"认知/社交情感",categoryEn:"Cognitive/Social-Emotional",howToUse:"读完后实践：和孩子一起制定一个真正的「寻宝计划」——选地点、制定清单、准备工具、出发寻宝、回顾。",developmentGoal:"规划能力——完整的PDCA循环。观察力。问题解决。语言表达。",parentReview:"最大价值不是读故事本身，而是读完后把故事变成真实活动——带着清单去寻宝。",howToUseEn:"Practice after reading: create a real 'scavenger hunt plan' with your child—choose a location, make a list, prepare tools, go on the hunt, and review.",developmentGoalEn:"Planning ability—a complete PDCA cycle. Observation skills. Problem-solving. Language expression.",parentReviewEn:"The greatest value is not in reading the story itself, but in turning the story into a real activity after reading—going on a scavenger hunt with a list."}]}];function n(e){return o.find(t=>t.id===e)}export{n as g,o as k,a as s};
